 the university\'s faculty of science, technology, engineering, and mathematics, as well as the faculty of geography. The narrator is Byron, a student at the university. He\'s interested in plants, and particularly in a group of them called the Amalanchier family, which includes the Juneberry, the Shadbush, and the Saskatoonberry. He listens to the program every week to learn more about these plants. The first thing he does is read a book called \"Shrubs of Ontario\" by James H Soper. The book is written in the early 1980s, and it was put out only in 1982. The narrator notes that the name \"Amlancier\" comes from the French word for \"honey.\" He also notes that some of the flowers are long and some are short. He notes that there are many different kinds of plants that live in the same place, and that it\'s hard to tell which ones are the same. He also says that he likes the fruit, which is a bright red, and then fades to a dark purple. He names his bike Juneberry in honor of the berries. He decides to read some of John Eastman\'s book \"Forest and Thicket\" because he\'s really interested in how it describes plants. It describes plants in very simple terms. The',NULL,'The narrator tells the story of plants that live in the land'),(61345,86,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/07/17/The Deep House Project - July 17, 2023 at 22:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-07-17 22:00:00',86507648,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(61346,79,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/07/24/Breezy Breakfast Radio - July 24, 2023 at 10:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-07-24 10:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-09 03:29:58',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(61347,85,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/07/17/Ripcord Radio - July 17, 2023 at 21:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-07-17 21:00:00',86507648,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(61349,78,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/08/02/Morning Soul Shake-Up! - August 2, 2023 at 08:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-08-02 08:00:00',86507648,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(61350,84,'https://archive.cfru.ca/a