d the way the pollen was moved, and she was able to observe how those plants affected the way their species evolved. Rosalind was also interested in how these plants were able to change over time, so that the different types could mate and produce offspring that were of the same type. Rosalind is particularly interested in the question of \"perfect flowers,\" which she describes as \"wet that tail.\" She is also fascinated with the concept of gender, because \"the concepts of gender are extremely important.\" Rosalind describes a new project called \"Ontario Heritage and Feral Apples.\" The goal of the project is to better understand the distribution and abundance of domestic apples and to study the potential applications of these apples for cider production and wild environments. She also discusses the idea of \"heterozygous,\" which is the definition of a \"high heterozygousion.\"',NULL,'The UM\'s Rosalind explores how plants evolve from cross-breeding to exclusively self-breech'),(62359,108,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/08/27/Wind-Down - August 27, 2023 at 20:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-08-27 20:00:00',86507648,'2023-08-29 13:52:13',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(62360,140,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/08/26/Caribbean Anthology - August 26, 2023 at 17:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-08-26 17:00:00',86507648,'2023-08-29 13:52:44',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(62361,140,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/08/26/Caribbean Anthology - August 26, 2023 at 16:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-08-26 16:00:00',86507648,'2023-08-29 13:52:45',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(62362,138,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/08/26/Sound Magic - August 26, 2023 at 14:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-08-26 14:00:00',86638720,'2023-08-29 13:52:45',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(62363,138,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/08/26/Sound Magic - August 26, 2023 at 13:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-08-26 13:00:00',86507648,'2023-08-29 13:52:45',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(62364,139,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/08/26/Bel Arab