u\'re looking for a great time, check out this list of the most popular songs from the past year on the show. The first song is called O\'sinner off leaving none but small birds from the Body\'s 2021 release. The second song is Dying on the vine from John Cales 1985 release Artificial Intelligence. The third song is Modern Fiction from the Ducks Limited label. The fourth song is Are you sure off of a record called Life is not a lesson from the Avlov label.\n\nAnd the fifth song is Stick from the 2018 release. This is the last song on the list. The program will be celebrating its one year anniversary with some songs from its archives. These songs include Margot Shake from California Gurion, Vivi Live from Whitney Kaye, White Horse from Montreal, and Blind from the swans 1991 release.',NULL,NULL),(64454,122,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/28/Forever Deaf - September 28, 2023 at 22:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-28 22:00:00',86638720,'2023-12-04 18:47:43',NULL,'This week on the show, Dean and Byron talk about the upcoming Kidney Walk and the work of the Die Out Community Workshop. They also talk about how they can use their tools and equipment to help people start their projects. Dean plays a little bit of music from the escape from the fire release he played earlier. He\'s sad to say that Razor has pulled out of their remaining shows in 2023 because of a heart condition. He was hoping to find a band to play in his place while Bob was away, but he has a broken hand and will be out for six weeks.',NULL,NULL),(64464,122,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/29/Forever Deaf - September 29, 2023 at 00:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-29 00:00:00',86638720,'2023-12-05 05:20:43',NULL,'Alice welcomes her listeners back to the show. She\'s played some of her favorite tracks from the past few years. She tells us that she first got sick a few years ago, and that she got a call from Robert Urbanati of Sacrifice. She had a great time talking to him.',NULL,NULL),(64465,122,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/28/Forever Deaf - September 28, 2023 at 23:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-28 23:00:00',86638720,'2023-12-04 15:08:06',NULL,'On this edition of the program, the young artists from the hip-hop collective known as the \"World Youth\" discuss a number of subjects, including impaired boating, the release of a new line of CFRU merchandise, and the latest news from his doctor. First, the group discusses Brain Scans, which are scans of the brain performed every two weeks. Brain Scan is a medical procedure that measures the extent of a tumor and its size.\n\nIt reveals that the tumor is spread throughout the brain, including the brain stem, and that it has tentacles that protrude outward. The tumor has three tiny lesions on its wall, which is why it is inoperable. The doctors hope that a new drug will help them. The next segment of the show is devoted to Hyperia, a type of extreme pain. The music is a combination of text, sword, and anvil from the cycle of the serpent.',NULL,NULL),(64475,122,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/29/Forever Deaf - September 29, 2023 at 01:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-29 01:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-04 14:48:13',NULL,'The program starts with a song called \"Drowning in Silver\" by a band called \"Death Valley Driver\" from Charlottetown, PEI. The first song on the album is called \"Stone Cold\" and the second song is \"Death valley driver\" from \"Deeperable\". The third song is a mini-song called \"Reanimation\". The fourth song is called, \"Goliath\" from the song \"Armageddon\".\n\nThe program ends with a soliloquy by Mac-Catee. He says that he\'s feeling fine and asks listeners to listen to his show next Tuesday at 5:00PM. He also tells listeners that meta-products like Facebook and Google are blocking news from viewers because of Bill C-18. He explains that the university is a campus, community organization and so it shares news and upcoming events as well as learning opportunities. The university is