r the world to participate in the Paris Games, as long as they adhere to the same rules as those in France.\n\nChina is expected to send tens of millions of people away for the week- long National Day holiday. The International Herald Tribune reports that Spanish archaeologists have discovered ancient sandals in a cave. A new report from the United Nations Children\'s Fund says that nearly one-third of unaccompanied children who have tried to cross the Mediterranean to Europe have died in the journey.',NULL,NULL),(64516,123,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/29/Thanks for Listening :) - September 29, 2023 at 09:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-29 09:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-04 13:45:48',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(64517,124,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/29/Planet Groove - September 29, 2023 at 10:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-29 10:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-04 13:29:11',NULL,'The show opens with a little bit of a rundown of the music on the program, which is called \"Planet Groove\" with the \"Funky Blues Doctor\" .\n\nThe show starts off by playing some of the most popular music of all time, like \"Cocaine Blues\" , \"Too Cold to Cry\" and \"I Want to Be your Dog.\" The doctor then goes on to say that he\'s going to perform some more of the Stooges\' stuff, including \"Masters of Punk\" and the \"Shaker Down\" : \"That was Gia Wasted potential. And that was Jamie Standstill\'s Shaker Down.\" The Doctor then gets down to the business of the show, and says that he has a band called \"Great, awesome four-piece band\" that\'s playing some \"live taste, some \"black country communion\" and some \"UFO.\n\n\" The show ends with a discussion of Silence, a new music venue in town, which can be rented out for a fee. If you\'re in the market for a rehearsal space, or a jam space, then you\'ve come to the right place. Sounds is offering a special flat rate rent for $100 per day. Sounds also has a lot of great music on its roster, so you can always count on them to be there when you need them.',NULL,NULL),(64527,1437,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/29/Democracy Now - September 29, 2023 at 11:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-29 11:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-04 13:07:35',NULL,'Meanwhile, the United States is preparing for a government shutdown Saturday night. The Washington Post reports that a group of right-wing Republicans are planning to remove as Speaker of the House the conservative House speaker, John McCarthy. Meanwhile, Vice President Joe Biden warns that the Trump administration\'s embrace of the MAGA and white nationalist movements threatens the democratic process in America. A climate activist interrupts Vice President Biden\'s address in Arizona and asks why the President has not declared a climate emergency to address the growing threat of climate change.',NULL,NULL),(64528,3686,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/29/Volunteer Playlist - September 29, 2023 at 12:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-29 12:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-04 12:44:27',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(64538,126,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/29/Viejoteca - September 29, 2023 at 14:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-29 14:00:00',86638720,'2023-09-29 20:07:17',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(64539,126,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/29/Viejoteca - September 29, 2023 at 13:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-29 13:00:00',86507648,'2023-09-29 20:07:18',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(64549,127,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/29/LiYghTE FM - September 29, 2023 at 16:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-29 16:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-04 12:32:15',NULL,'This is the very first episode of what will be a series of interviews with the host of CFRU\'s 93.3 Liyghte FM, DJ DD. The show begins with a monologue in which the host admits that he is disappointed with the character of the man, who works in a grocery store and has no views on the music of any artist. The host explains that he has heard that the man is trying to \"change the entire universe\" through a \"love revolution.\n\n\" The host goes on to say that he himself is roasting chestnuts and that his station is the \"number one radio program\" in the world when it comes to the roasting of chestnuts. He also says that the number of people who are musicians is a great thing, as it enables people to contribute to the creation of music. He explains that the only reason he is angry or upset about people in music is because they are making money. The only real reason to be angry is because there are too many people making music. The lame commercial reason, he says, is a \"horrid reason\" to make music',NULL,NULL),(64550,1620,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/29/Hellfire Radio - September 29, 2023 at 15:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-09-29 15:00:00',86638720,'2023-12-04 12:13:02',NULL,'This is the second in a three-part series on the value of music. First, we hear about the cool stuff on this page, which includes a cool screen printing, a cool cassette liner notebook, and a CD that says \"Here burn a CD... at the famine\'s C a slash K R U / G E R.\" The CD is called \"Famines,\" and the liner notebook is \"Nardware The Human serviette / Monumental.\" This is a very different scene from the one on the first part of the show. The liner notebook was written by a guy named Nardware, who played punk music in the West Coast.\n\nThe CD and liner notebook are from a similar scene. The first song we hear is \"Elevator To Hell,\" a song about an elevator. This is kind of the first song that we hear that sounds like elevator to hell . The second song is \"The Who and Double Pleading,\" which is about the two guys who go to the bottom of the stairs. The third song is called Elevator To Hell, the Who and the Double pleading. The seventh song is a cool one called \"X Trip,\" which was the first project of Julie Doron, who used to work for Doron Music. The eighth song was \"Eric\'s Trip,\" a band called Rick White.',NULL,NULL),(64560,128,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/09/29/Walkuman Style - September 29, 2