 to 4pm at the main library branch of Guelph. It is for adults. The next event is next Friday from 2pm until 4pm.',NULL,NULL),(64672,148,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/01/Clan Na Gael - October 1, 2023 at 13:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-01 13:00:00',86638720,'2023-12-04 01:50:46',NULL,'The show starts off with a description of the music they\'re playing. It sounds like old times. The first song is a Scottish song called \"The Queen of Argyll\" . The second song is by a Newfoundland man named Terry Kelly, who\'s a singer, songwriter, and musician. The third song is \"Cayley\" , which is a song by Karen Matheson. The fourth song is from a Canadian named Danny Boy, who was a prisoner during the Second World war. The fifth song is another song by Dardian Evans from Myra Times.',NULL,NULL),(64673,148,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/01/Clan Na Gael - October 1, 2023 at 12:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-01 12:00:00',86638720,'2023-12-04 01:09:16',NULL,'The host plays some new songs and tells the audience that he has a new band lined up for them, but he doesn\'t yet have a name for them. He tells them that he\'s got a band called Glass Tiger, which is a rock band from Newmarket. The lead singer is a guy named Rom Scotland, who\'s also from Newmarket, and the band\'s only song is about a Celtic song. And then he tells them about Runrig, another famous Scottish band.',NULL,NULL),(64674,144,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/01/The Underground - October 1, 2023 at 00:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-01 00:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-04 00:44:48',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(64675,146,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/01/The Kookoo Bananas Variety Hour - October 1, 2023 at 10:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-01 10:00:00',86638720,'2023-11-08 15:34:15',NULL,'This week\'s set of songs is by a band called Bodega Run, who have a female singer named Julie Bodega. The song sounds like a game, but the narrator thinks it\'s a great song to start the show off with. He decides 