. The quality of the music is amazing.',NULL,NULL),(64886,178,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/5ax4cf/October_1_2023_EqualizingXDistort90apx.mp3','2023-10-03 16:47:55',287962512,'2023-12-03 11:15:11',NULL,'In this second part of his interview with Josh Nichols, Andre explores the history of music in the city. The first part of the interview focuses on Head Cheese, a band that is playing a show at the Bovine with the Indestructibles on Friday. The second part is about a band called Verify, a power-violence band from Montreal that was originally released in 1981 . The third part of this interview is about the band Neon, a group that was released in 1985 and is best known for its song Billboard Hero.',NULL,NULL),(64892,1437,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/03/Democracy Now - October 3, 2023 at 11:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-03 11:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-03 10:48:58',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(64893,12585,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/03/CFRU Mobile Community Radio Show - October 3, 2023 at 12:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-03 12:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-03 10:30:47',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(64895,171,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/iycy59/podbean_versionb96h3.mp3','2023-10-03 18:39:54',235168369,'2023-12-03 10:06:54',NULL,'I Like That\" . . I Like the Change from Summer To Autumn . Then Of Course the Gradual Change to the Barrenscape Autumn !!! Do you feel it? I Don1t Enjoy the Summer When It1s Hot',NULL,NULL),(64904,125,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/03/Power Up! with Electrified Voltage - October 3, 2023 at 14:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-03 14:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-03 09:49:22',NULL,'The show starts off with a song by Quincy Conserve. Then we hear from Nigeria, Zeder Oliver, and then Corsas. Then the show moves on to Canadian music. It starts with The Folklord\'s, then King Cobb\'s and finally Nina Hagen.\n\nThen it\'s Happy End, then Ghost Hill, then Nina Hagen, and finally Happy End with Haikara. We\'ve got a lot of music on the show. It all starts with the song from the Nina-Hagen band\'s first album. We then hear a song from Happy End\'s second album. Then Ghost Hill. Then Nina Hagen again. Finally, we hear the song by the singer of the band from her new album. She\'s called Valencia Kent.',NULL,NULL),(64905,3686,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/03/Volunteer Playlist - October 3, 2023 at 13:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-03 13:00:00',86638720,'2023-12-03 09:07:39',NULL,'This is the music from the new album by the Toronto Thavala Ensemble. The show is going to be at the Al Green Theatre on November 4 th . Check it out at TorontoTavla.org. This is a great way to start off your new music collection. You can also get tickets for the show by visiting the Thavla.com website. Alice is on the show and introduces us to Community Food.\n\nIt\'s a non-profit organization that provides free or low-cost food to poor and working-class families in the city. It also has a Facebook page and a Twitter account. Alice invites you to join her on Sundays at 9pm as she travels around with the Looking Glass. If you\'d like to advertise on the station, we can help you.',NULL,NULL),(64915,1453,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/03/Silver Screen Dream Machine - October 3, 2023 at 15:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-03 15:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-03 08:51:43',NULL,'This week on the Silver Screen Dream machine, we hear music from three different Canadian films. The first is a horror movie called Back Country, the second is a comedy called I Like Movies and the third is an animated comedy called Garfield and Friends. The music starts off with the theme song for the first season of the animated show, friends are there. The second song is the theme for the second season of Mr. Bean. The third song is Howard Goodall\'s. Three years have passed since Eddie Van Halen died.',NULL,NULL),(64916,3033,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/03/A Multilingual Affair - October 3, 2023 at 16:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-03 16:00:00',86638720,'2023-12-03 08:32:35',NULL,'This is a very short program, and it is all about the singer\'s mission to \"liberate\" the listeners from the \"filth\" of society. The program consists of a series of monologues and a short section of music. The first is about the theme of \"freed\" people, and the second is about \"Israeli vibes\" and the listener\'s need to \"feel that wonderful vibe.\" The program ends with a shout-out to the \"lady who wears many hats\" .',NULL,NULL),(64926,91,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/03/Tuesday at 5 - October 3, 2023 at 17:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-03 17:00:00',86638720,'2023-12-03 08:07:01',NULL,'On Tuesday, October 3rd at 5pm, Danika Charles hosts another edition of her program on CFRU-FM 93.3. She begins with a song called \"On the Mini Haha\" about Kirsten Neuhauffer, a sailor who won a difficult race around the world with her boat. Then she plays some new music from the Northern Pike and Stephen Fairling. She ends the program with a play called \"The Things You Saw In Me by the Pikes\" about the narrator of the book. The October party by George Cooper was a grand affair. Professor Wind led the dancing, the band played, and everyone stayed. Then they had David Archibald, Myra McBrien, Douglas Paisley, Say what you like and Claire Davis.',NULL,NULL),(64927,1455,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/03/Down the Rabbit Hole - October 3, 2023 at 18:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-03 18:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-03 07:08:26',NULL,'This program begins with the opening of the program by introducing the listeners to a new artist, Angel Olsen. The artist describes herself as a singer, songwriter, and musician who follows her own music. She has released several albums, including the critically-acclaimed All Mirrors. The show concludes with the announcement that the band will be playing some music by Ben Stager at an upcoming show at the Yeti in Kitchener. The band also announces that they have just released a new album by Kevin Bright with the Upper York County Mandolin Orchestra.',NULL,NULL),(64937,94,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/03/Let’s Get Lost - October 3, 2023 at 20:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-03 20:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-03 06:45:58',NULL,'This week on the Let\'s Get Lost program, Scott opens the program with a description of the music he\'s going to play. He introduces us to some of the artists he\'ll be playing with: Eric Chenot , Tanya Gill , Brody West , Lena Alomeno , Rob Clutton , and Nico Dan .\n\nScott then describes the tracks they\'ll play. First up is a track called Summer And Time from Eric\'s new album, Skull Splitter, which came out in 2015. Next up is another track from Tanya\'s Disappearing Curiosies album, called Marsh Music , which is also from her new album. The band is Lena\'s band, Four, which played at the recent Guelph Jazz Festival. Scott also describes a track from the band\'s latest album, Pipe Dream, which Brody West is also a part of.',NULL,NULL),(64938,1591,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/03/New or Never - October 3, 2023 at 19:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-03 19:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-03 06:28:09',NULL,'Adrian Hoad Reddick, a Canadian musician, introduces us to a dozen new songs. The first song is from Elizabeth, a singer from Northern Quebec.\n\nShe\'s got a cover of a song called Wild Hole, which sounds like a lot of gothic horror movies. The second song is by Corinne Bailey Ray, an up-and-coming Canadian musician with a punky vibe. The third track is by Abby Johnson, a North Carolina native who loves Taylor Swift. The fourth track is from Fertrade, an indie rock band from Canada. The fifth track is a rock song by Curtis Noahsad, a New York City based jazz drummer. The sixth track is one by Cassie, a folk singer from Quebec. The seventh track is an English post punk band called ACR.',NULL,NULL),(64948,94,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/03/Let’s Get Lost - October 3, 2023 at 21:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-03 21:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-03 06:08:59',NULL,'The Humanoid crew takes us back to the past to talk about Ken Oldcroft\'s music, which lives on and continues to make him popular.\n\nThe Ken Old-Cortana Ensemble brings us a track from Ken\'s Convergence album, Section Section 4. The Convergence album also brought us some tracks from Rob Clutton\'s trio, Rob, Nick, and Carening, as well as some tracks by Anna Weber, Longa Naahand, and others. The program is called Scott\'s Name, and it\'s a celebration of the 10th anniversary of the comedy festival in Guelph. The Humanoids begin the program with a track called Strangers Dance from Thomas Greer, a friend of theirs. They then begin with some other tracks from other albums, including a self-released track from Amonto Bin, an original motion picture, a self released track from Bonsai, an album from Chaos, and an album called Babe Terror from the TechnoJoy.',NULL,NULL),(64949,95,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/03/Humanoid Radio - October 3, 2023 at 22:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-03 22:00:00',86638720,'2023-12-03 05:06:44',NULL,'This week on Humanoid Radio, we hear a bunch of new music from experimental artists. We begin with Josh Cole\'s Kind Mind album, followed by Apollo Sons\' Departures album, Horses, Tony Price\'s Hit Piece album, I.G Oma\'s Late album, Worm Worms, Old Bones\' The Dirty Gorilla Revenge Volume 2 album, and Mocha Only\'s In and of Itself album. We hear about how the technology to communicate with outer space has been developed by radio, and how they\'ve tried to contact them by radio. We also hear about a new program called Sounded Out Together, which is about how parents can help their kids learn to speak alien languages.',NULL,NULL),(64959,96,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/03/Cyber Lich’s Gothic Castle - October 3, 2023 at 23:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-03 23:00:00',86638720,'2023-12-03 04:44:00',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(64960,109,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/04/Radia - October 4, 2023 at 00:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-04 00:00:00',86638720,'2023-12-03 04:38:15',NULL,'This is a show for \"RADIOVA\", a group of radio stations that bring \"new and forgotten ways\" of making music to their listeners. The mission is to find people on the internet who are interested in making music. The group gives artists the challenge of making a music that works across Europe and beyond every week.\n\nEach week they give artists a challenge to make a music track that works in the whole of the European continent and beyond. Do you know how to make music? Well, dreadric uses a little man to ask them questions. He has a lot of food for you, I\'m happy with you, do you love song, I love song? Do you love music? I love music. I love songs. I am Otis and you\'re listening to \"CFRU 93.3\" at the \"I\'m Otis\" and \"you are listening to\" .',NULL,NULL),(64980,217,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/h6c5ee/CIUTOct3.mp3','2023-10-04 09:36:54',143961989,'2023-12-03 04:07:06',NULL,'The narrator tells us that the show will feature a number of acts, including a number from Cub, who will perform in honor of drummer Valeria Felli, who died this past week, and the Wasaga\'s, a Montreal punk band that recently lost its drummer. The narrator also tells us about the release of a new album by the American Devices, and about the death of drummer Carl Van Helm, who was a member of the band. The show closes with the performance of the Wasags, whose drummer also died this week.',NULL,NULL),(64985,180,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/yyfn6z/HOWL_OCT_03_20238kxz7.mp3','2023-10-04 11:50:59',56689813,'2023-12-03 03:47:46',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(64992,174,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/xq8h6r/October_4_2023_Global_Rhythms8y3ll.mp3','2023-10-04 14:03:01',431961989,'2023-12-03 03:06:29',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(65001,280,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/uaeycn/ABROAD_82_TFA_SouthKorea7ucz3.mp3','2023-10-04 12:50:00',113470824,'2023-12-03 02:50:00',NULL,'This week on the University of Toronto\'s student