 show hosted by the Canadian musician, singer, and curator, The Stillsman. The show begins with a heavy note, as the performer announces that he has been recently diagnosed with a rare, optimistically malignant form of breast cancer. He has had to withdraw from his studies for the semester and will be going to Toronto to get treatment. The doctors are hopeful that he will recover, but uncertainty is something he lives with in his world. He describes the outpouring of support he has received from his listeners and friends, and he hopes to continue his show for the eight year anniversary. He says that he is also concerned that his new programming will be inconsistent over the next few months, as he will be undergoing radiation treatments for the disease. He hopes that his show will continue to be well received, as it has done for him. He adds that the show is also a somber one, as there is a lot of music that he just loves',NULL,'The Stillsman’s radio show tells us why he has been diagnosed with breast cancer '),(65024,100,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/04/We Know Some Stuff + CFRU playlist - October 4, 2023 at 12:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-04 12:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-03 02:13:20',NULL,'Before we get to the interview, the two students talk about their educations. Caroline is from Quebec and graduated from McGill University with a master\'s in earth system science. After completing her masters, she decided that she wanted to leave science behind and become a ski bum. As a result, she moved to Colorado and became a snow scientist. She then went back to school to study mountain hydrology.\n\nShe\'s now a PhD student at the University in Saskatchewan. We learn that she has traveled a lot of the provinces in Canada, and that she\'s been accepted into all the universities in the country. We\'re also interested to hear that she doesn\'t have the toll of going to Saskatoon for meetings. It\'s not like she\'ll have to go back and forth to Saskatoon every time she wants to meet someone. But she does have to commute during her courses, and she has to go once or twice every year.',NULL,NULL),(65025,1437,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/04/Democracy Now - October 4, 2023 at 11:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-04 11:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-03 01:51:44',NULL,'The House has voted to remove the speaker of the House, Republican California Congressman, House Majority Leader, and one-time ally of President Donald Trump, Republican House Majority Whip, Republican Congressman, and former Trump campaign manager, Republican Representative, Congressman from California, and current leader of the Republican House, House of Representatives, Republican Kevin McCarthy. The vote comes just days after he worked with Democrats on a budget deal to avert the government shutdown. In response to the vote, McCarthy says he\'s not regretful for standing up for what\'s right. He says he doesn\'t regret negotiating with the other side',NULL,NULL),(65028,155,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/2pu5yx/DrMouth_CIUTshow_oct3_2023_fullshow.mp3','2023-10-04 18:14:25',287930048,'2023-12-03 01:14:06',NULL,'The host launches into a tirade against the evils of dropping out of school. He advises students to get an education and pursue a career, rather than being discouraged by the fact that they don\'t have a good job. He says the only way to have a successful life is to get a good college degree and then pursue a profession. He suggests that students \"take it with however much salt you wish, the brown acid, that is circulating round us is not too good.\" . .',NULL,NULL),(65037,13298,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/04/CFRU Selector - October 4, 2023 at 14:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-04 14:00:00',86507648,'2023-10-04 20:08:31',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(65047,102,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/04/End Credits - October 4, 2023 at 15:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-04 15:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-03 00:30:09',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(65048,1464,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/04/Gryphon And Special Olympics Sports Show - October 4, 2023 at 16:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-04 16:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-03 00:15:01',NULL,'The Griffins are back on the air, and the show\'s host, Leonard Squosins, is back on stage with his boss, Taylor Remen. They\'re talking about the Griffins\' basketball team, and they\'ve just had another interview with the team\'s head coach, Megan Reed.\n\nThey have a song for the show, and it\'s called \"Firing Lips\" from the CFRU library, and \"Flamin Grooves\" from C4u\'s vinyl collection. The first song is a garage punk band called \"Garage Proto Punk\" and the second is a rock song called \"Kicks.\" The first one is a song about a single night in Australia, while the second one is about peat towns and covers. Leonard and Taylor start off by playing a song called flammin lips, which is from the first album of the CFRu library. The second song is called \"Fireworks\" from a later album called \"One Night Stand\" . The third song is \"Fireballs\" from another album called One Night Live, which was recorded live off the ground in Australia.\n\nThe song is about a long tour of Australia, Japan, and Europe. We\'ll hear the song in the first segment, and then we\'re going to hear the interview with Coach Megan. The coach will give us an update on the Griffin\'s women\'s team, so we\'ll listen to the song she\'s talking about',NULL,NULL),(65058,13298,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/04/CFRU Selector - October 4, 2023 at 17:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-04 17:00:00',86507648,'2023-10-05 00:07:55',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(65068,105,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/04/B Siide Radio - October 4, 2023 at 19:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-04 19:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-02 23:04:42',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(65069,106,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/04/Trail Mix - October 4, 2023 at 20:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-04 20:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-02 22:48:47',NULL,'This is a message from Connex Helpline and from the Guelph Community Radio station. The message is about listening to a show on CFRU and how to find out more information about mental health. You can also call the mental health helpline toll free at 1-866-531-2626',NULL,NULL),(65079,289,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/fxzd76/The_Next_Stop_119a1kw2.mp3','2023-10-05 05:22:51',268872654,'2023-12-02 22:28:30',NULL,'This is the 119th episode of the Next Stop. It\'s hosted by Sage Ranaldo and it\'s all about independent programming that can\'t be found anywhere else. It starts off with a bang with the music from Forest Swords\'s first film, \"The Machine Air.\" The next two hours will be spent listening to ambient tracks. You can listen to the past episodes of the show over at \"The Next Stop\" on Soundcloud.',NULL,NULL),(65080,78,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/05/Morning Soul Shake-Up! - October 5, 2023 at 08:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-05 08:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-02 22:13:18',NULL,'This week on Morning Soul Shake Up, host Maheen discusses the 10th anniversary of the Comedy Festival and the upcoming Giggle Fest. He also discusses Silence Guelph, a new music venue and art gallery in downtown Guelph, which is available for rent. If you\'re in the market for a creative space, Silence is the place for you. The studio is open Monday-Friday from 9am- 5pm, and it\'s conveniently located just outside of downtown Guelph.',NULL,NULL),(65081,97,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/05/Wild Combination - October 5, 2023 at 01:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-05 01:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-02 21:08:58',NULL,'This episode of the Morning Show features Byron, host of CFRU\'s To Know The Land, and his son. Byron tells his son that he is a \"deity without a compass\" and that he wants to know what\'s on his mind. He explains that he doesn\'t know how to explain himself to his son, who is confused by the world.',NULL,NULL),(65082,97,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/05/Wild Combination - October 5, 2023 at 00:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-05 00:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-02 20:49:08',NULL,'The phone lines are busy with calls from listeners, including Jerry, who wants to know what happened in the last election. The caller says he wants Trump to win the election, but that he\'s against him because he doesn\'t want to consume. The man wants to hear the guy\'s thoughts on the future, and the man wants his own.',NULL,NULL),(65083,107,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/04/Tone Zone - October 4, 2023 at 21:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-04 21:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-02 20:31:38',NULL,'This is the second part of the Tone Zone, and it starts off with a new song from the new Slowdive album, Everything Is Alive. The first song is a cover of the title track from the first album, called Long Weekends, Don\'tReach Out. The second song is called A Life from the second album. The third song is the cover of Can\'T Hardly Wait from the third album, Pleased To Meet Me. The fourth song is from a band called Grade School. The fifth song is an acoustic guitar, vocal, and cello version from Dear Diana. The sixth song is Pete\'s first full length solo album, Come Back To Me.',NULL,NULL),(65084,110,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/05/Here Today - October 5, 2023 at 07:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-05 07:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-02 20:14:20',NULL,'This week on the host\'s show, we find out that Will Butler has been in the band Arcade Fire for the last ten years. He is now releasing a solo album with Sister-Squares. The band is touring as well, so it\'s not clear what they\'re doing, but it sounds like they\'ll be doing a lot of shows.\n\nAlso, we learn that Cassie Noble has released her first two EPs, and she was in a band called The Lindsay Do Goodleys. She also has an album called Nowhere To Go But Everywhere, which was nominated for an album award. And then there\'s Neil Redke, who has released his second album, called Alveen in Alchemy. He also has a new song called Venus Child, which is from an EP called The God\'s Design, which he\'s played on.\n\nThen there are some other artists who are also on the show, including Venus Child\'s bandmate Alzombe, and their bandmate Deborah Fajalkova, who\'s also in the group Spore. Finally, we hear from Retro Graph, who have a new single called Read Out. They have a brand new album coming out next year, and they\'ve already played two of the songs on it.',NULL,NULL),(65095,111,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/05/Tales from the Bridge - October 5, 2023 at 09:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-05 09:00:00',86638720,'2023-12-02 19:48:01',NULL,'We\'re back with another episode of the Science Fiction and Fantasy Show, and this time we\'re talking to a real-life writer named Alexandra Harrow, who\'s a self-described \"full-time writer\" living in Virginia. Her latest book, \"The Starling House,\" is coming out in October. We\'ll get to that in a minute, but first, we need to talk to Alexandra about how she uses footnotes in her stories.\n\nShe says that, as a writer, she uses them because they add to the story. She also says that she\'s inspired by all the things she read as a kid, including Alice in Wonderland. We learn that she was on her grandma\'s Kentucky farm when she wrote her book.',NULL,NULL),(65096,112,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/05/FoodFarm Talk - October 5, 2023 at 10:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-05 10:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-02 19:11:44',NULL,'The latest episode of The host\'s Podcast focuses on the topic of food inflation. It\'s been growing at an average annual rate of about 10% over the last few years. This is bad news for everyone, especially for those families who rely on grocery stores for their food.\n\nThis week\'s guest on the program is a former grocery industry executive named Sheriff Clinton. He tells the listeners that he studied food distribution at the university and has been in the grocery business for over 30 years. He was the president of the Canadian Federation of Grocers for 25 years and he\'s now a board member. He says that he enjoys going into the stores and giving people a real-time look at the state of the grocery industry.\n\nHe is also a big fan of John Scott, who he says is the \"guru of grocery retail\" . He explains that the grocery retail industry is devoted to just one thing: delighting the consumer, and that\'s why everyone in the industry has to do it. And that is to keep up with the latest and greatest consumer trends. For example, a store has to look its best the next day, even if it\'s just changing the way it sells certain products.',NULL,NULL),(65103,189,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/wr7nzj/VFTC_Stu9r0fe.mp3','2023-10-05 16:08:11',283547688,'2023-12-02 18:49:47',NULL,'The first guest at the show is a guy named Stuart who\'s been making music mixes for friends and family for years. He\'s a big fan of all the music on the bill. We learn that he\'s also a fan of the guy who played meatloaf in \"Rocky Horror Picture Show\" on Broadway and \"bat out of hell\" on his long-running partnership with \"Jim Steinman\" . The first song on the list is \"Tonto\'s\" from the first \"Max Webster\" album. The second song is \"JJ James\" from \"Thundermug Strikes\" , the third is \"Mashma\" from a \"Festival Express Tour\" in 1970. The fourth is \"Cowsill\'s with hair\" by the Partridge family. The fifth is \"Arthur Brown\" by \"Ed Mervis\".\n\nThe sixth is \"Rocky Erickson\" from his early days as a member of the \"13th floor Elevators\" who suffers from paranoid schizophrenia. The seventh is \"Slaughter from bad religion\" by an albican named \"Rambo Erickson\" who got electroshock therapy when he was a teenager. The last song is called \"Olbican\" by a band called \"Scorpio\" who used to play in the basement of the old building.',NULL,NULL),(65107,90,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/05/Bridging The Social Distance - October 5, 2023 at 12:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-05 12:00:00',86638720,'2023-12-02 18:29:08',NULL,'In this rebroadcast of an earlier episode, Jenny Mitchell speaks with Ted Prezant at the Riverside Glen Retirement Community. The interview is originally recorded in March of 2022. In this interview, we learn that Ted was born in the 1930s and grew up in Chatham, on the edge of London and Windsor, during the Great Depression. He had friends who lived in the area and he had many of them.',NULL,NULL),(65108,1437,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/05/Democracy Now - October 5, 2023 at 11:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-05 11:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-02 17:08:47',NULL,'Two Republican leaders emerge as leading contenders for the speaker of the House. One is Jim Jordan, the chair of the powerful House Judiciary Committee. The other is Steve Scalise, the speaker\'s nominee from Louisiana. The two men have both been accused of sexual abuse by current or former students.',NULL,NULL),(65116,182,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/4phzru/Oct_4_20237c0pp.mp3','2023-10-05 19:49:48',147924113,'2023-12-02 16:47:23',NULL,'The narrator of this program thanks listeners for their financial support and announces that the show this week will be re-titled \"No Beat FM\" and will focus on more abstract, experimental sounds and more punk rock. He also introduces himself as Minesh and says he will be hosting the show. He says he\'ll be listening to a live version from the band She\'s Been Hit. He\'ll also be watching the band upstairs. He describes the band as \"a disturbance\" and says this is one of the most beautiful absova he\'s ever seen.',NULL,NULL),(65119,205,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/9g2ax4/October_15th_2023_Music_at_High_Noonb8rcj.mp3','2023-10-05 18:26:12',227246841,'2023-12-02 16:27:25',NULL,'This week\'s program opens with music from \"Music At High Noon\" hosted by Mike Tadros and featuring the Canadian band \"Twin Peaks\" from British Columbia. The first set is comprised of AC/DC\'s \"Problem Child\" followed by Velvet Trip with \"Take Control of your Mind\" and the Dolly Rocker\'s movement with \"What\'s that Sound\".\n\nThe last set is composed of ACDC\'s song Problem Child followed by Psychedelic Porn\'s track Native Tongue, the Davidians\' \"Don\'t get hung up\" and Frank Zappa\'s Willy the Pimp with \"You Shook Me\". If you\'re interested in listening to this program, you can find it on the program page of the Podbean Show on the website of CIUT. FM. Just visit the show page and then click on \"Music at High Noon.\" If you have any questions about the program or about the playlist, you just have to send an email to \"High Noon\" at musicathighnoon@gmail.com.',NULL,NULL),(65120,113,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/05/Android’s Dungeon - October 5, 2023 at 13:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-05 13:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-02 16:12:48',NULL,'The host starts off by saying that this is like the old days, where it was easy to get everything you needed in one place. He\'s doing his solo show in a pub instead of going to a concert. He wants to save the listeners from having to listen to his thoughts all the time. He decides to load the show up with music, since it\'s a solo show. He doesn\'t want the listeners to feel like they\'re listening to him the whole time, so they\'ll hear the entire thing.\n\nHe thinks that the death of music has kind of heralded a new age of people who don\'t care about their own music. He tells them to buy their own media, including music and movies. He also tells them that if they want to buy a copy, they should buy a physical copy. He says that people buy physical copies of movies, music, and books because they\'ve been out of print for a long time and they can\'t be found anymore.\n\nIf you\'re going to buy something, he says, you should buy it. If the artist isn\'t making any money from it, he or she\'s not getting any money at all. So who wants to buy the up-dated stuff?',NULL,NULL),(65121,13307,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/05/Eclectic Selections - October 5, 2023 at 14:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-05 14:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-02 15:52:58',NULL,'This week on the Eclectic Experience, host CFRU 99.3 FM talks with musician Karim Mosna about his recent gig at the University at Guelph.\n\nHe\'s part of the Griffin Reeds, a group of students who study the Middle East and North Africa. This year, they\'ve brought in Giller Prize-winning author, CBC-Canada Reeds finalist, and journalist, Omar El Aqad to speak about his novel \"What Strange Paradise.\" Mosna says that the book has a unique format. Before focusing on Amir, a Syrian boy, and his family, they are boarding a ship with other refugees, and then the \"after part Amir\" on an island. This is where the narrator comes in. He has a chance to talk to El Aqdad about his own experiences as a journalist and his personal experiences as an Egyptian and a Qatari.\n\nThe narrator says that he\'s really getting the perspective between the Syrian boy arriving and the young woman Vana on the island. He asks why he chose to write this novel in this unique way. The novel was written in a straight narrative, but the narrator realized that he had a story that was going to happen in the Old Testament, but in the New Testament it had to happen with an \"earthly exodus\" and a \"miraculous rebirth\" . So he decided to write in this way. He says that this format allowed him to tell the story upfront without acting on it.',NULL,NULL),(65131,115,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/05/RadiOPIRG - October 5, 2023 at 15:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-05 15:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-02 15:29:10',NULL,'Another bus trip is planned to bring people from five First Nations nations - Wapakaka , Nxitanga , Big Trout lake , Muscat Dam , and Grassy-Narrows .\n\nThe students and community people are going to call on chief Chris Munius of Nesaka . Chief Munius is from a small community called Atch and he\'s here to talk about the government of Duckport. He says that the government continues to divide and conquer First Nations and that they continue to try to shut them up. They invite him to come and talk to them, but he doesn\'t show up. He is a liar and they can\'t access him.\n\nHe lied the day before he came to Atch. He returns calls but never even comes. The youth from Atch are chanting, \"Duckport, weres Duckport\" . They call for him to resign. The young people from Neska are also there. They are there to protest against the corrupt government of Doug Ford. They say that there is no need for any government to destroy their lands, rivers, and lands without their permission. They also say that they will continue to fight for their rights.',NULL,NULL),(65132,116,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/05/T.K.O. - October 5, 2023 at 16:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-05 16:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-02 15:08:10',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(65133,118,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/05/Open Sources Guelph - October 5, 2023 at 17:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-05 17:00:00',86638720,'2023-10-30 19:18:30',NULL,'On this week\'s Open Guelph, Scott Hertz and Adam A Donaldson discuss the politics of the week. The show opens with a brief history of the show. The program discusses the election of Greg Fergus as the new speaker of the House and the re-release of the Deshane report, a government document that attempted to track down and punish war criminals. The government has also been criticized for allowing the university to continue to give money to former Waffen soldiers. The Canadian government has been accused of killing a Sikh nationalist named Singh Naijar in Canada, but this has not stopped the Indian government from sending more than 40 Canadian diplomats to India.',NULL,'Open Guelph, Scott Hertz and Adam A Donaldson discuss politics of the week'),(65134,120,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/05/The Crooked Beat - October 5, 2023 at 20:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-05 20:00:00',86638720,'2023-12-02 14:44:39',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(65135,120,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/05/The Crooked Beat - October 5, 2023 at 19:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-05 19:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-02 14:28:43',NULL,'Welcome to the Crooked Beat. We\'re back with Dread, who\'s here to bring you all the latest music. There\'s a lot of new music coming in, too, including some old favorites.\n\nWe start off with a new song from Be Humble, a dub of Riddim Wise. Then the next song is a new one from Take It Easy, a Vienna-based band. Then there\'s another new song by The Future Man, this one from Austria. And then the third song is another new one by Uwe Bant, from Germany. Then it\'s time for Roots Radix to come in and play some of his old hits. Then we hear more new music from Twon Tiyamaunda, AmaGold, and more from the Future Man. Then again, we also hear some new cuts from Scratch Perry, Akaya, and Uwe. And finally, we hear a new track from Dennis Walks. It\'s from Neb.',NULL,NULL),(65136,119,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/05/Turtle Island Underground - October 5, 2023 at 18:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-05 18:00:00',86638720,'2023-12-02 14:09:18',NULL,'Mac introduces the music from his show on CFRU, which is dedicated to listening to new music from the library. He and his listeners will hear tracks from Beika Moingan\'s latest album, Bleached Waves; Heart Bites, the latest album from Kristi Lane Sinclair; and Super Blood Moon, a new album from Chris. The music from these albums will be paired with a pair of tracks from the 1987 debut album by Canadian musician Mark Robertson. The final track will be from Robbie Mitsuap\'s debut album, which will be released in the United States in September.',NULL,NULL),(65146,1551,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/nur9g9/OCTOBER5TH.mp3','2023-10-06 03:14:47',431961989,'2023-12-02 13:48:29',NULL,'The host returns to the Ciut.fm studios to continue his weekly Thursday night setlists. He tells us that he\'s been busting the show out from late summer until early fall. Now that the weather\'s finally nicer, he\'ll be back at the studio.\n\nThis time, he and his crew will be playing music from an upcoming album from Crates and Keys. The duo will also be chatting about their new album. On top of that, they\'re going to be getting the listeners up to speed on what\'s going on in the underground music scene. They\'ll also be playing some music from the upcoming Thursday night sets.',NULL,NULL),(65147,121,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/05/Sundowner - October 5, 2023 at 21:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-05 21:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-02 13:25:09',NULL,'Here\'s a bunch of fun things you can do at the university\'s community radio station, CFRU. They\'re looking to hire people to promote events and festivals all over the place. They also need volunteers to record public service announcements, which is a great way to get involved in the community. Sounds like a great gig for you. The festival is celebrating its 10th anniversary this year, and the university is throwing a big bash. The university is putting on a comedy show with some of the festival\'s alumni. This one is called Clown Prov and it\'s free and open to anyone.',NULL,NULL),(65148,122,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/05/Forever Deaf - October 5, 2023 at 22:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-05 22:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-02 13:07:06',NULL,'The \"Forever Deaf\" music show on 93.3 CFRU in Guelph, Ontario, Canada, begins with an introduction from the host, Todd. He tells the audience that Dean will join the show at 11:15 but that he\'s stuck with him until then.\n\nHe announces that he just heard some new music from Aghuriam, from Regina, SK. He also announces that the band is reformed and that it\'s from Saskatchewan. He then introduces the band from Regina as \"unearthly Will.\" He also mentions that they\'ve just heard from Phantom Parallax, Cryptopsy, Cryptypse, Cannibal Corpse, and Chaos Horrific, among others. Next up is Ken Mode, Juno Award-winning band from Canada. They just released their latest album, \"Besieged and Violent Beyond All Reason,\" and they\'re also the band featured on the cover of the new album. They also have some other bands on the bill, including Better Lovers, Fugitive, and Razor. The show ends with the band Baroness, from Victoria, British Columbia.',NULL,NULL),(65158,122,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/06/Forever Deaf - October 6, 2023 at 00:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-06 00:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-02 12:47:41',NULL,'The program begins with the music of a band called The Narcotic Wastelands. The song is about partners and Sex, Lies, and DNA is a sign that it\'s about partners. The rest of the band plays tracks from new albums from Ringworm, Necrofony, Something Ominous, and Kika Mora. The program ends with the voice of Dean Yunt from the painting of unknowns. The band has finished listening to all of the tracks on the new album Seeing Through Fire, and the other tracks on Seeing through Fire are called Thought Crimes, Breakdown, Oathbreaker, Ring Lung, Mountain Throne, and Bound for Destruction',NULL,NULL),(65159,122,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/05/Forever Deaf - October 5, 2023 at 23:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-05 23:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-02 12:27:59',NULL,'The show opens with a description of a project called \"Life in Covid Study,\" which seeks to understand the experiences of young and old people during the Covid-19 pandemic. The project is supported by the Office for Research and Ethics at the University at Ottawa and the Office of Institutional Review at the Vermont School of Law. The program includes music from the latest album by Danco Jones, a song called \"Good Time,\" and a concert by Northern, Surgical Sacrifice, and Guelph Crusher at Monks, a club in Guelph, on October 13.',NULL,NULL),(65169,122,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/06/Forever Deaf - October 6, 2023 at 01:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-06 01:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-02 12:06:59',NULL,'This program is a little bit different than the others be