live sound. The event is free and open to all.',NULL,NULL),(65228,195,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/dc6gue/Dementia13RadioShow_23_10_03.mp3','2023-10-06 19:57:43',173991544,'2023-12-02 08:48:40',NULL,'The narrator starts this program by talking about how he\'s digging into his collection of music to find some of the stuff he hasn\'t heard before.\n\nHe starts with a song called \"Upon the Earth\" from a band called Manmade from Montreal in 1970. It turns into a band that\'s called Keep On Moving from another band called Jerry Mercer. Then Sarah Brum from Spain. Then Arthur Gee from Canada. Then another song called Plain Talk from a group called Arthur Gee. And then another song from Dr. Strange from Dublin. And finally, a song from the wimple with marmalade hair from the British psych band Spirits & Worms. Sounds like the group tanked after the band was pulled from an A&M store because they had a goat on the cover of their record.\n\nThe narrator hates when people treat animals badly. Then there\'s a song by a Canadian band called Cat from 1970. It\'s \"The Whole World Watching\" from \"A New Kind Of Cat\" from 1970. And then a song about an American singer named Melanie Safka from \"People In the Front Row\" from the same band. And last but not least, there was \"The Darling\" by American Darling from 1970. The narrator says he thinks she\'s one of the best artists of all time.',NULL,NULL),(65229,257,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/vmsjf6/October_5_2023_Psychedelic_Stoner_Rockalmpd.mp3','2023-10-06 18:37:50',287962512,'2023-12-02 08:24:31',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(65230,292,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/8xfv8q/October_6_2023_The_Cool_Side_of_the_Pillowb8v22.mp3','2023-10-06 19:22:59',287962512,'2023-12-02 08:04:42',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(65231,126,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/06/Viejoteca - October 6, 2023 at 14:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-06 14:00:00',86507648,'2023-10-06 20:07:07',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(65232,126,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/1