ral foundation of a politician, as it will help us make more informed political decisions.',NULL,NULL),(65244,1620,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/06/Hellfire Radio - October 6, 2023 at 15:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-06 15:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-02 06:30:13',NULL,'The band announces that they\'re back, and they\'ve got a new song from France. They\'re psyched to have it from a band called Gros Soleil.\n\nThe band\'s not sure what to make of the first song, but the second one is even better. The first song is super good, and the second song is better than the first. The guys are psyched to hear more music from Canada. They also get a new track from Saxon, a.k.a. Sanji. This guy is a heavy metal chef. He\'s also a big fan of \"God rhythm Doom 23\" , which the band played on the previous show. He also plays a lot of metal albums, so he\'s very familiar with this band. They play a new metal track called \"Tris Tris Kelly\" . This is Canadian melodic metal. They have some new stuff coming up, too.',NULL,NULL),(65254,128,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/06/Walkuman Style - October 6, 2023 at 18:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-06 18:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-02 06:12:31',NULL,'Connex Ontario\'s mental health helpline is at 1-866-531-2626 to speak with a specialist. It\'s also available via the mentalhealthline.ca to chat with a mental health specialist or to send an anonymous message. Mac D is a local musician who works at the University of Guelph\'s community radio station.\n\nHe\'s been hanging around the university for a long time because he\'s had a blast. He started out working the equipment and producing shows, and then moved on to doing his own show. He still loves what he does. If you\'d like to learn more about what\'s going on at the university, Mac D invites you to visit the university\'s second floor and check out what the university has to offer.\n\nHe also tells you about the War-Amms, a charity that provides artificial limbs to people who have lost their limbs due to war. He tells you that the war-',NULL,NULL),(65255,135,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/06/Folk Roots Radio - October 6, 2023 at 17:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-06 17:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-02 05:09:24',NULL,'This week on the show, we hear from Paul Smith, Watt Macums, Amelia Baker, John McCuskers, Alison Russell, Peter Wan, and Kyle Weymouth. All of these artists have new music releases, and they want to thank the listeners for their support.\n\nSo they\'re starting this week by playing a song called \"Untanked Smith\" by Paul Smith. We also hear a song by Amelia Baker called \"Cinderwell\" and a song from John McCustker called \"Sprig of Time\" which features Island singer Heidi Talbot on the vocals. Then we hear \"All Woman Supported Solo\" by Annie and \"Co-It\" by Kyle Weymouth, which is a song about love and belonging. Next up is Peter Wan\'s song \"Birds Go Die out of Sight Go Home\" from his upcoming album.',NULL,NULL),(65265,129,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/06/Digital Statik - October 6, 2023 at 19:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-06 19:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-02 04:44:30',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(65266,3686,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/06/Volunteer Playlist - October 6, 2023 at 20:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-06 20:00:00',86638720,'2023-12-02 04:26:40',NULL,'In this program, we learn about the work of Community Food, a non-profit that takes high- quality produce and transforms it into delicious take-home meals for the wealthy. The meals are offered for free or for donation, and they help to divert raw ingredients and excess food from fields and farms and onto dinner table of families throughout the community. We also learn about Ritesh Das\'s new album, which is now available on all the major streaming services. He will perform at the Al Green Theatre on November 4. Also, there is a new edition of the Selector on the way, and if you\'d like to hear it, you can find it on the Soundcloud page.',NULL,NULL),(