Achilles always has a lead.',NULL,NULL),(65465,196,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/32n4zv/October_8_2023_Across_the_Universe6vpuz.mp3','2023-10-09 00:03:51',431961989,'2023-10-31 03:42:26',NULL,'The program begins with a song by Baba Maul, titled \"Across the Universe\". The song is dedicated to Elizabeth Montgomery, the matriarch of the Montgomery family. She died on Friday evening at the age of 93. Elizabeth had lived alone for the last 50 years, but she managed to get by by on her own for 40 years. She had seven distinct bouts of breast cancer, but none of them was caught in time, and the eighth was caught this past Friday evening. Elizabeth was very stubborn, and her entire family is going to miss and miss her dearly',NULL,'Baba Maul\'s \"Across the Universe\" song is dedicated to Elizabeth Montgomery, the matriarch of the family'),(65466,200,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/ztsxmm/Karibuni_Oct_8-239vsik.mp3','2023-10-09 00:24:42',287962512,'2023-12-01 14:30:05',NULL,'The first act of the show is called \"Ubuntu,\" and it\'s the first time we\'ve heard about it. It\'s an all-star line-up of artists, including Berita, an artist from the Eswatini kingdom of Swaziland, and a band from Zimbabwe.',NULL,NULL),(65467,296,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/mwc756/9_30_23_showap4iu.mp3','2023-10-08 21:11:52',80801820,'2023-12-01 14:07:32',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(65468,101,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/08/Seems Like Old Times - October 8, 2023 at 15:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-08 15:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-01 13:57:03',NULL,'The whole gang is ready to take Cathy home. Just when we think it\'s safe to leave her in the back of the car, she suddenly notices the gas gauge on the dashboard. It\'s clearly not a gas gauge, but rather a liquid gas. This is the kind of thing that\'s called \"gas\" but is really \"stove gas\" . So you see, it doesn\'t really matter what the gas is called, it\'ll always be gas. Anyway, she\'s so glad to see her dad back in the car that she can\'t wait to get home.\n\nSo we find out what\'s wrong with the car. We find out that the car\'s ignition has gone off, and that the horn won t work. We also learn that the speedometer is broken, and the kid\'s not paying any attention to her dad. She\'s just laughing at him. He\'s going to get a speeding ticket. This whole time, he\'s been talking about how fast he was going when he was speeding. The kid has no idea what he is talking about. So she asks her dad if he was joking about her being pregnant.\n\nHe says that he was happy when her baby was born, but that he\'d been speeding so fast that he almost ran into someone else\'s car and knocked them down. He also says that when he blew his horn three times, the kid had no idea he was blowing',NULL,NULL),(65469,101,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/08/Seems Like Old Times - October 8, 2023 at 14:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-08 14:00:00',86638720,'2023-12-01 13:32:10',NULL,'The program opens with a song from the musical The Ritz Rollin\' Rock, written by the great Cole Porter. The song is from a 1930 recording by Ted Lewis and the orchestra. The program also discusses the upcoming Lions Club Healthy Aging Show, which will take place on Tuesday.\n\nThe show is free and open to the public. The Legion branch 275 hosts a Mixed Cribbage Tournament on Saturday. The entry fee is $20 per person and the entry deadline is 1pm sharp. The tournament is open to everyone. The host introduces a new artist, Bria Skorbur, who sings on her CD Bria. She also performs the trumpet on her music. She is a relatively new artist on the music scene, and she is known as \"Bria Skonber.\" The program ends with a program celebrating Thanksgiving. It is a variety show called \"Lady Day herself\" and \"Billie Holiday\" and it is at 2pm on CFRU 95.3.',NULL,NULL),(65470,108,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/08/Wind-Down - October 8, 2023 at 20:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-08 20:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-01 13:13:35',NULL,'Ritesh Das 