ing songs for the other band members. Kim finally left the band and joined the Breeders. She continues to influence women in rock with her music. The album is called Give Up, and it\'s the only album by a band called the Service.',NULL,NULL),(65531,81,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/09/The Sentinel’s Marvellous Kaleidoscope - October 9, 2023 at 15:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-09 15:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-01 06:12:42',NULL,'In this episode, Lucra talks about the people and regions of the Sentinels\' Marvelous Kaleidoscope. It is a syndicated program in Fredericton, New Brunswick, Canada. It covers the traditional territory of the Meckmacks, Wollestakeas, and Milisette peoples in Wabanaki territory. Lucra would like to thank the Black community for their contributions to todays popular and alternative music spheres. The first act of the show begins with a track from the trans-electro-hyperpop musician, Patricia TakSin. They listen to her Bandcamp release. Next up is a track by Jake Hoffman, the composer of the original music for the smash indie game, Shovel Knight. Then they listen to a cover of Donovan\'s \"Guinevere,\" a song that is often overlooked.',NULL,NULL),(65532,84,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/09/Blues Around the Block - October 9, 2023 at 20:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-09 20:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-01 05:08:12',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(65533,84,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/09/Blues Around the Block - October 9, 2023 at 19:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-09 19:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-01 04:49:16',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(65543,86,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/09/The Deep House Project - October 9, 2023 at 22:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-09 22:00:00',86638720,'2023-10-31 05:33:28',NULL,'The show starts off with a song called \"Yeah, yeah, Yeah, Yeah\" by Junior Jack. It\'s a classic disco song about happiness. The guys play some remixes of some of the biggest hits from the 80s and 90s. The show closes with a new track from Calipo.',NULL,'The guys play some of the biggest hits from the 80s and 90s'),(65544,85,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/09/Ripcord Radio - October 9, 2023 at 21:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-09 21:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-01 04:39:53',NULL,'This week\'s program starts off with a song by a band called the Groovy Goolie, who released a song called What\'s little Medusa in 2001. This song is dedicated to a famous Greek goddess named Medusa. Some people think she\'s a monster, while others think she symbolizes female rage. The song is from the band\'s 2001 EP Freaks On Parade, which is available on iTunes. Next up is a song from another band called The Suck.\n\nThis band recorded a song for a split 7-inch they just released with Johnny and the bad lieutenants. It\'s called Cult of the fawns and it\'s an original by the band. Johnny and his band also recorded one song for the split and one for the 7-inch. The next two tracks are from a group called Death from Above 1979, who will be playing a concert in Guelph on October 15th and tickets are available on Eventbrite.\n\nNext, we hear music from a London band called Mall Crimes, who are coming to play a show at the Jimmy jazz on October 28th. And then we hear a classic song from a British group called The Damned, who were fronted by Dave Vathesis. This is one of their earliest releases and is from their 1979 album Machine gun Etiquette. The last track is from a 2000 split album called Greber with old Losers, which also includes Cell Press and Spot Fly.',NULL,NULL),(65554,87,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/09/Back in the USSR - October 9, 2023 at 23:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-09 23:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-01 04:14:47',NULL,'On this episode of the program, Seigfried, a political scientist, talks about the significance of the October Revolution 60 years later. She also discusses the effects of the Cold War on the health of the people of the former Soviet Union. In this episode, she also talks about her recent experience with the \"Covenant Flu\" .',NULL,NULL),(65555,1447,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/10/Rainbow Country - October 10, 2023 at 00:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-10 00:00:00',86638720,'2023-12-01 03:13:51',NULL,'Gino Vanelli, Mark Tara, Emily Saliers, and Chris Harder are all on the show to talk about the current state of affairs in the world of the LGBT community, and to tell us about some of their favorite movies and television shows.',NULL,NULL),(65566,1447,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/10/Rainbow Country - October 10, 2023 at 01:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-10 01:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-01 02:50:32',NULL,'This is the second part of the tour, and it\'s called \"Rainbow Country.\" It\'s all about the music, and the artists. The first part is all about Trans Express and Trans Express Express, the second is about Trans Europe Express, and then the third is about Grace Jones.\n\nWe hear about Boy Games, Burn, Big Boy Games , Demolition Man , Hold On , Superficial , Sometimes we all go crazy , and He\'s my man . The last part is about Mike Nagoda\'s 2022 album, \"Outside the Box.\" The tour is over, and now we can hear about all the other artists on the tour. So, if you\'re a fan of music, check out this tour.',NULL,NULL),(65585,80,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/10/CFRU Playlist - October 10, 2023 at 06:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-10 06:00:00',86507648,'2023-10-10 12:06:29',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(65595,78,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/10/Morning Soul Shake-Up! - October 10, 2023 at 08:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-10 08:00:00',86638720,'2023-12-01 02:28:39',NULL,'On the 10th anniversary of the annual Guelph Comedy Festival, there\'s a lot of fun stuff for the whole family to enjoy. One of the fun things they\'re doing is putting on a clown show with Isaac Kessler and Ken Hall. The festival also has a ton of other events to look forward to, including a live reading of a Native American novel, a public screening of a First Nations film, and more.',NULL,NULL),(65605,280,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/hnfiug/Scotland_-_Tracks_From_Abroad_Ep_8377zcl.mp3','2023-10-10 15:28:15',84106400,'2023-11-30 23:13:05',NULL,'Seth Martosh is a student at the University of Toronto who is studying Middle Eastern music with Megan Traxell. Before the show, Seth tells us that he\'s thankful for living in Canada, where he can express his opinions and values.\n\nHe also says that Canada has a good relationship with the United States, which is good. Seth says that they\'re also going to hear a lot of Scottish music, as well. Seth also says they\'ll hear some Canadian music that\'s Scottish in nature. At the end, Seth says, you can hear Donovan\'s song, \"Herdy Gertie man,\" which he thinks is a really good song. Seth is from Glasgow, Scotland, and he says that he has lived in Scotland his whole life.',NULL,NULL),(65606,2653,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/10/Solipsistic Retreat - October 10, 2023 at 10:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-10 10:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-30 22:46:34',NULL,'This week\'s program is all about the Negative Approach. It\'s about how Paul and John are actually the same person. Paul thanks John for helping him find a cop, and John thanks Paul for helping with the music. They\'re both really into the music and the music is really good.',NULL,NULL),(65607,2653,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/10/Solipsistic Retreat - October 10, 2023 at 09:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-10 09:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-30 22:27:25',NULL,'The band begins by answering the question, \"What is the killing-joke?\" The first question is, \"Is it a comic?\" The second question is \"Is It an album from Batman?\" The third question is whether it is a 1980s album by the band \"The Killing Joke\" or a 2003 album by \"The Laughing Dudes.\n\n\" The band explains that they are not talking about the music, but about the people. The people matter. The band is about to go on a trip and they are about to hear a