o the show. He also gives a shout-out to the band Frank Zappa.',NULL,NULL),(65876,113,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/12/Android’s Dungeon - October 12, 2023 at 13:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-12 13:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-30 01:53:21',NULL,'The first part of the show is devoted to the definition of a \"geek\" and how it\'s different from a \"nerd\" . The first definition is that of someone who finds their passion and decides to share that passion with others.\n\nThe second definition is for someone who becomes an evangelist for something they\'ve seen, heard, or read about. So, if you\'re a musician and you find out that Miles Davis is a big influence on you, you can talk to someone about it and they\'ll tell you about it, too. Now, if someone says they\'re going to a jazz conference and they decide to listen to all of this music, you\'ll be a nerd because it\'ll consume all of your time. The third definition is a person who becomes a nerd when their past becomes the center of their personality, and they can\'t relate to the people around them.\n\nSo we get the idea that people are all \"geeks\" and \"nergs\" in this particular case. The only difference is that the first definition says something like, \"I\'m a geeky person if I really like music and can talk about it\" while the second definition says, \"It consumes your life\" and you can just go listen to the music and not feel like you\'ve been a part of something. So that\'s the definition. The guys are now able to go to the bank and listen to their show and see if they',NULL,NULL),(65877,13307,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/12/Eclectic Selections - October 12, 2023 at 14:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-12 14:00:00',86638720,'2023-11-30 01:30:05',NULL,'The show begins with a cover mini-theme, this time featuring a jazz vocalist named Patricia Barber. She sings a song called \"She\'s A Lady,\" and we learn that she\'s a \"traitor with respect\" .\n\nWe also learn that the song was originally wr