ls us about his introduction to improvisation. He adds that his parents are opera singers and classical pianists.',NULL,NULL),(66685,122,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/20/Forever Deaf - October 20, 2023 at 00:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-20 00:00:00',86638720,'2023-11-26 14:07:27',NULL,'This is the first time we\'ve heard Black Braid\'s \"Moss Covered Bones on the Altar of the Moon\" on the show, and it\'s the longest running song on the program. It goes something like this: \"In the United States, this is Blackbraid with moss-covered bones on the moon on forever deaf years. for over 30 years. This is forever deaf!\" . We\'ve also heard \"As in Hell With the Island of the Dead Men\" , \"Wake Before That\" and \"Slaughter to Prevail With Viking\" . Judas Priest has announced that they\'ll be releasing a new album called Invincible Shield in 2024. The first song is \"Panic Attack,\" and the first video',NULL,NULL),(66686,122,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/19/Forever Deaf - October 19, 2023 at 23:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-19 23:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-26 13:48:14',NULL,'The next song is from Nick\'s band, which is playing some new material. The first song is a new song from a band called Tomb Mold, who have just released their new album, The Enduring Spirit, and are also playing some brand new music. The next band is called Baffled-Brains, who were once a band known as the Brains. They have released a new record and are currently based in Vancouver. The band is releasing a new album called F Off 2020 on the 25th of this month, and the first song they\'re going to play is a song called Stoned',NULL,NULL),(66696,122,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/20/Forever Deaf - October 20, 2023 at 01:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-20 01:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-26 13:28:18',NULL,'The host returns to his regular Thursday night gig at the host\'s house. The show opens with a long monologue about how the world is full of different artists and how they all 