of the next year and he\'s about to go to the K.',NULL,NULL),(66785,135,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/20/Folk Roots Radio - October 20, 2023 at 17:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-20 17:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-26 10:49:33',NULL,'The show opens with a conversation between Andrew Lambrecht and his friend, Jan Hall. They\'re both musicians, and Lambrecht is a member of a band called the Walked 45- 45s. They play a song called \"Thanks,\" which was written by Dave McEntire. They also play songs by March and April, who play a duet called \"Not to Fall,\" by Cody Walters and Faris Romero, and by Meredith Moon, who plays an instrumental called \"Needle Case Melody.\n\n\" This is the first time anyone has played a song that is the daughter of a famous folk singer. Next, we hear from Bruce Coburn, who reflects on his life on his latest album \"Osan Omen,\" which has already been critically acclaimed. Then we hear a song from Manitoba Prairie singer-songwriter, Del Barber, called \"On the Miladyhaha Taxi,\" which is a song about a female sailor who travels around the world. And then we hear the song \"On Lake Superior Sunset\" by Pete Eastmures from his latest release \"Devil\'s Sunset.\" And then there\'s \"Sea Glass\" by the Gallants, who are a band from the South.',NULL,NULL),(66786,128,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/20/Walkuman Style - October 20, 2023 at 18:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-20 18:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-26 10:24:17',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(66796,129,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/20/Digital Statik - October 20, 2023 at 19:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-20 19:00:00',86507776,'2023-11-26 10:04:31',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(66797,3686,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/20/Volunteer Playlist - October 20, 2023 at 20:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-20 20:00:00',86638720,'2023-11-26 09:46:38',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(66807,132,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/20/Global Rare Grooves - October 20, 2023 at 21:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-20 21:0