ymes of all time, and it\'s a great way to end this song.',NULL,NULL),(67822,197,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/vbxpj5/phil_s_inn_oct_14_237h1dy.mp3','2023-10-29 05:35:07',287962512,'2023-11-17 14:12:40',NULL,'The two talk about the end of the season. The place is full. The Pumpkin Pie Society has been baking pies in their rooms, and they\'re just appreciative of Yankee dollars. They\'re also getting ready for fall. The two make pumpkin pie spice cookies and then sit down to enjoy the afternoon.\n\nThe show is called \"Acoustic Music\" and it\'s going to be Jonathan Richmond and Tommy Larkins. It\'s always a great show. The program starts off with a hymn called \"Come Thou Faunt Of Every Blessing\" written in 1748 by a young poet named Robert Robinson. The song is so suited to the voice of Sufjan. Then we hear \"Old Brown Shoe\" written by George Harrison, \"The B Side of The Ballad of John And Yoko\" by Robert Robinson, \"Get Away\" by Young Ryland Co.\n\n, and \"Sure Enough Did i Do\" by a song called \"Chicken or Egg\" by the Captain Beefheart Magic Band. We also learn that Jonathan Richmond will be in town on October 23 for a \"Gary Top\" and \"CIUT\" presentation. It was such a great time, he says, that it will be \"a great concert\" .',NULL,NULL),(67823,197,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/3enkiq/phil_s_inn_oct_28_237xgm3.mp3','2023-10-29 05:24:34',287962512,'2023-11-17 13:58:19',NULL,'This is a short interview with Dave Kane, a musician and founder of the Roots Ramp Collective, a collective of musicians, artists, and writers who live in Toronto. The interview is part one of a three-part series in which Dave tells his story. The first part of the interview takes place in a hotel room, where he describes the state of affairs in the building.\n\nThe second part takes place at the sound booth, where the musician and his friends listen to music. They begin with a song called \"I Feel Sanctified By the Commodores\" from a series of vinyl records, and the third part of this interview is a piece by Anne Pebbles called \"Can\'t Stand The Rain.\" The fourth part focuses on Maria Callis\'s performance of a piece called \"The Wall-E.\"',NULL,NULL),(67824,144,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/29/The Underground - October 29, 2023 at 00:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-29 00:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-17 13:44:50',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(67825,144,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/28/The Underground - October 28, 2023 at 23:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-28 23:00:00',86638720,'2023-11-17 14:02:38',NULL,' ',NULL,NULL),(67835,144,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/29/The Underground - October 29, 2023 at 01:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-29 01:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-17 13:30:15',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(67863,145,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/29/Visions fugitives - October 29, 2023 at 08:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-29 08:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-17 13:22:39',NULL,'In this episode, the co-hosts explain that they are each choosing a piece of music to play each week. Each week, they will respond to the other\'s selections by choosing their own. For example, this week Fangwei will play a work by Morton Siotnik and another by Pablo Neruda called United Fruit Company.',NULL,NULL),(67873,145,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/29/Visions fugitives - October 29, 2023 at 09:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-29 09:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-17 13:09:14',NULL,'The program opens with a discussion of Beethoven\'s Op. 17 , which is a cycle of nine dance movements. In this program, Christopher Curry responds to the recital with a piano concerto that he has selected for the week. The piano concerto he has chosen is not by Maurice Ravel, but rather by Eric Wolfgang , who lost an arm in the First World War. The piece, called the Piano Concerto for Left Hand, was written in 1922 for Paul Wittgenstein who lost his arm during the war, and was composed for the left-hand side of the piano. It is also written for Howard Shelley, who played it with the BBC Symphony Orchestra and conductor Matthias Spard.',NULL,NULL),(67874,146,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/29/The Kookoo Bananas Variety Hour - October 29, 2023 at 10:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-29 10:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-08 14:31:23',NULL,'The gang teases the audience by playing a short song called \"Scarecrow Songs.\" It\'s about Clementine, a song that\'s been sung by a guy named John Zacharels. Yeah, this guy is a big fan of Clementine, because she\'s a big favorite of his. But he\'s also got a new love in the making, a new crush named Clementine. The gang asks everyone in the house what their favorite candy is for Halloween. The oldest kid, Henry, says that his favorite is chocolate. The second oldest kid is Henry\'s friend, Rowan, who says that he likes snickers too much. The third kid is a teenager named Henry Jr. who says he likes chocolate too. The fourth kid is Jacky, who likes candy too.','This is our ninth Halloween special. We have so many songs so many scary songs to play. Let\'s go around the room and find out what everyone\'s favorite candy to receive on Halloween is. Rowan bought a padlock for his pillowcase. It\'s my last year I need to make the most of it.','Halloween Candy Picks (Sponsor - Part I)'),(67884,148,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/29/Clan Na Gael - October 29, 2023 at 12:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-29 12:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-17 12:57:47',NULL,'This is a short program about the Clan Na Gael, a Scottish folk band. The program starts out with a song by Nonie Thompson, followed by a song from the movie Braveheart. It\'s a bit of a departure from the Clan\'s usual songs, but the music is still very good. The band closes out the program with another song from a collection of Scottish songs called Silver Collection. Marian Anderson\'s band also performs the song, but it\'s not as good as the first one.',NULL,NULL),(67894,101,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/29/Seems Like Old Times - October 29, 2023 at 14:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-29 14:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-17 12:47:11',NULL,'The program starts off with a song recorded in 1941. It\'s called \"Seems Like Old Times\" and it\'s about Helen Forrest and her orchestra coming back to Europe.\n\nThe song is also called \"Down, Down, Down\" and is the title of this program. The program goes on and on about how much music and music history has changed over the years. Dick Hames is one of the greatest songwriters of all time, and he\'s coming to town with a tribute to his music. A Christmas Craft and Artisan Sale will be held in Guelph on Saturday from 10am to 3pm. It will be a unique event. It sounds like \"Holly\" from the Makebelieve Ballroom CD. We\'ll also be back on the air with \"Young at Heart\" from 1954.\n\nAnd then we\'re back to Frank Sinatra. He\'s singing Young at Heart on the program. And then he\'ll say hi to a couple of his listeners. Finally, the program closes with two more songs. The first is \"Bogie Woogie Bugle boy\" from Bette Midle and the second is \"Buddy Holly\" from Andrews sisters. And finally, \"Halloween is coming up\" and the program is going to scare you',NULL,NULL),(67895,148,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/29/Clan Na Gael - October 29, 2023 at 13:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-29 13:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-17 12:35:05',NULL,'The show begins with a selection of songs from the Reel Time CD. The first song is Kelphic Thunder, a song by the Proclaimers. The second song is \"I\'m Going To Be 500 Miles\" , a Scottish song, and the third song is Rattlin. The band has disbanded, and they have put together an EP.\n\nThe fourth song is a song called \"Both Sides of The Tweed\" . The fifth song is the \"Fury Brothers and Arthur from Furys Finest,\" a song written by Eric Bogle . And the sixth song is The \"Greenfields of France,\" a version of the song that Bogle wrote. The seventh song is Rob\'s Pipe. The piper plays a piece from the Piper Legacy and D\'U A R T\'S Castle CD. He says that he plays some pipes. The next song is Maggie and Cassie from the Sterling Road CD. They sing about the \"King\'s Shilling,\" which sounds like it was written in Ireland and England, but in reality it\'s probably Scottish. The song starts off as a Celtic song, but then it changes its tune and sounds more like an English song. So the next song on the show',NULL,NULL),(67905,101,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/29/Seems Like Old Times - October 29, 2023 at 15:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-29 15:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-17 12:23:15',NULL,'\"The Black Figurine of Death\" The Black Figurine \"of Death\" is a tale of fear, and this is the kind of fear that most of us will have in life. The narrator begins his story by explaining that he is afraid of death itself, and that he has experienced this fear firsthand.\n\nHe tells the story of the night his Uncle Amos died, when he held a small figurine in his hand. The figurine was dead, and no one was there to see it. He goes on to explain that all of the people of the Hall of Fame will want to know what it is like to be filled with fear, a fear that will last for the rest of their lives. He then tells them that they will wish they had never known him, that they would never be born before he died.\n\nHe says that they all will learn how to fear, like the pieces in a jigsaw puzzle, and they will learn to fear even more. Three days after his death, he is buried in the Johnson family land. Ten days later, the narrator reads his uncle\'s will. It divides the property equally among the three main sons.',NULL,NULL),(67906,149,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/29/La Buena Onda - October 29, 2023 at 16:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-29 16:00:00',86507648,'2023-10-29 22:07:15',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(67911,170,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/by837d/MUS-TU-4P_31_oct_-_2023-10-29_943_PMaojll.mp3','2023-10-30 01:48:59',111378520,'2023-11-17 12:08:27',NULL,'Ruby Slippers, the station manager, and program director, have given the hosts a second hour to perform some new music. The show begins with a brand new song from Alice and Cammy. The first song is from a duo called Mccarr, and the second is a song called Fancy Hercules.\n\nThe third song is Douglas Von Ervins Carnival from the Meet the Monsters. The fourth song is a message from a band called Ace Of Wands. The last song is one from CIUT, which is a well-known Halloween-kind of place. The band says that they\'re wishing everyone a happy Halloween. After this show, the hosts leave the listeners with some more songs from the Dolly Rot\'s.',NULL,NULL),(67917,200,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/g23gqj/karibuni_oct_28-236aisn.mp3','2023-10-30 01:59:56',287962512,'2023-11-17 11:57:37',NULL,'In this short conversation, we learn that the Bolshoi Theater is bringing a production of the opera \"From the Roots Up\" to Chicago. The Bolshoim\'s Artistic Director, Alexandre Dumas, has just won a prestigious prize at the Theater Club of Chicago for his artistic direction of the production. We also learn that Alexandre\'s wife, Nadine, recently won a major award at the same Theater Club. We learn from the Artistic Director that Alexandre intends to continue his work for at least another 100 years.',NULL,NULL),(67918,207,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/9vskru/Music_w_db_Hawkes_Nov_1_2023_podcast9tf2v.mp3','2023-10-30 12:00:05',281801664,'2023-11-17 11:43:50',NULL,'The next morning, kids want to eat chocolate-covered bars for breakfast, which is a big departure from their normal breakfast routine. The problem is that they\'ve got tons of candy. The trick is to slowly eat the candy down, so that it\'s gone down quickly.\n\nThe other option is to put the kids on a strict diet where they only get to eat a certain amount of food a day, and they can choose what they want. The third option, the one that makes sense to the author, is to let the kids gorge themselves on the candy, which will get rid of the sugar quickly. This way, the kids will learn to control their appetites later on.',NULL,NULL),(67919,78,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/30/Morning Soul Shake-Up! - October 30, 2023 at 08:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-30 08:00:00',86638720,'2023-11-17 11:33:24',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(67920,108,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/29/Wind-Down - October 29, 2023 at 20:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-29 20:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-17 11:21:52',NULL,'This program is for you. It\'s called \"The Wind-Down\" and it\'s all about music. It starts off with a selection of spooky music and then we\'re introduced to October Country and my girlfriend is a witch.\n\nIf you want to know more about the music, check out the show\'s play-by-play page at the wind down. Here\'s what we learned today: \"The Shadow is also source of light / That produced that shadow.\" This is a reference to the song Crying Contest by the band Mother Tongues. And then we get a new song from Twin Temple called Let\'t Have a Satanic orgy. We then get a song from The Specials called Ghost Town. Then we get two songs from the Beach Loveitch called Sugar Land and October. The program ends with La Force by Exoskeleton.',NULL,NULL),(67921,110,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/30/Here Today - October 30, 2023 at 07:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-30 07:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-07 05:59:50',NULL,'Aaron Badgley is back with his \"halloween\" show. He\'s going to kick it off with a song by Bing Crosby, \"I am a demon\" . Badgley explains that he\'s not a fan of trick-or-treating at all, but he\'ll do his best to entertain listeners. He tells listeners that he is a \"demon\" , a \"vampire\" and a \"wolfman\" ; that he sings songs about the supernatural . Finally, he explains that the song about the gums is actually a song about \"the gums\" and \"the g\" : \"The gums are called \'the gums\' . The g is called the gums, the g is the gums.',NULL,'Aaron Badgley\'s \"Halloween\" show kicks off with Bing Crosby song \"I am a de'),(67922,150,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/29/Zombie Jamboree - October 29, 2023 at 19:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-29 19:00:00',86638720,'2023-11-17 11:11:18',NULL,'The UM takes over the program to discuss the upcoming Zombie Jamboree. He says that he\'s going to focus on the things that are important to him, such as how to survive in the dark. He also mentions that the first song he\'ll play tonight is from the special Bataclan concert. Next up will be \"The Wind Down.\"',NULL,NULL),(67923,150,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/29/Zombie Jamboree - October 29, 2023 at 18:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-29 18:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-17 11:00:44',NULL,'This is the second part of the interview with Bruce, who introduces himself as \"your dungeon master\" and \"S-world in the next\" . This is part one of a two-part interview. The first part is about Bruce\'s role as a dungeon master and part two is about the music.\n\nThe music starts off with a song called \"MMIGW2s\" meaning \"Missing and Murdered Girls Women, and Two-spirited People\" , and it ends with \"It\'s Future Memories\". The music is a mix of songs, including two songs by Feller Kutu and two by Dave. The song \"Munich Central\" is also a song, and part one ends with the song \"Moth Yellow\".\n\nThe songs are all part of a service from the University of Guelph, which can be found on the university\'s website at www.curriculum.ca. The second part starts with Dave\'s explanation of his father\'s wolfman background, and then includes songs by Elizabeth, Sarah Through Chronoscope, Colliding Canyon, and the Yayaaz along with Dr Octagon. The Yayazes lead a \"Zombie Jamboree\" seminar, which is also part of this interview. It',NULL,NULL),(67924,149,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/29/La Buena Onda - October 29, 2023 at 17:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-29 17:00:00',86507648,'2023-10-30 14:07:39',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(67925,152,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/29/Through the Looking Glass - October 29, 2023 at 21:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-29 21:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-17 10:50:05',NULL,'The show continues with a song from Woodhawk, followed by one from Well Bad and one from the Canadian artist Cammy Van- Houst. The first song is called \"My Alice featuring Barry\" and the second song is \"Am I Carrie\".',NULL,NULL),(67926,154,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/30/This Night Wounds Time - October 30, 2023 at 01:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-30 01:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-17 10:40:41',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(67927,154,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/30/This Night Wounds Time - October 30, 2023 at 00:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-30 00:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-17 10:34:54',NULL,'This chapter opens with the announcement that the band is going to play music from all over the world. The band has been going through different provinces of Buenos Aires for a while, and they\'ve been missing a show. So, they\'re back to the music. This time, though, it\'s Halloween. And, as always, the music will be a little different. Instead of playing music that\'s associated with the supernatural, it will be music from an Australian band called The Church.\n\nThe Church\'s first album, Sometime Any Place, came out in 1994. A lot of people think that this album and its follow-up, Among the Spirits, are the worst albums ever recorded by the band. But, according to the band, these albums aren\'t so bad. They\'re just not good enough. The first album is called Skins and Hearts, and it was recorded by a guy named Nick Ward. The second worst album is Seance, which was recorded in 1983, but it was also recorded with a production error that made the drums sound like \"pistol shots.\"',NULL,NULL),(67928,154,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/29/This Night Wounds Time - October 29, 2023 at 23:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-29 23:00:00',86638720,'2023-11-17 10:21:47',NULL,'This night, the band plays a psychedelic rock show. The band starts with a set from Vanishing Twin, followed by Chuck Copenas\'s \"Current,\" a track from \"Requisites,\" and then a track by Faith Healer. The show ends with an anticipatory song from The Church.',NULL,NULL),(67929,153,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/29/Backtracks - October 29, 2023 at 22:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-29 22:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-17 10:10:43',NULL,'On this edition of CFRU 93.3, host Jennifer Eileen explains the history of Halloween. She tells listeners that it is a Celtic festival that marks the end of harvest and the start of winter. She explains that the festival of Samhain, also known as Samain, was believed to mark the beginning of the winter. The festival was celebrated with bonfires and animal skins. The name of the festival comes from All-Hath-Eve, which means \"All-Saints-Day\" or \"All Hallows Eve.\" The festival is celebrated on the eve of the feast of All Saints',NULL,NULL),(67939,79,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/30/Breezy Breakfast Radio - October 30, 2023 at 10:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-30 10:00:00',86638720,'2023-11-09 04:38:32',NULL,'Fazzari ran down Morris Street and died on the front porch in Morris Street. He moved back to the city after being detained for a while. He ran away with a woman who was running a boarding house. She was named Bessie. She had two children who were assumed to be middle-class Jewish girls. She left them with her husband and her two children. She ran away to Hamilton with Perry. He became one of the most successful legger in the city. Bessie\'s story surprised Perry because he was a very different person from Verroni. He carried all the family grudges against Verroni in Italy. He didn\'t lay aside that Perry was more a business man. He looked it. He worked with blacks, he worked with northern Italians, even worked with Americans. He knew that he had to put it aside. Verroni was indiscriminate in killing people. He had his own group of people who would go missing. Perry continued to rise. Bessie told her grandfather that she worked for him and she went looking for him. She told him that they needed to make money and besides Perry was a nice guy. They went inside Perry\'s home and then Bessie told him what was going on. They didn\'',NULL,'Bessie\'s story surprised Perry because she was a very different person from Verroni (13 minute read)'),(67940,79,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/30/Breezy Breakfast Radio - October 30, 2023 at 09:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-30 09:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-09 04:22:41',NULL,'This week\' s episode of the Breezy breakfast takes place in Guelph and features three guests: Susan Radcliffe, who will be on-air, Jay Walking, who has included a spooky dress code around the city, and Bonnie Derthnall. Phil Ault welcomes everyone to the show and begins by acknowledging the city\'s rich Indigenous history. The city has served as a refuge for many generations of people, but more specifically for the Anorwandrung and Haudenosaune. This land is part of the treaty lands of the Mississaugas. The guests are invited to hear stories of the past from three great guests, but the guests are free to express their own opinions. Phil notes that the show is a special one because it is a holiday, and he feels that this is his favorite of the year',NULL,'The Breezy Breakfast: Guelph, Canada (Sponsor)'),(67950,1438,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/30/Worst Responders - October 30, 2023 at 12:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-30 12:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-17 09:57:37',NULL,'In this episode, Carissa and Renee discuss their show, \"Worst Responders.\" The show is a satirical comedy about horror movies and their problems.\n\nIt is a comedy that is in good fun, but it does not represent the opinions of the College. It also does not support \"murder, ghouls, or goblins,\" or any other visitors who \"maim or otherwise injure human mortals.\" Carissa says she never really thought about Halloween and that she is excited to discuss the \"maiming\" of humans. She has dressed up as a \"Cthulhuth,\" a \"weird\" creature, and she says that she would pass for a normal human being if she were dressed in a costume that didn\'t look like a haggard old man.\n\nShe also says that her favorite thing about Halloween was when she was with a friend and they would have kids come to their house to get candy. She says that was the \"first time\" she got the \"joy\" of Halloween. She loves children who don\'t have a clue what is going on and who just stare at her dead-eyed because they haven\'t yet figured out what\'s going on.',NULL,NULL),(67951,1437,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/30/Democracy Now - October 30, 2023 at 11:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-30 11:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-17 09:47:24',NULL,'Israel has killed more than 8,000 Palestinians, including 3,500 children, in its latest attack on the Gaza Strip. The United Nations says the siege of the coastal territory has reached its breaking point. Families of Israeli prisoners held by Hamas call on the government to exchange their loved ones for the prisoners. Meanwhile, Prime Minister BenjaminNetanyahu has apologized on social media after he published a statement blaming the attack on civilians. The Palestinian death toll has reached 111, and seven settlers have been killed, including Bila Saleh. On October 30, Israeli bulldozers demolished a memorial for a slain journalist in the West Bank.',NULL,NULL),(67961,206,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/dgvbjv/October_28th_2023_The_Minx_Sessionsa9qp7.mp3','2023-10-30 19:19:51',287962512,'2023-11-17 09:37:54',NULL,'The host of the underground music station, CIUT 8, introduces himself to his listeners and tells them that he\'s just getting started. He wants to thank them for listening to his show, which is packed with independent artists and music from all over the world.\n\nHe\'s going to kick things off tonight with a \"little boogie\" and a \"really awesome drummer bass piece\" by an artist named \"Mikel Sessions.\" The show is going to continue on Fridays from midnight until 2am. The host also tells us that he has added all of the links to all the music that he plays on his show. He also says that he wants to play Tom Hates\'s music now.',NULL,NULL),(67962,247,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/ihtvqc/October_28th_2023_Calling_All_Blues6qtfp.mp3','2023-10-30 19:24:32',143961989,'2023-11-15 01:05:42',NULL,'The next segment of the program is called \"Calling All Blues.\" It\'s all about the music and the people that are playing it. It starts off with a conversation about a singer named Shakur Saeedas second track, and then it turns to a conversation between Bill Withers and Susie Vinnick, who are both playing some blues. The conversation then turns to an old friend named Eugene Smith, who used to play the tenor guitar with his brothers. Now that he\'s dead, he\'ll be playing the kalimba again.',NULL,NULL),(67963,37839,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/30/Feeding Tummies and Souls - October 30, 2023 at 14:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-30 14:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-15 00:56:19',NULL,'After a few years of living with his stepdad and stepmom, David decides to return to Canada. He loves coming home for Canada Day. The fireworks are his favorite. When he turns 16, his step dad and mom separate. David moves back to Canada with his dad, step mom, three younger siblings and his two teenage brothers. He begins counseling with a woman at Kids\'Ability, who is wheelchair-bound. The woman makes an impact on David\'s life.\n\nWhen David graduates from high school, he receives the Optimist Award for overcoming adversity. He is given a pass to attend his graduation ceremony, but returns to Polarwood for the night because of his second bout of depression. He enrolls in an early childhood program at Conestog College. He finds a mentor at Action Program Read who encourages him to follow his dreams. He volunteers at daycare and in elementary schools when he turns 18. He graduates from the program when he is 18.',NULL,NULL),(67964,37839,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/30/Feeding Tummies and Souls - October 30, 2023 at 13:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-30 13:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-15 00:42:26',NULL,'The program opens with a description of the event, which was originally presented as a benefit for the Harvest Market. The program is a mix of poetry, spoken word, and storytelling. It is also a celebration of National Indigenous History month. The stories will be told from the point of view of five young people who were forced to live in a residential school.\n\nThe audience will be able to donate to the Harvest market directly. The performers will also have a chance to chat with the audience during the performances. The live performers will be turning off the live chat during their performances. As a thank you for listening, the program ends with a brief interview with Jenny Mitchell, the volunteer and mobile studio coordinator at CFRU. Jenny is on parental leave and has just returned to her job.',NULL,NULL),(67974,196,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/rcyuq3/October_29_2023_Across_the_Universeakhzr.mp3','2023-10-30 20:09:29',431961989,'2023-11-15 00:31:09',NULL,'This is a special edition of the Sunday morning program on the free-form, open-air, FM radio station, CIUT 89.5. The program is all about the fall campaign, \"The Sound of your City,\" which will take place beginning on November 13th and concluding on November 19th.\n\nThe station will need your financial support to continue to serve the community and to provide listeners with the best of the best. If you\'re a regular listener of the station, then you already know all about it. But there are some people who are new to the station and they\'re only listening for a short period of time. So they need to make a donation. To do this, you can go to the website and sign up for the program. This is the first program of the day and it\'s all about raising money for the station. It\'s a celebration of his mother\'s life.',NULL,'The Toronto Tabla\'s narrator tells listeners about their new album and their live show'),(67975,81,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/30/The Sentinel’s Marvellous Kaleidoscope - October 30, 2023 at 15:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-30 15:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-15 00:21:31',NULL,'This is a little bit of a mouthful, but it\'s what we\'ve got to hear here: the first track on the new album is a remix of a piece from Solace Shard by Output 111.\n\nAfter that, we have a bunch of other stuff: the Victoria BC avant-garde experimental sound composer Marlen Arroma, the purveyors of free Will, the original track from their new Rolling Pathetique album, the track Man from the new Gold album, and the song from Kim Petras\'s new album, In the next life. The second track is a shortcut from Jenny is a witch, followed by another shortcut from The Riveen, and then the fifth track is from Post-Traumatic Stress Disorder, a new EP from Gold.',NULL,NULL),(67976,1591,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/30/New or Never - October 30, 2023 at 16:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-30 16:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-15 00:09:55',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(67986,83,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/30/to know the land - October 30, 2023 at 18:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-30 18:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-15 00:01:14',NULL,'In this chapter, the UM talks about his love for stories. He loves the fact that the stories can be repeated endlessly. But sometimes, stories are lost, and the themes that are there are lost. For example, he has been looking for stories about tracking signs of animals.\n\nHe knows stories like the Volscian Saga or the Beowulf. There are elements of this, but it\'s hard to find them. One of the themes he\'s looking for lately is stories about mushrooms. He\'s read a lot of books about the cultural value of mushrooms, but there aren\'t any stories about them in the stories. There\'s one of his favorite stories, which is about a young woman picking mushrooms. The young woman learns about the plants from the snakes that she encounters in the forest.',NULL,NULL),(67987,82,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/30/Big Sis Radio - October 30, 2023 at 17:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-30 17:00:00',86638720,'2023-11-14 23:46:52',NULL,'On this week\'s edition of Big Sis Jobs Radio, the narrator is psyched to get dressed up for Halloween. He\'s dressed as Steve Jobs, an iPod guy, and he\'s got a new trick up his sleeve: a black shirt and running shoes.\n\nThe narrator also has some scary songs to play, including a song about a haunted house and a song called \"I Don\'t like my mind\" by Mitzki. The song is about how our minds are full of all kinds of scary things, and that\'s scary. The next song is \"Haunted House on Zillow\" by The Garden and it\'s about how scary it is everywhere. This is a reminder that the world is scary, but it shouldn\'t scare you.',NULL,NULL),(67997,84,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/30/Blues Around the Block - October 30, 2023 at 20:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-30 20:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-14 23:35:09',NULL,'Mac Dee is a new host of Blues Around The Block. He\'s got a new name, but he\'s also got a bunch of old favorites. He starts off with Hamilton City\'s Smoke Wagon Blues Band, which is a band from the old days. Then, Tinsley Ellis, Just Like Rain, and Tommy Castro finish off the show.\n\nMac Dee wants to go home, so he starts with Kenny Neal\'s \"It Don\'t cost anything it don\'t-cost anything and spread a little love / Then Selwyn / Burchwood from June 2023 release of alligator records / Call me what you want / And Susan Tedesschi from September 2023 release/ On fantasy records/ Can\'t you leave you alone\" . This is all from CFRU\'s 93.3 FM. MacDee also starts with Kristin Ingram, aka Kingfish, from his September 23rd release on alligator-records live in London.',NULL,NULL),(67998,84,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/30/Blues Around the Block - October 30, 2023 at 19:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-30 19:00:00',86638720,'2023-11-14 23:26:24',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(68008,85,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/30/Ripcord Radio - October 30, 2023 at 21:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-30 21:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-14 23:17:13',NULL,'In this episode, the gang continues its program with a look at some of the latest metal acts. We start off with Denmark, who have a song called \"Trick or Treat\" from their latest album.\n\nThey also hear a song from Motorhead called \"I\'m your witch doctor\" and a song by the late great Eddie Clark called \"Motorhead with i\'m / Your witch doctor\". They hear a cover of John Mayall\'s \"Blues\" from the band Beer Drinkers And Hell Raisers. And finally they hear \"GBH with lycanthropy\" from Birmingham England. The band originally came together in 1980 under the name Fast Boys. They were not able to celebrate their 40th anniversary due to travel restrictions imposed by the CoVID-19 pandemic, but they have been busy touring ever since. They put on a great show here in Guelph in October as part of their tour celebrating the anniversary of their 33rd album City Babies Revenge. The next song is from the Los Angeles band Nice Blitz. The song comes from an EP called Not Lockdown. The first song we hear is from an album called All Serious Seriousness Aside. The second song is about a fictional murderer. The third song is a',NULL,NULL),(68009,86,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/30/The Deep House Project - October 30, 2023 at 22:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-30 22:00:00',86638720,'2023-10-31 04:56:55',NULL,'The show kicks off with a music selection from the 90s. It\'s called Future Shock and it\'s a horror movie set in a virtual reality world. It also has a book and a short movie about how people get stressed and paralyzed by too much change. The music is all about going back and forth in time. Way back, way back. Way way back, Way back! Way back... Way back. The group then goes back in time to listen to a song called Spooky Cowboy, which sounds very much like a mass-produced costume. The song basically says, \"I\'m not a cowboy, I\'ve got a plan. I\'ll never be wrong.\"',NULL,'Future Shock is a horror movie set in a virtual reality world. Way back, way back'),(68019,80,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/31/CFRU Playlist - October 31, 2023 at 06:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-31 06:00:00',86638720,'2023-10-31 14:06:18',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(68020,78,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/31/Morning Soul Shake-Up! - October 31, 2023 at 08:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-31 08:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-14 23:56:30',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(68021,87,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/30/Back in the USSR - October 30, 2023 at 23:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-30 23:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-14 22:49:56',NULL,'In this Dispatches, the human rights journalist and author of the book, The Return of the Detainee, discusses Israel\'s recent war in the Gaza Strip with journalist and documentary maker, Abi Martin. She also discusses her latest work, which is called \"Gaza Frights For Freedom,\" which was released four years ago and continues to be an important part of the discourse on the situation in the Middle East.',NULL,NULL),(68023,1447,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/31/Rainbow Country - October 31, 2023 at 01:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-31 01:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-14 22:39:52',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(68024,1447,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/31/Rainbow Country - October 31, 2023 at 00:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-31 00:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-14 22:30:02',NULL,'On this episode of Rainbow Country, host and producer Mark Tara introduces his guests, including porn star Chris Harder and award-winning author Karen Michaelsen. In addition, they discuss the latest film, Dick\'s the Musical, and the novel, The Maynith\'s God. In this episode, Tara also talks with the stars of the film, Josh Sharp, and Aaron Jackson about their work.\n\nFinally, he talks about the money that keeps rolling in his pocket. He says, \"The good times never cease. There\'ve never been man like me, and I always have been on top.\" He also talks about Craig Tittle and Trevor Brock, his two top salesmen, who look like they could be twins, but they\'re actually twins. He thinks that if mom and dad get married, then they\'ll have a real, family-like family. He feels that he\'s gay, and he only plays to win a woman boss.',NULL,NULL),(68034,2653,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/31/Solipsistic Retreat - October 31, 2023 at 10:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-31 10:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-14 22:20:07',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(68035,2653,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/31/Solipsistic Retreat - October 31, 2023 at 09:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-31 09:00:00',86638720,'2023-11-14 22:12:57',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(68036,38498,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2019/10/31/CFR Booo! - October 31, 2019 at 16:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2019-10-31 16:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-14 22:04:34',NULL,'In this episode of the College Radio Hour, the CFRU student narrator explains the station\'s mission and how it\'s being used to raise awareness of issues facing the university and its students.\n\nHe plays a song by Andrew Collins from the band Hamburger Hot Dog, which he co-wrote. The song is about a family who built a small shanty on the banks of the river and were destroyed by a wind one October night, when their butane stove caught fire. The couple and their child were presumed dead, and the city evicted the river people. The narrator then plays songs by Pink Moth and The Smack It is Way.',NULL,NULL),(68037,38498,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2019/10/31/CFR Booo! - October 31, 2019 at 15:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2019-10-31 15:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-14 21:48:58',NULL,'This episode of CFRU Boo is all about the music, and it\'s all about a place called the Homewood sanitarium, which opened in 1883 and was used to treat people who were disturbed by the supernatural. Since its inception, patients have flocked to the hospital for experimental electroshock treatments. Many patients complain of headaches and hallucinations, but the medical community has been impressed with the success of the treatment. The patients are cast into a basement deep in the bowels of the hospital, left to stew in their agony within their minds.\n\nMany cry, some say on a clear night. The first song on the program is \"Big Black Death\" off of the album \"The Singing from Mount erie\" by local artist Cots. The second song is \"Cotts\" from the album, \"The Song from Mount Erie\" by Pooch Yates. The third song is from \"Evan Gordon\'s Haunted History of Guelph\" about a \"haunted kind of ghostwalk\" we had with Evan a few years back. The fourth song is a \"horrible soul\" singing their last song. The fifth song is the live version of \"Cots\" by the local artist, Pooch. The live version is \"',NULL,NULL),(68038,38498,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2019/10/31/CFR Booo! - October 31, 2019 at 14:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2019-10-31 14:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-14 21:35:06',NULL,'This week on the program, Tom talks about the upcoming Guelph Film Festival. The festival is taking place from November 1 to 9th. He tells the listeners that they can listen to the program on their own devices and on the web. They can also make a donation to the festival. The program ends with a reminder that the festival is coming up on October 31st.',NULL,NULL),(68039,38498,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2018/10/31/CFR Booo! - October 31, 2018 at 20:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2018-10-31 20:00:00',86638720,'2023-11-14 21:20:03',NULL,'This week\'s program is a mix of news and music from the Guelph area. It begins with a brief announcement from the host of the station, who says that the program called CFRU Rhythm will not be airing tonight because of a technical issue. The program will instead be airing a rebroadcast that was originally airing earlier this year, Eternal Rhythm. The host also announces that the upcoming Guelph Film Festival will take place on November 2nd and 10th.',NULL,NULL),(68040,38498,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2017/10/31/CFRBooo! - October 31, 2017 at 19:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2017-10-31 19:00:00',86376576,'2023-11-14 19:10:16',NULL,'This program is a mix of news and music from the CFRU campus. The program begins with the announcement that the university has a power outage. The station is broadcasting via backup generators, but they are still doing their Boo show. The show\'s director, Christopher, explains that he had planned to come on at 6.35 but had to come early because of a power surge at the university.',NULL,NULL),(68041,38498,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2017/10/31/CFRBooo! - October 31, 2017 at 18:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2017-10-31 18:00:00',86376576,'2023-11-14 18:58:02',NULL,'Welcome back, we\'re back on the streets of Guelph, where we left off. Okay, so this is where it all started: the Underground Pit. Just outside of the city limits lies a mysterious sinkhole. The Ministry of Environment can\'t figure out what\'s going on, but it\'s causing all kinds of weird noises and sickness in the neighborhood.\n\nAround this same time last year a mom and daughter decided to climb into the pit to play a game. The kids heard weird noises, and some people even got sick from the pit. Now we find out that this is the same place where the underground pit used to be, the Homewood Sanatorium. It\'s where people from all over the world go to undergo electroshock therapy. Unfortunately, these people don\'t like it, and they end up in the basement of the Sanatorium with all the pain and suffering. The story of the underground hospital is just one of many stories of people suffering and dying from their own misfortunes.',NULL,NULL),(68042,38498,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2017/10/31/CFRBooo! - October 31, 2017 at 17:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2017-10-31 17:00:00',86376576,'2023-11-14 18:42:01',NULL,'The second edition of the Secret Scope program opens with a description of the music on the program. It\'s a collection of progressive rock and alternative music from the Prague- and Alt-sounds. The music opens with the music from a children\'s game called Ned, which was released in 1997.\n\nThe music in this program comes from an upcoming quadruple listening set, which includes a new album from a Victoria artist named Rained a ton, an album from Brian Eno, a folk album from Philadelphia called Shadow band with Shadow Land, and a psychedelic rock album from Blood Ceremony. The program closes with the instrumental music from Maria Zuda\'s solo project, Lunatic soul.',NULL,NULL),(68043,38498,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2017/10/31/CFRBooo! - October 31, 2017 at 13:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2017-10-31 13:00:00',86376576,'2023-11-14 17:02:17',NULL,'The show opens with the theme of \"spooky\" and the song \"Goli Mar\" is a song from a movie about an actor called Chiranjeevi.\n\nThe song is from the movie \"Donga\" and it is from a song called \"Gol Mar\" by the singer. After the song is over, the group discusses the holiday of Halloween and its significance to them. The group discusses music and its importance to the holiday, and the songs that have been played in the past day. They decide to start with \"Fresh Prince\" and \"Are You Ready For Freddy\" by Will Smith and the Fat Boys respectively. After \"Are you ready for Freddy,\" they will continue with \"Spooky Scary\" by Trey. He explains that he was \"wrong time\" to join the \"Wolfen Clan\" at his bar mitzvah.\n\nThe bar mitzvah was a success, but he was too busy to sing the song. He dances with his cousins and they had fun making \"circumcision jokes\" but then he remembers the song and remembers that the song was about a group of people who were all \"brain sucking pack\" and they were on the attack because they were \"all turned into zombies\" and were \"on the',NULL,NULL),(68044,38498,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2017/10/31/CFRBooo! - October 31, 2017 at 12:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2017-10-31 12:00:00',86376576,'2023-11-14 16:47:20',NULL,'This is the second part of a two-part interview with the host of the local music station, CFRU 95.3FM. The first part is about the upcoming Guelph Film Festival that\'s coming up in a few days. The host explains that the festival is for people interested in issues such as social justice, community building, and the environment. The second part is a little bit more personal. The show is going to take listeners back to the days of the jungle, when jungle music was more popular than today\'s alternative music.\n\nThe jungle music that the host is playing is actually one of the tracks from an album called Unified Colors, which was released in 1994. The show goes on to explain that the music is being played because it\'s lonely and lonely out in the cold and dark. The night sky is full of dark clouds and all kinds of things are lurking around you. The house where the show is taking place seems to be very scary. The only thing that seems to make the house more scary is the fact that there\'s electricity in the house. The music is playing because the house has some kind of power. This is because the place you\'re in seems to have some sort of power source. So you',NULL,NULL),(68054,1437,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/31/Democracy Now - October 31, 2023 at 11:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-31 11:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-14 16:30:40',NULL,'The war in the Gaza Strip continues, and the death toll has reached 8,500. As the war continues, the United Nations Childrens Agency warns that Israel is committing \"rampant grave violations\" of children\'s rights.\n\nThe agency\'s director-general warns that over 8,500 children have been killed in the last 26 days, most of them women and children. In the aftermath of the latest attacks, the Israeli military has pushed deeper into the besieged territory. The Israeli Prime Minister, Benjamin Netanyahu, has refused to agree on a ceasefire. He says that calls for Israel\'s surrender to Hamas are just calls for the surrender of Israel to terrorism. In response, Hamas has released a prisoner video showing three women held captive by the military wing of the Islamic militant group. The release of the women is a sign that Israel has freed one of the captives, Ori Megadish. The death of Shani Luke is also a sign of the end of the war.',NULL,NULL),(68055,38498,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/31/CFR Booo! - October 31, 2023 at 12:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-31 12:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-14 16:20:36',NULL,'This is the first time Jenny has been involved with the festival, and she is very excited. She is also excited because she has been part of the technology side of the event as well. She says that it is the busiest time of the year for her manager, Brian. They have a bunch of new volunteers this year, and they want to make sure that they are all up to speed on the latest technology.',NULL,NULL),(68065,38498,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/31/CFR Booo! - October 31, 2023 at 14:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-31 14:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-14 16:03:07',NULL,'In this chapter, we find out about the experiences of one of our students, who goes by the name of Dr. Brown. He was a medical student at the University of Nebraska Medical School. He had co-op at the medical school and was able to experience what medical procedures were and how they affected people.\n\nHe thinks it was a cool experience and that it encouraged him to go into medicine. Dr Brown notes that he thinks universities take into account the amount of experience students have at co-ops, but he doesn\'t know if they actually do. He does know that he got good recommendations for co-operation from the people at the school. He also thinks it\'s a good way to gain conflict resolution and understanding of people.\n\nEven if it didn\'t contribute to his degree, he still benefited from the co-operative experience. He says he never did coop in his high school but he did a ton of extracurriculars at school. The professors told him that if he were going into a particularly competitive school and there were lots of applicants and good grades, then things that separated students would be helpful, like co-curricular experiences. He adds that he did not get the best grades in his class, but that',NULL,NULL),(68066,38498,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/31/CFR Booo! - October 31, 2023 at 13:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-31 13:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-14 15:45:12',NULL,'In this episode of the CFRU 9:20AM program, the students discuss the band Per with the station\'s host, and the students also discuss the Per\'s early days. The students began playing music together when they were in high school, and they met at a bullring in the spring of last year.\n\nThey liked the opportunity to play together, and decided to keep playing. As the school year progressed, they spent more time together and the summer passed. Per says that they\'re back in full swing now, and that they plan to continue to play in the future. They\'re still a band, however, and have a sense of humor, which keeps them together.',NULL,NULL),(68076,1453,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/31/Silver Screen Dream Machine - October 31, 2023 at 15:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-31 15:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-14 15:29:20',NULL,'On this special edition of Dream Machine, we hear music from a variety of animated and live-action films. The first song we hear is the opening song from a 1993 stop-motion animated film called Before Christmas. The second song is from the 1991 animated film Beetlejuice. The third song is a parody of the song \"Ice Baby\" by Vanilla Ice. The fourth song is \"Trick or Treat\" from the 1995 animated film The Haunted Mask. The fifth song is the theme from the original animated film. The last song is entitled \"Ungrateful Dead\" from a 1988 animated movie called Haunted Halloween.',NULL,NULL),(68077,3033,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/31/A Multilingual Affair - October 31, 2023 at 16:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-31 16:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-14 15:13:32',NULL,'In this short scene, Eren introduces the listeners to the music that she plays on the university\'s 93.3FM. She and her co-presenter, Major Daijaskenuchena, are discussing the latest music in the university and the students\' response to it. The music in this scene is a mix of various kinds of music, including rap, rock, and folk. Eren encourages listeners to tune in and enjoy the music.',NULL,NULL),(68087,91,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/31/Tuesday at 5 - October 31, 2023 at 17:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-31 17:00:00',86638720,'2023-11-14 15:00:37',NULL,'This week\'s guest is Don Brenton, host of the local CFRU program \"Lenny Halloween\" . He\'s also a regular guest on the \"Tuesday at 5\" program on CFRU\'s 93.3FM. He starts the show off by telling us that Halloween is an ancient festival celebrated by the So-Wens, a group of ancient cults who believed that the ghosts of their dead loved ones returned to earth. On that night, they dressed up in animal skins and drove away phantom visitors',NULL,NULL),(68088,1455,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/31/Down the Rabbit Hole - October 31, 2023 at 18:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-31 18:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-14 09:40:29',NULL,'On this edition of the Underground Man\'s Nightly Show, the UM goes back to the music he played on the previous show. He starts off by playing a song called \"Feels Like Heaven\" by Ariel Pink, which reminds him a lot of his favorite band, MGMT. Next, he plays \"Reborn\" by Colin Stetson, from the soundtrack to the movie \"Haunted.\" Then he plays a song from the album \"Asteroid Blues\" by Eve\'s Tumor. Then, he\'ll play \"California Nebula\" by George Childdrainhole.',NULL,NULL),(68098,94,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/31/Let’s Get Lost - October 31, 2023 at 20:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-31 20:00:00',86638720,'2023-11-14 09:28:39',NULL,'Scott\'s name is Scott, and he\'s on stage with his band. They\'re going to play some music from a friend, Matt Gustafson, whose band is known as \"Fire. Fire!\" They\'ve also got a new album out called \"Echolocation,\" which is full of bat imagery. This is a brand new song to the band, so they\'re psyched to have it on their show. They also play a song from an EP called \"Requiesce,\" which invited Stephen O and David to sit in on the recording. This special is bringing \"Godspeed U,\" also known as Black Emperor, on stage, and they rarely play these tracks.',NULL,NULL),(68099,93,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/31/Melonaut Radio - October 31, 2023 at 19:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-31 19:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-14 09:19:20',NULL,'The narrator, whose given name is Alia Maxwell, is a musicologist and host of the podcast Melonaut. The show has aired for two years, due to other mysterious circumstances, but this year, they\'re releasing an entire special program.\n\nThis time, the narrator is trapped in an abandoned mansion in Ireland and has to use his own cassette tape recorder to communicate with outside the world. This is the second time he\'s been trapped in such an abandoned place, and the first time he found music on the abandoned house. The second time, he was transported to Dublin by a mysterious force, so he\'ll be airing this program from there. Before we get to the music, though, we need to know that this is a spooky holiday called Samhain.\n\nHistorically, this was a time when the boundaries between the worlds were crossed, and this meant that the spirits of the fairies, known as Aos Shih or the mount fairies, could come into the world and be particularly active. The Irish language means \"people of the mount\" and means \"the fairy mount\" in Irish. So, basically, the Irish people believe that the fairies live underground and can\'t see or hear them. They\'re also said to be',NULL,NULL),(68109,95,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/31/Humanoid Radio - October 31, 2023 at 22:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-31 22:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-14 09:05:07',NULL,'The second segment of the show is called \"Radio Humanoid\" and it begins with Audrey Ochoa playing a track called \"It Never Happened.\" The second track is followed by iGoma, the syndicate, and Bonsai. The next track is called Different. The last track is titled \"Kongo Symphag.\" The key to communicating with an alien is the technology of sending or receiving signals. The key is the language, says the narrator.',NULL,NULL),(68110,94,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/31/Let’s Get Lost - October 31, 2023 at 21:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-31 21:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-14 08:55:02',NULL,'The program begins with a description of the music on Gord Gurdina\'s project \"Let\'s Get Lost.\" The music on the show is described as \"cringe-worthy\" and \"snivel-worthy.\" The program concludes with an introduction to the CFRU.com website, which provides the listener with a wealth of information about the station, including a live broadcast stream, an on-line program guide, weekly music charts, and information on how to become a volunteer.',NULL,NULL),(68120,96,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/01/Cyber Lich’s Gothic Castle - November 1, 2023 at 00:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-01 00:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-14 08:44:34',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(68121,96,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/10/31/Cyber Lich’s Gothic Castle - October 31, 2023 at 23:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-10-31 23:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-14 08:37:33',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(68131,38669,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/01/NOSFERATU! - November 1, 2023 at 02:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-01 02:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-14 08:28:52',NULL,'As the war continues in the Gaza Strip, the United Nations Childrens Agency warns that Israel is committing \"rampant grave violations\" of children\'s rights. An Israeli warplane has attacked the Turkish- Palestinian Friendship Hospital, which serves as the sole hospital in the besieged territory for cancer treatment. The hospital has also been destroyed by the attack. The Israeli Prime Minister, Benjamin Netanyahu, has rejected a ceasefire call, saying that Israel will not surrender to Hamas or to terrorism. In response, Hamas has released a prisoner-confession video in which three Israeli women are held captive. The release of the women comes as the Israeli army threatens the family of the Gaza correspondent of El Jazeera, Yumna El Sayed.',NULL,NULL),(68132,38669,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/01/NOSFERATU! - November 1, 2023 at 01:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-01 01:00:00',86638720,'2023-11-14 08:16:00',NULL,'This program is a continuation of the program that was originally aired on CFRU 91.3. The show opens with a message from a man named Bahamudah, who is a deaf man. His name is Pops, and he is the host of the Morning Soul-Shake-Up. He asks his son how he is feeling, and Pops answers that he is fine.\n\nBefore he can continue, however, he is interrupted by an urgent message from Canada. The message is from Mad Canada, and it is from the Ad Council and the Pivotal Ventures, who are supporting Sounded Out, a national campaign to raise awareness of the dangers of impaired boating. The program ends with a reminder that the Alzheimer\'s society of Waterloo Wellington has a music project to help people with dementia. They need volunteers to help set up an iPod, play music, and create playlists. The project is free of charge and provides a personalized playlist for people living with the disease. The organization is also looking for people who want to donate money, iPods, or gift cards.',NULL,NULL),(68159,180,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/5pa2jd/HOWL_-_OCTOBER_31_2023a7xg1.mp3','2023-11-01 12:22:59',56689813,'2023-11-14 08:06:35',NULL,'This is the first episode of the new music show on Hal 895. It is called \"The Halloween Open Mic\" and it is hosted by the man who hosts the show, a musician named \"Valentino Assenza.\" He is a musician who lives on Turtle Island, an island off the coast of Nova Scotia in Canada. He is known for playing music that is both \"adult\" and \"sexy.\" He plays music that has a \"Tokata Fugue\" or \"Gothic\" vibe, which means \"Gothic.\" He also plays music with a Latin vibe, such as the \"Toka Fugue.\n\n\" He explains that he is a fan of horror movies, and this is a good time of year to re-watch them. He also says that the open mics that he hosts are not as popular as they once were. He received seven submissions for the open mic, and only seven people responded to his open mic. He wants to make sure that the next open mic is a success, so he\'s going to put on another open mic in November. He\'ll be holding it from 10pm to 11pm on November 28, 2023. There will be 17 minutes of submissions for that open mic and he wants',NULL,NULL),(68162,80,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/01/CFRU Playlist - November 1, 2023 at 07:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-01 07:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-01 14:06:12',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(68163,78,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/01/Morning Soul Shake-Up! - November 1, 2023 at 08:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-01 08:00:00',86638720,'2023-11-14 07:51:58',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(68165,159,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/mzw2at/CAREER_-_CareerBuzzCIUTfinalnovember120236hvpn.mp3','2023-11-01 15:30:00',85474859,'2023-11-14 07:42:15',NULL,'On today\'s program, Hoda introduces her guests, Joe Iuiby and Dave Crumby. In the first half of the program, Joe shares valuable information about the 360-degree, and in the second half, Dave shares valuable insights on the reasons employers are using it.\n\nJoe is Chief Executive Officer and Co-Founder of Track Surveys. He works with clients to create a culture of feedback in the workplace. He has worked as a Learning and Development Director at Ernst & Young, as well as as as a Director at Fujitsu and a Learning Director at Saudi Telecom. He is also the author of a guide to success with 360 degree feedback. Joe divides his time between London, Dublin and working with clients in the Middle East, London and Woodhouse College. Joe shares his definition of a career term, and he and Hoda discuss the importance of having good work conversations.',NULL,NULL),(68166,174,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/mpv72s/November_1_2023_Global_Rhythms6aube.mp3','2023-11-01 14:05:01',431961989,'2023-11-17 09:28:25',NULL,'Ken Stauer welcomes listeners to his program on CIUT 89.5. The program opens with Stolen Moments, a song from Anushka Shankar\'s new release Chapter One Forever For Now. It is followed by The Gentle Good from Kamini Netarjan, the compositionji, and the song The Darkening. The songs follow from Wales,The Gentle Good,The Darkening, and The Long Long Rather For Light. Outta Sync is the track followed from the new release by Holly Cook.',NULL,NULL),(68175,280,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/drs9gq/Ep86_India_and_Myanmar8mjte.mp3','2023-11-01 15:12:30',84333979,'2023-11-14 07:28:16',NULL,'This is the second part of a two-part interview with Seth Martosh, a student at the University of Toronto who studies physics. The first part of the interview is with Truxell, the host of the university\'s popular radio show, Tracks From Abroad.\n\nThe second part is with Seth, who explains that the show is a way for students to travel and learn about different countries around the world. He tells us that today\'s show will be a packed show. He introduces us to Harman, an Indian student who has moved to Canada to study at the university. The show also introduces Brian Dickey, a photographer who went to Myanmar to document the revolution in the country. Then the show shifts to the topic of Seth\'s thesis, which is studying the relationship between physics and chemistry.\n\nHe explains that he studied physics in high school and he had a good teacher who motivated him to study. He says that he hated chemistry because he had bad teachers. He\'s now working on the connection between the two sciences. He wants to use electrons as a way to study proteins, and he\'s working on a new class of bacteria that\'s called mass stars.',NULL,NULL),(68176,99,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/01/The Stillness & The Dancing - November 1, 2023 at 10:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-01 10:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-07 14:34:11',NULL,'The Stillness And The Dancing is an hour long program, and it starts off with John Swank, who is a music journalist, talking about some of his favorite albums. He starts with Soundings and Fathoms, which is a collection of tracks from various artists, including Bodov Songs , Attic Reverb , and Stench Of Exist . The next release is Arrow Wounds\'s \"The Slow-Boiling-Amphibian-Dream-State,\" which is the first part of a four part album series. The second release is Hiss Tracks , whose album is called Shortwave Nights , which captures all of Godspeed\'s noisy side. The third release is Stad , an EP by a flank named Deruntin , followed by Jackson Payne\'s Leisure Time Explosion , a track from the game Mist . And the fourth release is a release by Towers , called Towers 3 .',NULL,'The Stillness And The Dancing (Sponsor), Episode 3 (Twitter Thread)'),(68177,99,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/01/The Stillness & The Dancing - November 1, 2023 at 09:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-01 09:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-07 14:24:50',NULL,'The Stillness and The Dancing opens with a spooky mix of music. It\'s a Halloween edition, which means that the show is going to be a little more sinister. The show\'s narrator explains that he\'s been living in the city during the week and is undergoing treatment for his brain tumor. He\'s grateful that he has some fresh music to share with the listeners. The first track is a new release from the band Grotto Veritano, called \"Endless Vacation.\" The second track is \"If only you knew what you claimed to.\" The third track is from Richard Skelton, \"The Inward Circle.\" The fourth track is called \"The Stillness in dancing here on CFR 93.3 . . and the localFM die all over th world through the streaming services.\" The last track is new music from Inward Circles. The narrator says that this track captures \"something kind of haunting, melodic for me.\"',NULL,'The Stillness and The Dancing (Sponsor), a Halloween spooky mix of new music '),(68187,100,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/01/We Know Some Stuff + CFRU playlist - November 1, 2023 at 12:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-01 12:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-14 07:15:53',NULL,'The first guest on the show is a guy named Serge, who is a student at Laurentian College. He\'s a master\'s student in electrochemistry at the university. Serge started his studies in science because he wanted to study water and how it\'s used. He wanted to work on wastewater treatment.\n\nAs he was making his way through his program, he decided to focus on microplastics. He decided to go back to school to do his masters. He went to the university to study hydroponics. Here\'s what he\'s doing: he\'ll use electrochemistry to treat hydroponics, which is basically a water-growing system. He uses electrodes to do things like chlorination, which kills microorganisms, and hydroxyl radicals, which are short-lived chemicals that kill off certain kinds of microorganisms. He also uses fluoroalkyl substances, which aren\'t as good for killing off microorganisms as fluoroquinolones, to protect hydroponics from certain types of pathogens.',NULL,NULL),(68188,1437,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/01/Democracy Now - November 1, 2023 at 11:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-01 11:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-14 07:00:57',NULL,'On this edition of Democracy Now!, Amy Goodman takes us to the Besiege Territory, where we\'ll hear from a former resident of the city of Jabalia, a humanitarian advocate, and a long-time human rights attorney. Amy also talks with Craig McIvers, a former United Nations official who\'s now an attorney in New York. This is part one of a two-part program on the war and peace in the Middle East. The first part of the program is about the humanitarian situation in the besieged city of Gaza.\n\nIn the last segment, we heard about the latest developments in the war in the Gaza. Israel has struck the densely packed Jabalia Refugee Camp again, killing 50 people and injuring 150. The doctor who treated the victims of the attack at an Indonesian hospital tells us that hundreds of people have been injured, including hundreds of martyrs and children. The doctors say there\'s no way to treat them all. The only thing they can do is try to help them. The World Heath Organization warns of a public health crisis in Gaza. An engineer with Al-Jazeera\'s Gaza Bureau has lost 19 family members in the attack. Meanwhile, a deal has been reached between Qatar and Egypt to',NULL,NULL),(68191,155,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/nz33ki/DrMouth_CIUTshow_oct31_2023_fullshow.mp3','2023-11-01 19:47:30',431485568,'2023-11-14 00:57:13',NULL,'The gang gets down to business. They\'re talking about the various songs they\'re going to hear on the three-hour Halloween extravaganza. They start off by talking about how scary it is to be a rock \'n\' roll fan. They get down to the songs by the Ramones, the Ramones cover of Pet Cemetery, the Green Goblin in the animated version of Spider-Man, and Dr. Curse. Then they go on to talk about Dr. Frankenstein\'s monster, which they think will be a good idea. The gang also talks about the upcoming shows by the guys from the band called Dark Clouds. The guys will be playing three shows in Hamilton, Waterloo, and on the fourth, they\'ll be playing at a dive bar in Waterloo',NULL,NULL),(68200,3686,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/01/Volunteer Playlist - November 1, 2023 at 14:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-01 14:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-14 00:41:59',NULL,'I can make... I can do it... I\'ll do it. And I can tell you that you\'re going to find your way, too. \"I can make it,\" says Dr. Rivers. \"It\'s just a matter of