3-11-02 01:57:28',NULL,'We start this program with an interview with Doug Blackwith, host of the old time music program \"Sounds Like Old Times\" on CFRU 92.3. He tells us that he\'s been entertaining listeners with old songs and stories since the early 1900s. He\'s hosting a show on the 4th of November at the Al Green Theatre, a venue accessible to people with physical limitations. The show will be a benefit for the War Amputees, who need artificial limbs and equipment to live with amputation. If you\'re a war amputee and you want to help, visit waramps.ca. The song opens with a poem called \"The Story is Ours.\" It\'s about a man named \"Patient\" who is a patient in a war hospital. \"Patient,\" the song says, \"do you touch the sun. Do you realize sun. show my light. make the world my sun. Still light as soonas we agree Patient.\" The song ends with a quote from the poem \"The sun is near you. It\'ll not always be there on the opposite side.\"',NULL,'\'Sounds Like Old Times\': \'Do you touch the sun. Do you realize sun\''),(68222,105,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/01/B Siide Radio - November 1, 2023 at 19:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-01 19:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-02 03:27:42',NULL,'Stash Ram is back in the States. He\'s back to robbing. He has a new plan: he\'s going to start a new gang of robbers. This time, he\'ll be back to \"live like an orphan\" . He doesn\'t want to live like a homeless man. He is going to hit the road with a shotgun, and he can\'t even run with it. So, he needs to figure out a way to keep people on their toes. Stash Ram points out that the \"cats that be hating\" still love the dogs, even though they know that they\'re doomed to die by the law. He tells them that he got them all on the same team: \"you got money keep yours\" , and since Stash Ram took the governor\'s job, \"even the cats that are hating\" are still loving the dogs. He explains that he likes to use a watch as a weapon and a gun as a way of killing people. He compares his methods to the \"riots\" in a jailhouse. He buys an extra 20 bucks with the money, which he then uses to buy some drugs. He says that he can kill anyone he wants, even cats',NULL,'Stash Ram is back in the States and is going to start a new gang of robbers'),(68223,106,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/01/Trail Mix - November 1, 2023 at 20:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-01 20:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-02 03:16:24',NULL,'The Underground Man returns with a new song from a band called Thresh. The song is called \"Closing on a minor client\" and it opens with the words, \"True love is easy. It\'s easy to know it\'s true in the end. True love is the only thing that matters in the world. It is easy in the classic. I\'m just an alien horse power like an Mongolian trying to find soul. I can\'t complain though, as I am only an alien power trying to search soul again. The Underground Men also play a new track from Micaiah Mc-Raven\'s new album \"In These Times\" and a song from Panisaurus\'s \"Market Street Junkie\" from his new album.',NULL,'The Underground Man returns with a new song from a band called Thresh'),(68224,1321,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/01/Hong Kong Student Radio Association - November 1, 2023 at 18:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-01 18:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-13 11:23:50',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Hong Kong Student Association Various From the Roots Up CIUT 89.4 CFRU archives'),(68234,107,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/01/Tone Zone - November 1, 2023 at 21:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-01 21:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-02 04:38:49',NULL,'The show starts off with a rendition of one of Nirvana\'s most famous songs, \"In utero Scentless Apprentice,\" which was released in September of 1994 and is a live version. The show also includes a number of other songs from the band\'s career, including \"Pink Flag,\" \"Wire and mannequin,\" and \"The go-between\'s\" and \"Bachelor kisses.\" The show closes with a song from a band called \"Ducks limited,