ays music from La Paz. The songs they play are Charanguita, Chajhuanto, El Pototheto, Contregiadad, and Cyrina del Tambien. The band also has a song called Nino and Yocente. The narrator tells us that the band will be raising money to keep the program going every Saturday morning at 10 to 11 so that they can keep up with the latest developments in the music world.',NULL,NULL),(68354,120,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/02/The Crooked Beat - November 2, 2023 at 20:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-02 20:00:00',86638720,'2023-11-13 16:59:49',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(68355,120,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/02/The Crooked Beat - November 2, 2023 at 19:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-02 19:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-13 16:53:46',NULL,'This week\'s edition of The Crooked Beat features a bunch of new releases, including tracks from Escape Roots from Scotland, the Human Rights album Reggae Strong from Freddie McGregor, and new tracks from G-Potato Ranks, Jimmy Cliff, and Bishob. The band also includes Susan Kudogan, who\'s a regular on the show. She\'s also the host of the show, and she\'s got a list of artists she\'d like to hear on the next show. The list includes: BISHOB, Meta, and The Cornerstones from Brooklyn, the KRS-Ones from New York, and a remix from Bobby Brown.',NULL,NULL),(68365,122,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/02/Forever Deaf - November 2, 2023 at 22:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-02 22:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-13 16:41:53',NULL,'The show introduces its first host, Dean, who tells the audience that he\'s got an hour plus he got midnight and he got one hour. He finishes playing some songs for the show, which includes Doria, Atria, Artach, and Dysmorphia. He also announces that a Halloween party is coming up at Red Papaya, and he\'ll be there. Then he announces a concert for November 11th. He announces that Boffold, a band from Toronto, will be playing there. He says that the band used to perform in front of the city hall, but they were banned from