ming together for a big tour in the fall. The next track is from a band called Demon Hunter, who was killed in battle.',NULL,NULL),(68387,122,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/03/Forever Deaf - November 3, 2023 at 01:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-03 01:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-13 16:25:28',NULL,'So, here\'s what we\'ve got for you: music from the new albums Outside the Spiral, Cold Red, A Celebration I , Live in America , King Gizzard & the Lizard Wizard , and A Merciless Nation . And then some new music from a new band called Z-u-l-u. The band\'s name is Annelie Lee and they\'ve been together for a while. Annelie is a multi-instrumentalist and vocalist who\'s been making music since she was a teenager. Her band is called Zulu and they have a new album called I Do Tomorrow coming out soon. And they\'re going to play a bunch of new music. This isn\'t the music that we used to hear from this program, but it\'s cool.',NULL,NULL),(68416,78,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/03/Morning Soul Shake-Up! - November 3, 2023 at 08:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-03 08:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-13 16:24:05',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(68426,124,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/03/Planet Groove - November 3, 2023 at 10:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-03 10:00:00',86638720,'2023-11-13 15:44:46',NULL,'The show starts off with a description of the genre of music they\'re going to play. It\'s called \"Planet Groove of Your Funky Blues Doctor\" and it\'s about to get really interesting. The first show is going to be all about the \"Jurassic Park\" of music, but then the second show is all about \"Danger Sex Boss\" and \"Narusisa featuring BasilSilver and StephGoyer andMotorhead\" and the third show is about \"I\'ll be your sister baby from Overkill\" . The second show sounds like a mix of all of the same music, except you\'re singing along instead of playing along. The third show has \"Breeeeb Thunder Bay\" , and the fourth show is \"BeachBoys Long Promise Road\" ; the fifth show is called \"Kingdom Come\" and is about the band Robbie Robertson recently passed away from the band. The sixth show is a little more about the music, and this one is all \"Master versus Apprentice\" : people gotta move, triumph, and never surrender. The music ends with a shout out to Ed Video, the Guelph-based arts and culture hub. Get started, or advance your skills, with a year',NULL,NULL),(68427,123,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/03/Thanks for Listening :) - November 3, 2023 at 09:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-03 09:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-13 15:33:10',NULL,'This is a special edition of the show where the guest introduces himself as \"Megan\" and explains that she will be with the hosts until the end of their show. She plays music and gives thanks for listening. They play music from the program and then she goes to her room to record. She tells us that she is a big fan of the bands Plague and Long Way Down and she remembers when she was younger and she was obsessed with them.',NULL,NULL),(68433,175,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/2eyrcj/November_2nd_2023_No_Man_s_Land70d29.mp3','2023-11-03 17:53:25',287962512,'2023-11-13 16:24:17',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(68438,186,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/ig5ezh/November_2nd_2023_Higher_Ground69fin.mp3','2023-11-03 17:58:59',287962512,'2023-11-13 15:13:54',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(68439,1437,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/03/Democracy Now - November 3, 2023 at 11:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-03 11:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-13 15:04:10',NULL,'Meanwhile, the United States is spending money to defend Israel from Hamas\'s attacks. The House has passed a $14.3 bill to fund Israel\'s war effort. The Senate has approved a $106 bill to support Israel, Taiwan, and Ukraine. In the Middle East, the White House continues its refusal to allow a ceasefire in the fighting in Gaza. The vice president says the US will not create any conditions for the sale of weapons to Israel',NULL,NULL),(68440,3686,'https://archive.cfru.ca