nts to remind everyone that this show has been posted on the Halloweenspot, CarolB on the',NULL,NULL),(68474,127,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/03/LiYghTE FM - November 3, 2023 at 16:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-03 16:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-13 13:07:40',NULL,'The DJ double-d character, who is also the host of the light FM station at the University of California, Los Angeles, begins this program by stating that the guy who works at the grocery store has no views and that he has heard that he is distant from his family and friends. He also says that he heard the guy is trying to change light FM from being the home of only 222% more hits to being home for the \"love revolution\" and that this is all part of the reason why he is so passionate about music. He goes on to say that every hour of light-FM is perfectly curated to roast chestnuts and every turn of the pan is perfectly timed to get the perfect temperature. The DJ says that his listeners already know these things. He says that light-fm used to be more budget and more producers exploring abroad, but that was the good side of everything. He then points out that nobody has ever defined the term \"light hit,\" and when they say \"light-hit\" it is also \"ill defined\" and \"undefinable. It is undefinable. He adds that a lot of the pop songs he listens to have a \"truly wild\" chorus. He further says that if listeners really listened to',NULL,NULL),(68475,128,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/03/Walkuman Style - November 3, 2023 at 18:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-03 18:00:00',86638720,'2023-11-13 03:30:11',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(68476,135,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/03/Folk Roots Radio - November 3, 2023 at 17:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-03 17:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-13 03:23:59',NULL,'The show starts off with Helen Austin, a singer from Vancouver Island, and Paul Oten, a musician from Ohio, discussing their latest project, \"AMPM,\" a concept album. They talk about the project and its 