hear some new stuff. We\'ve heard a song by Choo Yan from the Panda Records album out of Singapore, and we\'ve also heard a new track from Black Classical Noise from Yousuf Day. And then we\'ll finish off the hour with a track from the Pharoah Sanders album, \"Pharahoah on India Navigation\" .','',NULL),(68500,1491,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/03/Industry Tactics - November 3, 2023 at 22:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-03 22:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-13 02:22:03',NULL,'This is the first episode of the \"Industry Tactics\" podcast, and it\'s recorded in early 2022. It\'s a conversation between host Friendly Rich and Sebastian Corri, a musician who has been dubbed \"Corino\" by the press. In this conversation, Friendly Rich describes his first meeting with Sebastian, who is the leader of a Canadian political party called the \"Rhinoceros Party.\" In this interview, he describes Sebastian as a \"great ambassador of weird\" and says that he\'s grown to respect Sebastian\'s work. Sebastian is also psyched about his upcoming Carbon Dioxide test, which he\'ll perform live with Maladita, the girl he met in the bar when he first came to Montreal. The two also discuss Sebastian and his first time meeting Friendly Rich, which was at a bar in Montreal. Sebastian says that, at the time, the people at the bar called him by his stage name, but he doesn\'t speak English very well, so they just called him Corino. It turns out that the people in Montreal called him \"Sebastian Corri,\" but they didn\'t know what to say in English, so he calls himself \"Sebastian Corino.\" Friendly Rich says that Sebastian is a \"beautiful',NULL,NULL),(68510,1491,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/03/Industry Tactics - November 3, 2023 at 23:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-03 23:00:00',86638720,'2023-11-13 02:11:47',NULL,'This is a really funny, funny, and depressing episode. It starts off with a guy named Sebastian Corino who\'s a big fan of the Canadian liberal party and a big supporter of socialism. He\'s also a big advocate of the idea of the free market. The guy\'s going on a tour in May and he\'s got a bunch of songs that he\'d like to play for the listeners. He also has some really funny political points about how he\'ll be very active in politics in the future. He wants to be active for democracy and not for socialism. We\'re going to turn this thing upside down and get into the 2025 elections. The next show is going to be a concert. It will be a totally different kind of music than what you\'ve come to expect from the CFR. There\'s no reason to miss this one. You can also lose. And that\'s the way it is.',NULL,NULL),(68511,1627,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/04/Jitterbuggin - November 4, 2023 at 00:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-04 00:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-13 02:01:37',NULL,'This is a weird show, says Adrian, because it is not actually a Friday night show. It is actually a mid-week show, which means that he is in his home studio in Mississauga. He says that he\'s going to cut the music off as he goes. He\'s not going to be on the air as usual, but he\'ll try to come on as often as he can. He invites listeners to tune in as he does a little dance routine. He tells the listeners that he sets his time as midnight, not midnight where he is, because he is so up. He plays three different tracks, one each from a Canadian band and a soul gospel group. He also plays a triple header, meaning he plays three songs back-to-back. This means that no matter what time of day it is, he can play music. He adds that he has three tracks for each person, so they can listen to him while he does his thing.',NULL,NULL),(68549,1551,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/ycb6k3/NOVEMBER2ND2023.mp3','2023-11-04 17:42:17',431961989,'2023-11-13 01:47:28',NULL,'In this week\'s show, David introduces the listeners to some new music from Roth Antic, which is based in Toronto. He also introduces Dim Kelly, a special guest DJ, who has a new EP called Pianoology, and he will also be playing tracks from that EP. Also on the docket for this week is a new album from Hercules, an album from Love Affair, and a new release from Vanity. The show closes with a mix from one of David\'s favorite producers, the Italian singer and songwriter, Dino Lenny.',NULL,NULL),(68550,136,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/04/A Dog’s Breakfast - November 4, 2023 at 10:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-04 10:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-13 01:36:31',NULL,'The group begins with a description of the music they are going to listen to. They are all going to be based in Toronto, and they are all singing Turkish. They have heard a lot of music at a dog\'d-breakfast, but this is the first time they\'ve heard something totally different. They\'re also going to hear a bunch of different kinds of music, but they\'re all coming from different parts of the world. They go from a Toronto based band called Minor Empire singing in Turkish, to a Vancouver based group called Pacifica singing in English, to another group called Rebetica singing in Greek. They also go to a Montreal based band named Land of Kush singing in Arabic, and a Toronto-based band named Sultans of String singing in Latin. The group ends with a music video for a snake. It\'s a nod to snakes, which isn\'t as common as spiders in the world , but it\'s still a good thing, and the group is going to go see it.',NULL,NULL),(68551,139,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/04/Bel Araby with CAWA - November 4, 2023 at 15:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-04 15:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-13 01:23:29',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(68552,138,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/04/Sound Magic - November 4, 2023 at 14:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-04 14:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-13 01:17:13',NULL,'The program opens with a piece by a contemporary Czech composer, Victor Kalabis. He lived from 1922 to 2006. He married a harpsichordist, Susanna Ruzicakova, and he worked as a conductor and a producer for the state-run Czech Radio. The composer\'s opus 42 is a work for four movements. It is the work he wrote for his wife. He is aware of the influences of the composer, Bohuslavu, and has arranged for the composer to have Susanna perform it. The program concludes with a program of music from the late 20th century by another contemporary composer. This is the harpsichord concerto by Victor Kalabus. He lives until the late century, but unfortunately his health stops him from composing. The harpsichord concerto and his wife are played by the composer and the orchestra is also played. The music ends with a farewell program from Michael Dallashell. He says goodbye to his listeners and goes to work for another station.',NULL,NULL),(68553,140,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/04/Caribbean Anthology - November 4, 2023 at 16:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-04 16:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-13 01:07:31',NULL,'The show starts off with an introduction to the music and then moves into the dance hall. Then it moves to the soca section and then back to the chart music section. The show was originally started by a guy named John Leacock who was a student at the university and a promoter. He used to have a CD collection of soca music that he would bring to the university for people to listen to. Leacock moved to real estate and decided to revive the music. He brought it back to live on the university station. Since that time, the show has been going strong.',NULL,NULL),(68554,138,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/04/Sound Magic - November 4, 2023 at 13:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-04 13:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-13 00:58:34',NULL,'In this program, the UM continues his discussion of the music of Czech composer and friend of Vlst and Sukh, Joseph Vershteh. He relates that Verstuh wrote five symphonies, the fourth of which will be collected in a new edition in springtime. He also discusses the works of another friend of Sukh\'s, Vcevitslav Novak, a composer who has not had much success in the West. The UM also plays two pieces that he has never played before, the South Bohemian Suite and a tone poem.',NULL,NULL),(68555,138,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/04/Sound Magic - November 4, 2023 at 12:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-04 12:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-13 00:49:14',NULL,'Sound Magic is the program of classical music concerts presented on the campus of the City University of New York. The program for this week\'s concert is a program of Czech music. This week\' composer is Josef Sukh, who was Dvorak\'s late son-in law and a major voice in the early 20th century. He is also known for his giant tom poem cycle, which he performed. The composer\'s Opus 25 is a fantasy piece. There is also a recording from the Buffalo Orchestra, conducted by Joanne Falera. The two orchestras are playing the fantasy piece on the Buffalo Philharmonic\'s recent album. The second program on the program is a Czech program. It is the time for the symphony at the later part of the program. This is a work by Paul Wernits, a composer who was famous in Vienna during Beethoven\'s time. He was well-respected. The symphony is published in 1797. It has four movements, an allegorymalto, adagio , a slow adogio, and then a vivace. The chamber orchestra of Patte Du Bice is conducting this symphony. It was the height of the classical style at the end.',NULL,NULL),(68556,1344,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/04/Beautiful Druid - November 4, 2023 at 09:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-04 09:00:00',86638720,'2023-11-13 00:37:56',NULL,'In this short program, Alden Hadwen, the host of Beautiful Druid, introduces himself and introduces the program. He explains that the program will be a half-hour program, in which he will play songs and read poetry at the same time. He says that he will try and tell the audience who wrote the song, and that many of the songs will be performed by people who did not write the song but who appreciate it. The theme of the program is \"uplifting songs,\" and he starts by playing a song by Jesse Winchester called Doulalé. He dedicates the song to Doulalé\'s \"wonderful listener,\" whom he calls \"Doulalé.\" After this, he plays a steel drum band called \"Steel Drum Beach Party.\" He then plays a song called \"The Secret of Life,\" which was written by a woman named Gretchen Peters. After that he plays \"All That Is,\" a song written by Garnet Rogers. Then he plays another song by Holly Cole, \"I Can See Clearly,\" which she sings with a trio. He also plays George Strait\'s song, \"In the Air Again,\" which he recorded in 1999.',NULL,NULL),(68566,141,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/04/Alternativa Latinoamericana - November 4, 2023 at 18:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-04 18:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-05 00:07:08',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(68567,140,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/04/Caribbean Anthology - November 4, 2023 at 17:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-04 17:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-13 00:24:44',NULL,'The Underground Man explains that he is trying to keep the whole thing going, but that he also wants people to be aware that they are not alone and that they can find help if they need it. He says that there is no way to do it and that it is very difficult, but he urges people to get together and find out what they can do to help themselves.',NULL,NULL),(68569,171,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/hdzg6a/phil_s_inn_nov_4_237i2lv.mp3','2023-11-05 00:32:05',287962512,'2023-11-13 00:15:33',NULL,'The group goes to the fall fair, where they listen to a variety of different acts. The first act is the band Luther Dickinson and his band the Collaborators, who perform an old spiritual song called \"Bula Land\" which is a metaphor for \"heaven.\" The second act is Alison Russell and her band the All Stars, the Black Crows, who play a song originally written by Billy J Kramer called \"Dakotas, Trains, and Planes.\" The third act is The Box Tops from Memphis, TN who perform a song by Billy Chilton called \"The Box Tops.\"',NULL,NULL),(68578,197,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/jie9ht/phil_s_inn_nov_4_23723co.mp3','2023-11-05 00:48:51',287962512,'2023-11-13 00:02:28',NULL,'In a rare interview, a Boston-based musician opens up about his travels and the music he has been listening to. He tells how he loves New England and how he came to be in the audience at a fall fair in Hamilton, Ontario. He explains that he is in the middle of a conversation with a Canadian company when he hears the music of Luther Dickinson and Allison Russell. They are both playing an old spiritual song called \"Bula Land,\" which is a metaphor of heaven. The song was originally written by Billy J, who performed it in the Dakota Mountains. The two artists perform the song together.',NULL,NULL),(68579,141,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/04/Alternativa Latinoamericana - November 4, 2023 at 19:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-04 19:00:00',0,'2023-11-05 02:07:20',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(68652,142,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/04/Tiempo de Mujeres - November 4, 2023 at 20:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-04 20:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-05 19:07:13',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(68653,143,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/04/Mach Vibe Radio - November 4, 2023 at 22:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-04 22:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-12 23:50:12',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(68654,143,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/04/Mach Vibe Radio - November 4, 2023 at 21:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-04 21:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-12 23:42:55',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(68655,145,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/05/Visions fugitives - November 5, 2023 at 09:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-05 09:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-12 23:34:35',NULL,'The show is called \"Git\'in\' Jean Fujitiv\" and it\'s hosted by Christopher Curry and Fangwei. Each week, Fangwei and Curry co-host a show. This week, the show is titled \"The Serpent-Fire,\" and it is inspired by the story of the serpent in the Bible, which tempts Eve to eat forbidden fruit. It\'s a work that doesn\'t quite go well with the story, but that\'s OK because the serpent is better than the apple in the story. So, this week, Curry wants to play a piece called \"Opus 13,\" which is a number associated with unlucky numbers. The reason for the unlucky number is that there are 13 people in the Last Supper, and one of them was a traitor, so the unlucky thing is that the number 13 is associated with bad luck. But, the good news is that Sunday is \"Sunday the 13th\" of November, which means that it\'ll just be a bunch of people who are Triska decafies. If you want to play your own piece of music, you can do so. But this is not a work of yours, says Curry, because he\'s not breaking',NULL,NULL),(68656,145,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/05/Visions fugitives - November 5, 2023 at 08:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-05 08:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-12 23:24:01',NULL,'The Christopher Curry and Fangwei co-host a music show called \"Visions of Fugitives.\" It\'s a sort of music-as-codicil show, where one of the co-hosts plays a piece and the other plays another piece. One week they\'ll play a bunch of music and the next week they can respond to the first piece they heard with their own selections. The show is sort of like a game of Who\'s Who in the music world. The two of them pick a song cycle and then they play the song that they heard the week before. The song cycle is called \"United Fruit Company.\" It was written by a Greek composer named Mikis Teodolians. It was one of many pieces written by Neruda that were set to music during the period of military rule in Greece from 1967 to 1974.',NULL,NULL),(68657,146,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/05/The Kookoo Bananas Variety Hour - November 5, 2023 at 10:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-05 10:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-08 14:17:16',NULL,'We start off this new episode with a song about robots. It\'s called \"Computers! Robots have Computers inside them basically two different things though.\" The first song is from Disney World. It was written by a group called the Sherman Brothers. They wrote songs for all the Disney theme parks. The song is called \"Everything Is Awesome\" and it\'s one of the most popular songs of all time. The second song that we\'re going to hear is a song by a guy called \"Jerry Paper\" . The guy\'s got a song called \"Fuzzy Logic\" , which is about being able to create something in the world that isn\'t just a yes or no. The world is like this. The cover of Jerry Paper\'s album is awesome. We\'ll start this song off with \"Lampan Fuzzy Logic,\" which sounds like a talking robot. It sounds like the voice of a German-speaking robot. Jerry Paper has a song for the kids called \"Jingles,\" which is also about a robot. The idea of a robot taking over the whole world is so awesome that it was actually the first song on the radio. It came from a game called \"Um Jamma Lamm','Rowan shares his favorite songs from Disney World, the Jungle Book, and a video game. Rowan also shares a song about how computers will take over the world. The song is called Fuzzy Logic and was written by the Sherman Brothers who also wrote songs for Disney.','The Magician’s Favorite Songs From Disney World, the Jungle Book, and Video Games '),(68658,144,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/05/The Underground - November 5, 2023 at 01:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-05 01:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-12 22:14:07',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(68659,144,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/05/The Underground - November 5, 2023 at 00:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-05 00:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-12 22:04:49',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(68660,144,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/04/The Underground - November 4, 2023 at 23:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-04 23:00:00',86638720,'2023-11-12 21:55:19',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(68661,148,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/05/Clan Na Gael - November 5, 2023 at 12:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-05 12:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-12 23:11:04',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(68671,101,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/05/Seems Like Old Times - November 5, 2023 at 14:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-05 14:00:00',86638720,'2023-11-12 21:34:06',NULL,'We start off with a little bit of a program summary, and it\'s going to be a big ol\' ol\' time bomb. The program starts with a guest speaker and music. The guest speaker is a singer named Holly Cole. She\'s got a song called \"My Foolish Heart\" with her band. And the song is about love. And, as usual, the guest speaker\'s name is Clifton Joseph. Clifton says that campus community radio stations are beacons all over the country, and they\'re essential in these days. He says that if it weren\'t for them, his band would be way less known. But campus community stations are the ones that really push dub poetry, and so many more things out there. And Clifton says he wishes he were a part of it. Clifton also says that he\'s glad to see that Holly is coming back to the River Run Center, because she\'s a big hit with the audience. Clifton then talks about all the other Remembrance Day events going on in the city. The Allura Legion is organizing a service in Salem at the Senate at 930, the Fergus Legion is planning one in Fergus, and the optimists are holding a service at Puss',NULL,NULL),(68672,148,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/05/Clan Na Gael - November 5, 2023 at 13:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-05 13:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-12 21:19:32',NULL,'On this program, the musician talks about his band, Spelled DIY, and how they are able to help people get started on their projects. The first song he plays is called \"The Celts,\" which is a song about the people of the Celts. He then talks about the rest of the program, which is sort of a remembrance day, but also a celebration of the many wars that have been fought in the Celtic lands. He also talks about a song called \"High Germany\" which is about the Germans in the German army during the Second World War. Then he talks about \"Ganymede Rogers,\" a Canadian legend, and \"11 11,\" a song he heard in the French army',NULL,NULL),(68682,101,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/05/Seems Like Old Times - November 5, 2023 at 15:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-05 15:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-12 21:02:44',NULL,'The kids begin their lessons with roll call, which is like a quiz. They\'re named Richard, Tommy, Harvey, Patrick, and Stockley. Richard is a sophomore at Roosevelt School, and he\'s joined by Tommy, a 12 year old; Harvey is a freshman at South Shore High; and Patrick is a 7 year old. Stockley is a 10 year old student at Resurrection School and he and his classmates are called Quiz Kids. The kids are asked to guess which branch of the Navy Virginia Connolly is in, and they\'re told she\'s a nurse at the Navy hospital on Mare Island in San Francisco. They also learn that a presidential candidate was kept up to date on the election, and that a president who was sworn into office in the middle of his term was actually sworn in after he died or was assassinated.',NULL,NULL),(68683,149,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/05/La Buena Onda - November 5, 2023 at 16:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-05 16:00:00',86638720,'2023-11-05 23:07:07',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(68693,149,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/05/La Buena Onda - November 5, 2023 at 17:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-05 17:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-06 01:07:22',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(68694,150,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/05/Zombie Jamboree - November 5, 2023 at 18:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-05 18:00:00',86638720,'2023-11-12 20:44:31',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(68704,196,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/yhgawg/November_5_2023_Across_the_Universe6wl3k.mp3','2023-11-06 01:07:48',431961989,'2023-11-12 20:32:31',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(68705,108,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/05/Wind-Down - November 5, 2023 at 20:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-05 20:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-12 20:21:57',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(68706,150,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/05/Zomb