y the Chamber Brothers from 1968. It was a psychedelic soul classic, a civil rights-based psychedelic soul anthem. It was forbidden to play on some radio stations, because it had a lot of \"black uprising theme\" in it. The song has been covered by artists like the Ramones, the Smashing-Pumpkins, Joan-Jett, and Willie-DeVille.',NULL,NULL),(68728,154,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/06/This Night Wounds Time - November 6, 2023 at 00:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-06 00:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-11 21:54:52',NULL,'The show moves on to a second hour of the show in which they\'ll feature music from the geographical spotlight section of the program. This is a first for the program, and it\'s going to be going to a state called Argentina soon. The program\'s narrator describes the situation in Ontario, where only 31% of the population has signed up to donate their body parts if they die. That means that one person dies every three days unless an organ is available to save him or her. If you have the chance to save someone\'s life, you should do it. Go to BeDonAor.ca and sign up to become a life-saving organ donor. That way, you\'ll save up to eight lives and improve the lives of up to 75 others. The narrator says, \"In the words of [heart recipient] Mike Willis, if someone had hadn\'t signed their consent to donation, I wouldn\'t be alive today.\" The program ends with the sound of boiling water. The show is called Wounds Time and the show\'s purpose is to feature artists from different regions of the world. In this program, we\'re going to go through all seven largest countries by area. We\'re','fix',NULL),(68729,154,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/05/This Night Wounds Time - November 5, 2023 at 23:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-05 23:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-11 17:08:05',NULL,'The Host of \"This Night Wounds time\" delivers the latest edition of the \"Geographical Spotlight series\" on his show. He has been covering the largest countries by area and he\'s been doing this for a long time. He says he has been playing music from these locations and he has already covered over multiple years that he have been doing it, the \"different parts of the 7 largest countries on planet.\" Argentina is on the list of countries he is covering. He\'s done a lot of work on this, and he says he finally has a list of the province in descending order. The province of Buenos Aires is not in the list, but it doesn\'t matter because it\'s a province known for producing music.',NULL,NULL),(68739,154,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/06/This Night Wounds Time - November 6, 2023 at 01:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-06 01:00:00',86638720,'2023-11-11 16:52:46',NULL,'This Night Wounded Time is a music-centric program hosted by Christopher Curry. The program is a celebration of music and culture from all over the world. The show also discusses a new project being conducted by the University of Utah to study the experiences of youths and older adults in the Covid pandemic. If you are a youth or an older adult, the UM team would like to hear your story. You can find out more about the study by visiting the UM\'s slash life and covid study or by following the link to the University\'s e-mail list. You\'re listening to the show on CFRU 98.3FM. It\'s all about music. We\'ve got some great music from the San Luis region of Argentina. The UM team is studying how youths and adults respond to disasters and how they shape the world in response to them. The team wants to know how youth and older people experience and influence the world, so they can recommend ways to mitigate future disasters. You might also be interested in hearing more about Sound It Out, a music collective that promotes the use of music in communities around the world by encouraging people to sing, play, and listen together. If your kid is having trouble finding the language',NULL,NULL),(68767,78,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/06/Morning Soul Shake-Up! - November 6, 2023 at 08:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-06 08:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-11 16:36:36',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(68768,110,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/06/Here Today - November 6, 2023 at 07:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-06 07:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-07 04:41:15',NULL,'The show opens with a discussion of David Bowie\'s new single \"Let\'s Go Crazy,\" which is being released on a new pop-culture label. The song is being recorded by a group called Martha Johnson and the Muffins, who have also just released a new album titled \"M.A.T. I.N.I..N.\" This is a personal album for Paul Manchin, who has been writing about his own life for the past 30 years. Manchin says that every project he writes about has the intention of being his last, so he hopes not to. He\'s always been a fan of diversity and he loves people who share his values. The new album is personal to Manchin because it\'s his first in three years. He says that he spent three years trying to make the best music he could, and he\'s super proud of his work. The novel is about transitions through death and illness. He also has Will I get better from the new album after this. Finally, the show closes with the song \"That\'s All\" from the upcoming February album Transients by the Church of Trees, which is also being released.',NULL,'Paul Manchin\'s new memoir \"M.A.T. I.N.I.N.\" (Sponsor)'),(68780,247,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/456s6t/November_4th_2023_Calling_All_Blues9cdec.mp3','2023-11-06 16:32:56',143346496,'2023-11-10 12:29:36',NULL,'The show opens with a tribute to a number of Canadian musicians who have recently died. The first artist is Ahmad Jamal, who died in April at the age of 92. He won the National Endowments for the Arts Master Achievement Lifetime from the Grammys. He was born and raised in Pittsburgh. He studied at the Musicians Union and moved to Chicago. He released more than 60 albums and released dozens of raps samples of his riffs. The second artist is Harry Belafontes, who did a whole of blues called \"Harry Belafonte sings the blues in\". The third artist is Tina Turner, who released three albums.',NULL,'Canadian artist tributes on the upcoming Canadian Music Awards — and a tribute to some of Canada’s most famous musicians '),(68781,79,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/06/Breezy Breakfast Radio - November 6, 2023 at 10:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-06 10:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-09 04:03:14',NULL,'The conversation moves to the budget process and the role of government in making decisions. When the conversation turns to the internet, the councilman argues that the government does not have a right to make decisions about how to pay for things like the internet. He says that he has been discussing this with Phil for many years and that the average citizen does not care about the cost of downloading anything. The councilman says that the province has been hiding behind the idea that it is not their responsibility to make the decision about whether or not to allow the internet to be used. The mayor responds that he understands the tax burden that the city bears, but he believes that the council should not make a decision until it is financially responsible for making the decision. He argues that if the government were to ever make the point of having part-time job positions, the city would have no choice but to cut back on staff. The conversation closes with a discussion of the budget and the importance of understanding the role that it plays in the overall picture of the city\'s budget. The budget comes from a combination of external organizations and the council, and the mayor says that it\'s important for the council to appreciate how important it is to have control over these things.',NULL,'Phil and Phil: What do you think about the city\'s budget? (11 minute read)'),(68782,79,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/06/Breezy Breakfast Radio - November 6, 2023 at 09:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-06 09:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-10 22:03:40',NULL,'Phil discusses the challenges of building a thriving community when the rules are constantly changing. He begins by introducing the guests at the next Breezy Breakfast: Ralph Mezenbritch, chair of the board of education, and Erin Catean, a first-year councillor. He also introduces them to the city\'s relationship with the Atwank and Haudenosaune, two Native American tribes located along the Haldim and Huron Rivers. He says that if the city can move toward reconciliation, it should take the time to do so. He then turns his attention to Ralph, who\'s chairing the board. Ralph has a long career in education, which he got by running for the board by his wife Linda, who is now his counselor. Ralph says that he\'s glad that he got the chance to serve on the board, because education is a huge part of the community in Ontario. He adds that he likes the separation between the two roles of governance and running the school.',NULL,'Phil explains the challenges of building a thriving community in Ontario'),(68784,164,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/t8xgf2/BTHMO111_Nov6BRI_FINALbr8l6.mp3','2023-11-06 17:55:09',66534737,'2023-11-10 12:18:23',NULL,'This week on Beyond the Heads, we take a look at the history of the Belt & Road Initiative, the Chinese initiative to build roads, railways, ports, and other infrastructure in developing countries. In this episode, Dr. Ian Chong-Jai discusses the significance of BRI for China, its impact in the South and Southeast Asian region, and its impact on Africa. Dr. O.Dome discusses the BRIs role in bridge building in Africa, and how it can help bridge the infrastructure gap between Africa and the rest of the world',NULL,'Beyond the Heads: China’s Belt and Road Initiative (27 minute read)'),(68793,206,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/w65wi2/November_4th_2023_The_Minx_Sessions7s4mi.mp3','2023-11-06 17:06:35',287320576,'2023-11-10 12:05:53',NULL,'Binny and the Minx take you through the next few hours of the show. They thank Prophecy for taking them on this journey and also give a shout-out to all the independent artists who have been participating. They\'re also going to be mixing in some Dove techno and some of the best independent music out there. The show will be called \"Binny the minx\" and it\'s going to feature a lot of great independent music. You can check out the show at ciutfm.',NULL,'Binny and the Minx: The Journey of the Independent Music Industry (Sponsor)'),(68794,1438,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/06/Worst Responders - November 6, 2023 at 12:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-06 12:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-10 11:58:14',NULL,'The first thing we learn from this interview is that the guy is really into listening to music. It\'s not necessarily the latest music, but it\'s definitely the most popular music in the world. He\'s also a big Justin Bieber fan, so he has to hide this fact from us. The guy says he likes to play songs that are really popular, but aren\'t necessarily the biggest hits in the music industry. He likes to listen to music that\'s really popular over artists. So, for example, he doesn\'t like Justin Bieber\'s song \"Sorry.\" Instead, he listens to songs by other artists. This is all part of the fun of listening to the guy play music. We learn that he\'s a student at the same university as Carissa and Brittany, and they\'ve both gone to school together. Carissa is from India, and Brittany is from the U.S. This interview is the first time we hear that Carissa has been to college, and that she\'s excited to return to school. We also learn that she has a crush on Justin Bieber, so we get the sense that she wants to be just like him, too. She wants to go to Justin',NULL,'Justin Bieber: The Biggest Music Fan in the World (13 minute read)'),(68795,1437,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/06/Democracy Now - November 6, 2023 at 11:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-06 11:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-10 11:46:05',NULL,'A Rhode Island city councilor has been fired for speaking out in favor of Israel\'s assault on Gaza. Meanwhile, a New York Times writer has resigned after signing a letter condemning Israel. A California port blockade has led to the stopping of a ship bound for Israel, and a San Juan man has climbed a flagpole to replace the U. S. flag with a Palestinian one. An Arab student at Stanford has been hit by a car, and the driver is being investigated for a hate crime',NULL,'A Rhode Island City Councilor Is Fired for Speaking Out in Support of Israel’s Attack on Gaza '),(68805,80,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/06/CFRU Playlist - November 6, 2023 at 14:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-06 14:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-10 11:33:59',NULL,'This week\'s topic is \"that video programming,\" which is all about teaching people how to make movies and other forms of media. It\'s also about how to get started with your own career. If you\'re a musician, you might be interested in learning how to use the latest technology in order to create music. Or you might just want to learn more about making music.',NULL,'That Video Programming 101 (Weekly News Thread), Part 1 (Sponsor)'),(68815,212,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/y3tckv/Soundtracks_-_12_October_20239o34r.mp3','2023-11-06 22:40:08',281550118,'2023-11-10 11:26:27',NULL,'This is the first of many shows that Chris Durand will give on the C-Int. 89.5 FM show. He begins by saying that he still works and that it is too late for him to leave, but he will continue to work. He is referring to the fact that he has not yet moved out of his house and that he does not want to disturb his friends and family by playing music on the wall. He also says that he likes to play music that sounds a bit more muted than his usual music, so that it will sound better when the music is played. He says that if the music sounds better, it is probably because he has moved house and he has very sensitive people living with him. He reasons that if it sounds good, then it is good. If it doesnt, then he will play it better next time, but if it doesnt sound good, he will listen to the music again. It is the most recent B-52s album from the legendary group. The album title track is Funplex. The track is called \"My eyes dont really see\" and \"I am not going listen to you\". It is his mistake to dream of the state, \"It\'s your fault\". It',NULL,'The B-52s Show: Chris Durand explains what he thinks of the state he is in '),(68816,212,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/xsdyag/Soundtracks_-_October_5th_2023_full_6lujg.mp3','2023-11-06 22:38:10',287420372,'2023-11-10 11:14:15',NULL,'This is the second in a three-part series on the Toronto-based DJ, Chris Durand. The first part is devoted to the music of his hometown, and the second part is dedicated to the themes of his show. This show is titled \"Noodle on the Wall,\" and it is a two-hour set that begins with a mix of music and spoken word. The second part of the show is devoted entirely to the theme of \"acoustic background,\" and the third part is all about his upcoming move into his new home. The show will be more like a fresh show, and he will be able to move into a more comfortable space. The final track is a song from his old radio station in Buffalo, New York, that was so well received that it was one of the most played tracks on the station.',NULL,'The New York DJ Reveals His New Home in a New York City Show '),(68817,81,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/06/The Sentinel’s Marvellous Kaleidoscope - November 6, 2023 at 15:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-06 15:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-10 11:00:53',NULL,'The opening track of this week\'s Turo Island Sound Show is a mix of experimental music from around the world. It is a mixture of progressive fusion, alternative styles, and other discoveries. The narrator says he would like to pay respect to local indigenous communities and recognize that the music is heard across treaty territories. He also acknowledges that many of the music styles originated from Black culture, and he thanks the Black community for their contribution to alternative music. The first track of the week is a song by the singer-songwriter of the Czech Republic, Golden State. She has just released an album on Bandcamp. The second track is an electropop track by the artist from Vancouver, Her Head Is a House. The third track is a grime track by Beverly Glenn and his album Ones Ahead. The fourth track is by Helios Kenneth, an ambient project. The fifth track is one by Lawrence Ann from Montreal. The sixth track is called Vites, an experimental track on an album called Ornament Sea',NULL,'The Turo Island Sound Show: A mix of experimental music from around the world (11 minute read)'),(68827,83,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/06/to know the land - November 6, 2023 at 18:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-06 18:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-10 10:49:33',NULL,'The narrator says he grew up in the area of the Chesapeake Bay and the Appalachian Mountains. He describes the region as a \"middle zone\" where there are \"a lot of interesting geologically speaking, but also we sit in the middle zone\" . The narrator tells us that he has always been fascinated by faraway places, but that he prefers to stay at home and study the land. He says that the more he studies, the deeper he gets into the subject, and the more questions he has about it. The more he wants to know about someone, the more depth he wants in the relationship.',NULL,'The narrator\'s favorite place to study is the Chesapeake Bay '),(68828,82,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/06/Big Sis Radio - November 6, 2023 at 17:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-06 17:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-10 10:36:53',NULL,'Big Sis Radio plays a set of songs by the Balutos. The first song is called \"Aligned by theBlaze Baluto\" and it\'s off of their latest album \"What\'s On your Mind\". The second song is \"Electric Spital Attack\". The third song is a cover of a song called \"You, you you, you\" by the same band.',NULL,'Big Sis Radio plays the Balutos\' latest album '),(68838,84,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/06/Blues Around the Block - November 6, 2023 at 20:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-06 20:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-10 10:20:33',NULL,'Mac Dee is the host of the latest edition of the weekly program, \"Blues Around the Block\" on CFRU\'s 93.3 FM. The music is described in the program\'s title, \"I\'m Old Enough to Know Better.\" He also provides a link to past editions of the program, which can be streamed or downloaded from the CFRU archives. Mac Dee also introduces himself as Mac D, a 41-year-old father of two. He explains that he has a business degree and loves to tell jokes.',NULL,'Mac Dee is the host of CFRU\'s 93.3 FM Blues Around the Block '),(68839,84,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/06/Blues Around the Block - November 6, 2023 at 19:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-06 19:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-10 10:09:43',NULL,'Mac Dee welcomes listeners to his show, \"Blues Around the Block.\" He tells them that they can watch the show on CFRU.org or by downloading it from the university\'s website. Mac Dee also tells listeners that if they enjoyed the show, they can reach him by email at macd@cfr.ca. He also tells them to keep the show locked on the university for more blues. Mac D closes the show with a song by the \"glamour puss band\" Live at Shadackd. If you\'re in the middle of a crisis or have a mental health issue, you can get help from a toll-free helpline, 1-866-531.',NULL,'Listen to Mac Dee\'s show, \"Blues Around the Block,\" on CFRU.org '),(68848,86,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/06/The Deep House Project - November 6, 2023 at 22:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-06 22:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-10 09:58:11',NULL,'The Underground DJ\'s talk about their upcoming show. They\'re playing a mix of tracks that are going to be featured in their upcoming PSA, which is coming up on September 24th at the Tri City Synth Society\'s open mic night. The Underground DJs are psyched to be playing at the upcoming PSA. They invite you to check them out on Facebook or on X, since they\'ll be posting the music of the show there. Back to the USSR is the first thing that comes to mind. It starts off by saying that they\'ve been listening to a local FM station right now, and they\'re doing a lot of work for the homeless. They want to help the Canadian Alliance end homelessness. They also want to do some work for a local charity called Spelled D\'I-Y\'O\'D.',NULL,'The Underground DJs are psyched to be playing at the Tri City Synth Society’s open mic night '),(68849,85,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/06/Ripcord Radio - November 6, 2023 at 21:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-06 21:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-10 09:48:28',NULL,'The band\'s studio album, \"Burnham wits and Liberation Fly,\" was originally released in 1993 on only vinyl, but the original artwork was not the correct one. The band tried to correct the mistake, but it was too late. The record label, \"temporary residence limited,\" issued a new limited edition of the album, and the band had to perform the original release live. The other albums released in this time period include \"Naked Ray Gun With Home of the Brave,\" \"Lamb Faucet With Cut Larry,\" \"Shocked Out,\" \"Shot Maker With Two Left Standing,\" \"Cray Crayon Club,\" \"A Moment In Time 1993 to 1996,\" and \"City Babies Revenge,\" which were all released back when they were known as charged.',NULL,'The band was forced to reissue their 1993 studio album after it was mistakenly released on vinyl '),(68857,87,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/06/Back in the USSR - November 6, 2023 at 23:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-06 23:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-10 09:36:40',NULL,'The show opens with a description of the program and its purpose. The program is dedicated to the plight of the people of the Occupied Territories, particularly the people in Gaza. Seigfried, the host, says that his shows have been dedicated to this cause for the past few weeks. He explains that there is still no ceasefire in the conflict, despite the fact that the entire world calls for one. The show has been attended by hundreds of thousands of the world\'s citizens, who have gathered in cities all over the world to demand a cease-fire. As they have, however, he says, they have not been able to get into the personal toll of the conflict. He has not gotten into the human side of the story. He says that he is going to play an excerpt from an interview he had with a visiting professor named Hada Ad-jeal, who lost many of her family members in the war. She is a third generation refugee from Beit-Dal, a village in the south of the Gaza Strip. Her family was supposed to live in the safe area in southern Gaza in the summer of 2016, but last week, the bombs went off without warning. Hada and her daughter, Nora, explain that',NULL,'The Host of \'Seigfried\': The World\'s Most Inspiring Show on the Crisis in Gaza'),(68858,1447,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/07/Rainbow Country - November 7, 2023 at 00:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-07 00:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-10 09:24:21',NULL,'This program is part of a three-part episode of Rainbow Country, a weekly radio show hosted by Mark Tara that airs on 12 different Canadian radio stations. In this program, the program is described as a \"little gay radio show\" that is \"working to give voice\" to the \"LGBT community and beyond\" and is produced by and hosted by \"Barbie Q\" and \"the P-Girl\" . The show airs every day on CIUT FM, which is the largest public radio station in Canada. Rainbow Country is a \"nationally syndicated\" gay-owned and operated show, a \"number one LGBT podcast\" and a \"gay and lesbian chart\" on \"Podomatic.com\" and on \"Feedspot.com.\" The show is also a \"one-stop shop\" for information about the various Canadian film festivals, including the 48th. The first part of the program features three Canadian films: \"Solo,\" \"Summer Camp,\" and \"The Short Bloom.\" In the second part, the show features three music and two music videos from the LGBTQ community, all of which are produced on \"this episode\" of the show. In the third part, \"Journey 377,\" the show is described',NULL,'This is a \"little gay radio show\" that is \"working to give voice\" to the \"LGBT community and beyond\" '),(68863,1447,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/07/Rainbow Country - November 7, 2023 at 01:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-07 01:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-10 08:59:47',NULL,'Marc Tara, the creator of the popular music podcast, \"Rainbow Country,\" introduces himself and his show. He\'s a musician, songwriter, and producer who\'s been working in the music business for over 20 years. He has a big voice in the business, and he\'s got a lot to say in this one. He describes himself as \"an artist, a songwriter, a producer, and a musician.\" He also says that he wants to be a part of the business because he thinks it\'s important to have a place to express his feelings and ideas. He hopes listeners will stick around and listen to his music. He also wants to thank them for their support and says he hopes they\'ll all believe in him. Finally, he asks them to take him out for one of his original tracks.',NULL,'The creator of the popular music podcast, \"Rainbow Country,\" tells us how he wants to be a part of the'),(68877,80,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/07/CFRU Playlist - November 7, 2023 at 06:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-07 06:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-10 08:50:29',NULL,'The show\'s narrator introduces the narrator, a Philadelphia-based musician and field recording artist. He explains that he is a member of a band called Hotel, which also includes a group called Mortensage, and he lives in Philadelphia. The narrator describes the region of the U.S. as being in the middle of the country, between the northeast and the southeast. He describes the landscape as \"quite an interesting confluence\" of geological, historical, and climate elements. He says that the region is so varied that he will never tire of exploring it.',NULL,'The Mid-Atlantic: The U.S. in the Mid-Century '),(68887,78,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/07/Morning Soul Shake-Up! - November 7, 2023 at 08:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-07 08:00:00',86638720,'2023-11-10 08:37:29',NULL,'This is the first of a series of songs that Thomas King will perform in Guelph and throughout the rest of the province. The first song is titled \"Morning Soul Shake-up\" and it is a celebration of the \"morning soul\" and \"rare soul\" that characterize the sounds of the day. The song begins by introducing the listener to Thomas King who is the host of a popular morning show on CFRU. The show airs every day of the week and mixes soul music with funk. The theme of the song is \"be good or not\" and Thomas King says that he is not a man and that this is the time to \"fire me up\"',NULL,'\'Morning Soul Shake-Up\' is Thomas King\'s first song to celebrate the sound of the day '),(68897,2653,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/07/Solipsistic Retreat - November 7, 2023 at 10:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-07 10:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-10 08:28:35',NULL,'The guys talk about the McCrackens, a band from New York City that\'s one of the best-selling indie acts of all-time. The band\'s first album, Tommy the Chicken from Gob, was actually released in the same year as Tommy\'s debut album, What Came First, which was a huge hit. The guys agree that it\'s awesome that guitarists can play the drums and that drummers can understand how to play the other instruments. The group\'s drummer, Spot, is a dog, which means he\'s the better drummer. So, listen to the band. If you like the band, then you can listen to them, even if you hate them. But if you like them, you can\'t just listen to their music. You have to support them through your music. Sounds like a good idea, right? According to the Canadian Medical Association, one in eight people will die without a living donor of their own. So if you want to save someone\'s life, you\'ve got to register. You can become a donor by going to BeAdonor.ca.',NULL,'How to become a living donor in Canada (13 minute read)'),(68898,2653,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/07/Solipsistic Retreat - November 7, 2023 at 09:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-07 09:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-10 08:19:41',NULL,'The boys are back from their trip to their friends and family and they\'re listening to a program called \"Solipsistic Retreat\" on CFRU 93.2. They\'re talking about a band called Rec Center and there\'s also a solo band called the Ramones. Tommy Ramone is one of the original members of the band, and he\'s been making music since the \'80s. The boys say they\'ve listened to a lot of music, including the Ramones, and they all have a favorite Ramone. One of the boys says he was told the Ramones were like Green Day, but he couldn\'t listen to them because he was too young to understand how seriously they took their music. He says he cried when he heard the Ramones say he cried and he cried, but eventually he realized that the joke was his friends because the Ramones knew how they sounded, and it was really funny. The brothers decide to follow the Ramones\' lead and listen to people who aren\'t like them. They decide to sing to someone who isn\'t their own caricature. And then they decide to listen to someone they like.',NULL,'The Ramones Are Like Green Day, And They\'re Laughing (11 minute read)'),(68908,90,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/07/Bridging The Social Distance - November 7, 2023 at 12:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-07 12:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-10 08:09:24',NULL,'The narrator introduces us to Jenny Mitchell, a long-time CFR listener who is currently living at Riverside Glen. She\'s 92 years old and a widow with five children who have all died of breast cancer. She has 11 grandchildren and eight great-grandchildren, all of whom are boys. One of her great-grandchildren is four years old. She says her birthday is coming up soon, and she doesn\'t know when it will be. She plans to have a party for her family, but no one has come up with a plan. She also says that she\'s planning to rent a hall and invite everyone over for a party. She wants a magician to play music for half-an-hour, and hopes that everyone will enjoy it.',NULL,'Jenny Mitchell, a 92-year-old CFR listener, is planning a birthday party for her family '),(68909,1437,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/07/Democracy Now - November 7, 2023 at 11:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-07 11:00:00',86638720,'2023-11-10 07:58:01',NULL,'The war in the Gaza continues to escalate, and the United Nations reports that at least 10,000 people have been killed and over 4,000 children have been injured. Israel has ordered the evacuation of a children\'s hospital in the city of Rafah. The hospital is being used as a staging ground for Israel\'s ground offensives. The Israeli military has admitted that it accidentally struck a group of ambulances outside the Al-Shifah Hospital last week, killing 15 people and wounding dozens of others. The patient, a man named Hanid Abi Hawim Saad, tells how he narrowly survived last week\'s attack. He says that he was on his way to Egypt when the ambulance came under fire, killing the passengers in the ambulance and forcing them to return to the hospital. The man\'s injuries include a fractured skull, a dislocated shoulder, and a broken head. Israel will not comply with international calls for an immediate cease-fire, however, because it does not want to release its prisoners.',NULL,'Israel orders evacuation of children\'s hospital in Gaza, says man who survived last week\'s deadly attack '),(68912,155,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/a5epfk/DrMouth_CIUTshow_nov7_2023_fullshow.mp3','2023-11-07 19:52:21',287261888,'2023-11-10 07:46:05',NULL,'Dr. Mouth opens the show with a \"rock and roll lunch party\" , which he describes as a \"two hours of solid rock and roll for you\" . The first song is from the new album by Neil Young called \"Barn.\" The second song is a \"laid out mellow almost blues thing happening\" from Crazy Horse. The third song is \"Pleasant Dreams\" from the \"Reconstruction de Blanc\" album by the Ramones. The fourth song is one of the most famous songs in the entire Marvel Cinematic Universe , \"Spider-Man versus the Fly.\" The fifth track is from \"Foot in Cold Water\" by the Foot in the Cold Water.',NULL,'Dr. Mouth opens the show with a \"rock and roll lunch party\" '),(68920,125,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/07/Power Up! with Electrified Voltage - November 7, 2023 at 14:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-07 14:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-10 02:12:02',NULL,'This program opens with a description of the songs on the program. The songs are listed alphabetically. The first song is from Nigeria, the second is from Brazil, the third is from Germany, the fourth is from Ivory Knight, the fifth is from New Zealand, the sixth is from Colombia, the seventh is from Alistair James, the eighth is from Natalia, the ninth is from The Cranberries, the tenth is from Lip Select, the eleventh is from Future Memories, the twelfth is from Gorilla Systems, the thirteenth is from Irish band The Chieftains, and the fourteenth is from Machiana.',NULL,'The Songs of the World (13 minute audio program), Part 1 (22 minute video)'),(68921,1783,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/07/Under the Needle - November 7, 2023 at 13:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-07 13:00:00',86638720,'2023-11-10 01:59:12',NULL,'On this show, we\'re introduced to the desert rock band TamaCrest, who come from France, Mali, and Niger. They\'re all from the same place: the Sahara. The band\'s singer, Usman, lives everywhere in the world because he\'s a \"bio\" . But generally he walks somewhere north of Algeria and south of Mali. They have a new album out called Tamotate on Glitterbeat, and they\'re influenced by some of the most famous acts in the music world, like Dire Straits and Pink Floyd. They also wrote a song about a remote island in Japan, which they played on this show. This is the first time we\'ve heard the songs from this album, so we\'ll have to wait until next week to hear more. Also, check out the 50 Years of Hip-Hop on KEXP podcast. You can listen to this show wherever you listen, and be sure to watch the video. This program is made possible by the Corporation For Public Broadcasting. KEXP is a public station that is owned and operated by the University of California, Berkeley. The University has a community outreach team that works to promote local events and festivals. They need people to help out',NULL,'KEXP’s 50 Years of Hip-Hop (Sponsor)'),(68931,217,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/rucb2v/CIUTOct31.mp3','2023-11-07 21:57:02',143961989,'2023-11-10 01:46:33',NULL,'This is the second part of David James\'s creepy Halloween show, \"The Creepy Halloween Hootenanny Part 2.\" It\'s an all-new set that includes \"House of Hunt,\" \"Amazing Crowns,\" \"Southern Culturana,\" \"Deja Vuja,\" and \"alleydukes.\" In this second part, David introduces the audience to the various characters in the show and explains the concept of the blue eyes, which are the eyes of a man\'s face. This is a reference to the \"blue match\" in the English language that refers to the blue color of a person\'s eyes, as opposed to the yellow color of an English man\'S face. He also describes the show\'s theme, \"Christmas spirits,\" as a way of \"stirring all creatures.\"',NULL,'The Creepy Halloween Hootenanny Part 2 (Sponsor)'),(68932,1453,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/07/Silver Screen Dream Machine - November 7, 2023 at 15:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-07 15:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-10 01:33:55',NULL,'The show starts off with a musical comedy trio called The Arrogant worms from their 2002 concert film Three worms in an Orchestra. It\'s an orchestral version of \"The Last Saskatchewan Pirate,\" which is about a pirate captain who stole fertilizer from a ship in the Norwegian harbor. The song is a bit of a tongue-in-cheek take on life. The band also makes a surprise appearance in the animated film \"Hans Zimmer,\" which was released in the mid-1990s. On October 28 th , the world lost Matthew Perry who played the role of \"Chandler Bing\" on the long running sitcom Friends from 1994 until its end in 2004. He died suddenly in his tub. The show then turns to the 2000 crime comedy Oz Gets A Surprise, which stars Matthew Perry as Oz-Ozzina alongside Bruce Willis. The score is by Randy Edelman. Then we hear the opening credits of \"Almost Heroes,\" a 1998 film directed by Chris Farley and starring Matthew Perry and Chris Vanston as explorers in the 1800\'s. And then we hear a mix of the soundtrack to \"Friends,\" the sitcom which has made Matthew Perry famous. And finally, the show closes with a set of covers of four songs by Van Parks. The',NULL,'The Last Saskatchewan Pirate, The Arrogant Worms, and Matthew Perry\'s Death in a Tub '),(68933,3033,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/07/A Multilingual Affair - November 7, 2023 at 16:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-07 16:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-10 01:17:04',NULL,'The foursome of Cosmovermo, HIM57, and Piers Ulvit bring their unique sound to the concert. The show begins with an introduction by A 777, who explains that he was talking with a friend about the world of music when he realized that the words he was using were inspirational. He plans to use the words to inspire others to pursue their dreams.',NULL,'A 777, Cosmovermo, HIM57, and Piers Ulvit Bring Their Sound to a Concert '),(68943,91,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/07/Tuesday at 5 - November 7, 2023 at 17:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-07 17:00:00',86638720,'2023-11-10 00:53:47',NULL,'On Remembrance Day, the show opens with a song about love changing. The song is about a woman who tells her lover that she no longer loves him. The tune is from an album by William Prince called \"Stand in the Joy\" and it\'s a collection of six songs. Also included is a song by Ken Dunn called \"Shifting Sand\" and a song called \"Blurry Days\" from Patrick Creif\'s album \"When You Miss Someone.\" The song by Sia is about madness. The show ends with a long song about the importance of Remembrance Day. This year, the Remembrance Day is on Saturday, so the show chooses songs that speak to him to remember. The first song is from a singer named Lorena McKeinnett who released an album called \"Elemental\" in 1985. The second song is by Douglas Campbell who recited a poem by William Blake called \"Lullaby.\" And the third song is a tune by the Kingston trio who recorded \"Where Have All the Flowers Gone\" in 1961. The fourth song is an Elton John song about \"Blueberry Hill.\" The show\'s not very eventful. The kids had four visits to trick or treat, and the house chores were very limited. The only activity',NULL,'The Remembrance Day Show Is a Must-See for All Veterans (13 minute read)'),(68944,1455,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/07/Down the Rabbit Hole - November 7, 2023 at 18:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-07 18:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-10 00:42:37',NULL,'The Underground Man takes us back to his apartment and tells us that he\'s had a great day. He\'s been talking to a friend about art and music, and he thinks it\'s really cool. He also says that sometimes small talk can be a good thing, because sometimes you need to talk to other people about things that you\'re interested in. He plays a song by Wisp, and then they play another song by David Bowie, which is called \"Blackstar\" from his last album, which was released before his death. The song is about going to the city, and the Underground Man says it reminds him of David Lynch\'s \"Twin Peaks\" movie. He thinks that this song is a good one. He goes on to say that this album is much more \"rooted in reality\" in terms of how sad the album is. He doesn\'t know how to interpret the word \"sad\" , and says that it might be more of a \"real\" thing, like \"Yeah I\'m going to die soon, but he ended up being something really great\" . But he does like the song. They\'ve also got a song called \"Headcase\" by the Island of',NULL,'The Underground Man reveals that he\'s had a great day. He\'s been talking to a friend about art and music'),(68954,94,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/07/Let’s Get Lost - November 7, 2023 at 20:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-07 20:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-10 00:27:35',NULL,'The show opens with a description of the band, led by guitar player Don Scott and bassist Michael Herring. Scott and Herring are known for their funk/soul fusion band, Butcher Brown. They are out of Virginia, but they\'re also out of Richmond. They\'ve got a new album out called We\'re Got Nothing, out on Step 3 Records. They have a new record out called Solar Music out on Concord Records. The Wonderland Wonderland album is very jazz-y. They also have an album out with the orchestra, Ex Machina, out by the National Orchestra du Jazz. The title track is from that album, called Talking Makes it Worse. The band also has an album coming out called Kind Mind from Josh Cole, who\'s from Toronto. The album is called Grimsta from IPA, a Scandinavian label. It has a great title track. It is out on C-uniform Records. There\'s also a new release from the Canadian artist, Mona Roberts.',NULL,'What\'s next for Butcher Brown? (Sponsor)'),(68955,1591,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/07/New or Never - November 7, 2023 at 19:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-07 19:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-10 00:17:30',NULL,'The show opens with a sampling of the latest music from the university\'s library. The first band we hear is Bombay Bicycle Club, a band from London. Safiya is a French Canadian folk singer songwriter from Quebec City, and the second band is A Senabi from Canada. He\'s an OG Cree, a member of Sandy Lake First Nations, who was born as Evan Pang Indigenous Racism by portraying himself to the community, as Asian rather than Indigenous. Brian Webb, also known as Bri Webb from the band Constantines, is a singer and songwriter. He has a new album out called Run With Me. The third band is Todo Todo Nada Mal, a Latin American singer-songwriter. The fourth band is Land of Talk from Montreal. They\'re led by Elizabeth Powell. The fifth band is Mariette from St.Andamont Quebec. She\'s with Joseph Mihailican and Samuel Gugsaux. The sixth band is Jordy Gordon, a Canadian musician known for performing as part of acts including Islands and US Girl.',NULL,'The University of British Columbia’s New Music Show: The Latest Music from the Library '),(68965,217,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/2ihb93/CIUTNov7.mp3','2023-11-08 04:35:30',143961989,'2023-11-10 00:05:51',NULL,'In this final episode of the series, James continues his discussion of music and its relation to the present. He announces that the CIUT Fall Funding Drive will begin next week, so he will send out invites for the show. He also reminds listeners that they can come down to the club and host the show for free if they donate to the cause. He says that he will also be sending out music playlists as always. He encourages listeners to check out the club\'s Facebook pages or to visit the club on the web. The club will also send out a reminder to listeners to come down and donate.',NULL,'James: The CIUT Fall Funding Drive will begin next week, so he will send out invites '),(68966,94,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/07/Let’s Get Lost - November 7, 2023 at 21:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-07 21:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-09 23:56:01',NULL,'This first part of the Humanoid Radio program introduces Alan, host of the CFRU-run radio show Humanoid, to a track by Reuben Von Smith. It is from his latest album, Da-Cuckoo Ya Ya. The song is a love song, and it is a symbol of unity.',NULL,'Reuben Von Smith\'s Love Song (Sponsor)'),(68967,95,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/07/Humanoid Radio - November 7, 2023 at 22:00