" by singer-songwriter Douglas Health. The song is about consciousness, reflection, and the mind. It is followed by a song about the self, \"Legend of a Mind.\"',NULL,NULL),(69280,154,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/13/This Night Wounds Time - November 13, 2023 at 00:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-13 00:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-13 11:14:05',NULL,'This night, the show\'s featured artist, Christopher Curry, takes a moment to talk about the show and its various parts. He tells us that the show has reached the part where he\'s going to begin a geographical spotlight series, where he plays music by artists from a particular country or territory. He also tells us about the other countries that he has covered, including Russia, China, Canada, the United States, Brazil, India, Australia, and the Vatican City. He says that he\'ll be doing a mini-spotlight on the eighth-smallest country, Argentina, when the show finishes up. He explains that this isn\'t the same place that he covered in the past, so he plans to do a little more of it when he gets to the end. He\'s also going to tell us that it\'s not a different country from the countries he has already covered. The first part of the spotlight is on Argentina, where there are 23 provinces and the city of the city, Buenos Aires. The second part of this is on the 19th province, which is called Taiwan, which means \"Taiwan island.\" It\'s a small island in the South Pacific.',NULL,NULL),(69281,154,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/12/This Night Wounds Time - November 12, 2023 at 23:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-12 23:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-13 10:57:39',NULL,'This Night Wounded Time The show begins with a description of the music on the show and then shifts to a discussion of the show\'s geographical focus. The show will be dedicated to music from a \"geographic jurisdiction\" somewhere on the globe. This is the first time the show has been able to do this, and the program will focus on music from the province of B