m Straight Ahead .\n\nThen we hear \"Bill Withers\" and \"Use Me\" from his 1972 \"StillBill\" album. The band also includes \"Underneath the Waves,\" a song that was originally written for the album Still Bill . We start the show and the show again with \"The Twilight Singers\" and underneath the waves from the album Powder Burns . Now we hear a song called \"Can\'t Believe we\'re here\" from Jay Mascis\'s new album \"What Do we do with you?\" . Also, a song',NULL,NULL),(69347,97,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/16/Wild Combination - November 16, 2023 at 00:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-16 00:00:00',86638720,'2023-11-17 09:13:16','2023-11-16 07:06:30','Equality 7-2521 explains that he and his family must return to their homeland and live in the refugee camps outside of Palestine. He recounts the hardships they endured in their village, which was very beautiful and full of life.\n\nThey were very hungry, and they lived 10 people in a small room. They had tuberculosis, which killed four out of five of their children. The revolution was the turning point in their lives. They started a general union of women and organized schools for women, which helped support their families. In 1956, they started the Palestine National Liberation Movement, also known as the Popular Front for the Liberation of Palestine, in the Gaza workshop. Equality 7521 tells the story of how he met with the other leaders of the Palestinian National Front.\n\nHe explains that for nine years, they were very secret about their military activities, but on January 1, 1965, they launched their first military operation in occupied Palestine. The people wanted to join them. They contacted the other political parties, but they rejected their ideas, saying that they cannot liberate their land, that the war should be short- and decisive, and that they should not worry about their revolution. Both the Israelis and the Arabs sent secret police to arrest their commanders. All governments feared the revolution',NULL,NULL),(69348,97,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/16/Wild Combination - November 16, 2023 at 01:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-16 01:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-17 09:02:38','2023-11-16 09:06:37','EdVideo is a local organization that offers a variety of creative workshops and educational opportunities for people of all ages. The organization is open to all levels of creative expression. EdVideo\'s goal is to provide a place for people to learn, create, and display their work.',NULL,NULL),(69349,78,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/16/Morning Soul Shake-Up! - November 16, 2023 at 08:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-16 08:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-17 08:51:01','2023-11-16 15:06:24','',NULL,NULL),(69350,110,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/16/Here Today - November 16, 2023 at 07:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-16 07:00:00',86638720,'2023-11-17 08:43:22','2023-11-16 15:06:45','Aaron Badgley, host of the popular CFRU 96.3FM show, takes us back to the present to tell us about some of the latest music. First, he tells us that Paul Manchin has released a new album, Master, which contains some of his most popular songs. Then he brings us up to speed on the latest news from the music scene. He gives us a rundown of all the latest releases, including a song by the Beatles, a new song by Church of Trees, and an update on the work of Deborah Fialkov.',NULL,NULL),(69351,111,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/16/Tales from the Bridge - November 16, 2023 at 09:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-16 09:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-17 08:31:13','2023-11-16 17:06:36','The guys get a bunch of new stuff to discuss, and this time, they\'re talking about a book. This one\'s called \"The Art of Living in Space.\" And it\'s all about living inside of an asteroid, which is a really popular space-colonization idea in science fiction, according to the guys. But there\'s another guy who\'s done some research on this, and he\'s written a paper showing how to do it in 12 years, which makes the guys super excited. The whole thing sounds like a good idea, but it\'ll take a lot of hard work and a lot more than that, because you need to build a huge, expensive space station to get to the moon.',NULL,NULL),(69352,112,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/16/FoodFarm Talk - November 16, 2023 at 10:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-16 10:00:00',86638720,'2023-11-17 08:21:00','2023-11-16 17:06:36','This episode of Behind the Aroma is all about supporting local farmers, and this is a big part of why we do it. We\'re supporting the people who are doing the \"itty gritty work\" behind the scenes, not just the \"people here\" or the \"corporations\" who are buying the original product.\n\nWe talk about Balzac\'s three different beans, one of which supports the Atwood blend. The other two beans support women\'s farmers in particular, and Balzac has been working with them to make sure that they sell all of their products to support them. The idea of supporting local people, even if they\'re in another country, is very appealing to us. We also talk about geographical indications, or GIs, which are a sign that a product is made from a specific geographical place.\n\nThis is a really important sign because it helps people know where the product came from, and it also helps people figure out who\'s using the product illegally. So, for example, if a company wants to use a product that\'s made in the U.S. to sell it in Africa, it has to have a sign saying that it came from Africa.',NULL,NULL),(69353,90,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/16/Bridging The Social Distance - November 16, 2023 at 12:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-16 12:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-20 03:59:23','2023-11-16 19:06:35','In this episode, Jenny Mitchell, the host of the local community radio show Bridging the Social Distance, interviews Francois Daucourt, a long-term resident at Riverside Glen. The interview is recorded in 2023. Daucourt is a native of Verner, an area near the town of Surgeon Falls in northern Ontario.\n\nWhen he was young, he learned English at an English school in Welland. He also learned French at a French school in Verner. He says that the younger years were wild, like \"dancing and associating with my friends\" . However, when he turned 17 years old, he was \"boy crazy\" and had to learn to be careful with boys. His mother was strict with him, but he says that he thanks her for being so strict.','',NULL),(69354,1437,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/16/Democracy Now - November 16, 2023 at 11:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-16 11:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-17 08:02:04','2023-11-16 19:07:35','The war continues in the Gaza Strip, with dozens of Palestinians killed. Israel allows fuel to enter the Strip for the first time since the beginning of the conflict, but it does not allow it to be used for humanitarian purposes.\n\nAt the largest hospital, thousands of patients, doctors, and workers remain trapped inside, unable to move. The World Medical Association has condemned Israel\'s attack on the hospital, calling it an \"unacceptable military incursion into a hospital.\" The Israel Defense Forces have published images of weapons inside the hospital but have dismissed the images as propaganda. Vice President Joe Biden has also repeated Israeli claims that Hamas uses the hospital.',NULL,NULL),(69355,113,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/16/Android’s Dungeon - November 16, 2023 at 13:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-16 13:00:00',86638720,'2023-11-18 12:49:49','2023-11-16 21:06:40',' The show is called \"Android\'s Dungeon,\" and it is hosted by Jack. He explains that it is now November and that the season is pre-holiday, meaning that people put up their Christmas decorations. ',NULL,NULL),(69356,13307,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/16/Eclectic Selections - November 16, 2023 at 14:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-16 14:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-17 07:37:55','2023-11-16 21:07:47','Jack says that the show is a little too much like