he same composer\'s discography.',NULL,NULL),(69573,146,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/26/The Kookoo Bananas Variety Hour - November 26, 2023 at 10:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-26 10:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-26 22:17:33','2023-11-26 17:07:03','The gang begins their morning program by singing a song about trees. The song is called \"The Breadfruit Tree\" and the theme of the program is \"trees\".\n\nThe song\'s title refers to the fact that breadfruit is a fruit that tastes like bread. The narrator, who is a friend of Granddad\'s, tells the listeners that he first heard of breadfruit when he was talking with a friend about it. The breadfruit tree is important in Florida because even though the state can\'t produce breadfruit, it could produce enough breadfruit to fill the entire home. In one year, a single tree could produce over 450 pounds of the fruit. This is a lot of bread. They then discuss apples, which they believe to be the best fruit for Jake.',NULL,NULL),(69574,101,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/26/Seems Like Old Times - November 26, 2023 at 14:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-26 14:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-26 21:55:37','2023-11-26 20:43:43','The program starts out with a half-hour of music and radio memories from the 30s and 40s. The first song is Frank Sinatra\'s \"You\'re Stardust\" which has been recorded by many artists.\n\nThe second song is \"Tales of the Texas and Box 13\" by Hoagie and Mitchell Parrish, which has also been recorded. The third song is Peggy Mayen\'s song \"Before Happy Will Be Beyond Sea\" which was written and performed by Duke Ellington at the 2000 Toronto Jazz Festival and which has now been recorded in the United States. The fourth song is a Christmas concert by the 50 plus members of the Cambridge 50 Choir. The concert is free and the choir is looking for more information. The fifth song is from the \"greatest songs of the fiftys\" by Barry Manilow. The program then moves to the third song, which is from Judy Ga