re music. Before the show ends, the program notes that Google and Metaproducts have announced that they will be blocking news content on Facebook and on Instagram due to the Bill C-18 that was passed earlier this year. The program explains that it is a campus organization and thus they share news and upcoming events as well as learning opportunities. Unfortunately, because of the response to the bill, the university will no longer have access to Facebook and Instagram. To continue supporting the program, please subscribe to the newsletter',NULL,NULL),(69583,150,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/26/Zombie Jamboree - November 26, 2023 at 19:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-26 19:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-27 03:29:44','2023-11-27 03:07:01','The first hour of the Zombie Jamboree is over, and it\'s time for another round of the music. The first act is from DJ Shub, followed by a bunch of other dudes. The second act is by Matt Berninger, who\'s just back from playing with The National. It sounds like this will be the last set of the festival, but there\'s lots of more music to come. Next up is a dance party from DJ JJ. It\'s called the \"smoke dance,\" and it takes place on the campus of Columbia University. The DJ and the other dudes are all psyched to be out there.',NULL,NULL),(69584,200,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/jg9dex/karibuni_nov_26-2023amcpp.mp3','2023-11-27 03:26:02',287962512,'2023-11-27 06:13:10','2023-11-27 05:05:42','On this edition of the show, the host, Nadine McNulty, thanks all of the listeners who have made donations to the station. She also thanks Alvin for saying that the show is one of his favorites at the station, and she also thanks Praveen, Rohini, and other listeners for their support of the station and for supporting live concerts in the city. The host also announces that they will be giving away tickets to a show by the Okavango African Orchestra on December 2nd. The show will be a celebration of the band\'s new album, Migration, and they will also play some of their favorites from their previous works.\n\nThey will also be playing some songs from their latest album, which is out as well. They\'ll also be celebrating the upcoming Christmas season and the show will also pay tribute to Sarah Tavares, a Cap Verdean woman who has recently passed away. She was one of the guests on the program, and the host decided to remember her.',NULL,NULL),(69585,152,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/26/Through the Looking Glass - November 26, 2023 at 21:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-26 21:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-27 05:49:06','2023-11-27 05:06:57','The next hour, the band travels through the Looking-Glass and listens to music wherever it takes them. The first track is Departures, a collection of songs by Fonzie, which the narrator describes as a \"slight throat\" which he hopes will keep listeners from getting sick.\n\nThe next song is the Alter-Cacters\' \"Unsidable\" from the late-century magnetic tapes. It is time to turn the conversation over to the German music correspondent Melanie, who has been listening to a lot of music for the show. The song is from a new album, \"The Revenge Of Hieronymus-Bosch,\" which is about to come out. The proceeds from the sale of the album go to the Save-the-Children charity. The program will go up on the CFR-U website under \"the show page\" next week. The band continues on with a song from Raised-By-Haze, Touch the Sky, and then a new track by Night Parrots, The Storyline-Ends Here.\n\nThe music is described as \"completely beautiful\" and the narrator hopes that listeners will come back next week as they follow the music through the looking-glass. The final track is a song dedicated to Matt, from the Tone-Zone, who is a \"massive supporter\" of Juliana Hatfield, who sings \"ELO\" and \"Bluebird is Dead.\" The program ends with a track dedicated \"to Matt from the T-Zone\" who is \"',NULL,NULL),(69586,153,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/26/Backtracks - November 26, 2023 at 22:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-26 22:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-27 05:31:21','2023-11-27 05:06:59','The program opens with the first of many covers of songs by Frank Zappa, the West Coast pop art experimental band, and the British psychedelic band Kaleidoscope. The program moves on to a song by Moby Spence, Bob Mose, Don Stevenson and Peter Lewis called Indifference, and then to Egyptian Gardens from the psychedelic band Side Trips. The show closes with Mars Bonfire\'s Born to be Wild. Both Mars and his brother, Jerry, recorded the song in 1968 and released it with Steppenwolf.',NULL,NULL),(69587,154,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/27/This Night Wounds Time - November 27, 2023 at 00:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-27 00:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-27 14:04:07','2023-11-27 07:07:16','',NULL,NULL),(69588,154,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/26/This Night Wounds Time - November 26, 2023 at 23:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-26 23:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-27 07:29:45','2023-11-27 07:07:17','The program opens with a description of the music on the air. The program is all about music that is \"off the beaten track,\" which means that it\'s not in the center of the world.\n\nThe music in this program is from artists who live somewhere in the world, and they\'re from different provinces in different parts of the country, so they\'ll be playing music from different regions. The first song on the program is \"Stray Carrier hidgen\" by Pierre Bastine, an artist from Canada. He\'s from the Netherlands. The second song is from Gabriel Burnbaugh, who\'s also from the same country. The third song is \"Rapid fr\" by Josh Zubat.',NULL,NULL),(69589,154,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/27/This Night Wounds Time - November 27, 2023 at 01:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-27 01:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-27 09:33:07','2023-11-27 09:07:03','In this week\'s show, the host of a local radio show, Christopher Curry, talks about the geography of the world. He explains that the show has been doing a \"geographic spotlight series\" for the past ten years. Since then, they\'ve covered the internal parts of seven of the largest countries on the planet, Russia, China, Canada, the United States, Brazil, and Australia. They\'ve also done a \"mini-series\" on smaller countries, including the Vatican City, the Galapagos Islands, Monaco, and Nauru. They also covered the smallest country in the whole world, the Marshall Islands, which is just a tiny speck of land in the middle of the Pacific Ocean.',NULL,NULL),(69590,78,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/27/Morning Soul Shake-Up! - November 27, 2023 at 08:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-27 08:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-27 15:47:23','2023-11-27 15:06:45','The university\'s Media and Communications Center offers a variety of volunteer opportunities, including hosting your own show or podcasting, as well as helping with a wide range of creative projects throughout the year. We\'re always looking for people with an interest and passion in music production, video production, or public service announcements. If you are fascinated by music and/or production, we\'d like you to help out with one of our shows, live events, or live events and live performances. We also want you to be interested in engineering a live stream of our in-studio streams. No experience is necessary, just a willingness to learn. When you\'re ready, email us at cpu.ca and we\'ll get you started.',NULL,NULL),(69591,110,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/27/Here Today - November 27, 2023 at 07:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-27 07:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-27 15:29:55','2023-11-27 15:07:09','The program begins with a description of the band Dirty Hurricane, which is described as a \"rocking country on steroids\" band. They have released a new Christmas single, \"Christmas is Coming,\" and they are described as being in a festive mood. The band\'s members include singer-songwriter Joe Leskoff, former members of the bands While You Wait and Justice FM, and Mr. Bottomline. The song is described by the program as being a \"great song.\" The program goes on to describe a band called Hillsborough, which has just released an album called \"Hillsborough.\n\n\" The band also has a single called \"Coming Down.\" The show then turns to some other artists, including Juno Award-winning British artist Deborah Fejallowicz, the English duo Moons of Jupyters, and Len Mazzoni. The program also describes Bernard Frazier, a Canadian artist who has made a name for himself as a singer, songwriter, and performer.',NULL,NULL),(69592,79,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/27/Breezy Breakfast Radio - November 27, 2023 at 10:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-27 10:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-27 17:51:15','2023-11-27 17:06:11','Dr. Rivers discusses the importance of having a male role model in a family and how having a female role model can be beneficial for a family.\n\nHe also discusses his practice, which is diverse, and how he sees his clients. He says that his job as a psychologist is to hold space no matter where he is from or what his culture is. He explains that there are two kinds of men in his practice: men who want to return to their original cultures and men who need to stay in North America or Canada. He adds that he has lots of diverse clients, and he has a fair share of them. He tells us that the whole underpinning of everything he does is the pain he carries as a client. When he can help a client figure out that there is other options than suffering, that he is not his own pain, then he can realize that there may be other options for him.',NULL,NULL),(69593,79,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/27/Breezy Breakfast Radio - November 27, 2023 at 09:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-27 09:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-27 17:28:30','2023-11-27 17:06:11','This morning\'s guest, Dave Robinson, is a local psychotherapist who focuses on mental health. Dave\'s a big supporter of the annual men\'s movement \"Movember\" , which is dedicated to raising awareness and funds to support mental health in men. Before we get into the topic of mental health, we should mention that suicide is a common problem in Indigenous communities. Because of this, the discussion will be more about reconciliation than it is about suicide.',NULL,NULL),(69594,164,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/ww6zkh/BTHNov27.mp3','2023-11-27 18:10:29',44384870,'2023-11-27 20:48:44','2023-11-27 19:05:26','This morning on Beyond the Headslines, Audrey, Mehdi, and Steffi discuss the housing crisis in Canada. The program aims to bring you into the conversation by discussing the issues beyond the headlines. The most pressing issue that we\'re going to discuss today is the crisis of housing supply. The government is making huge commitments to address the problem, but it\'s only part of the solution.',NULL,NULL),(69595,206,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/7jkyus/November_25th_2023_The_Minx_Sessions9d4ts.mp3','2023-11-27 17:44:21',287962512,'2023-11-27 20:27:26','2023-11-27 19:05:46','The host of the CIUT 99.5FM Minx Sessions program takes the listeners by the hand and tells them that he is a community radio station and that he cannot support all the independent artists if he did not have the same platform.\n\nHe encourages listeners to make donations to the station and to support the artists on the program. The music that he will play tonight will be all independent music. He will be playing music from Minas science out on the Balmat wonderful label, and he will also be playing some dub techno. The show will also include a mix of old school arrow bricks and home frequencies. The host also invites listeners to buy their releases and to share the music on Facebook. He tells listeners that every artist is making music for free and that it is his duty to support them. The first track is Balmat, which is quite a tidy and reminds him of the music he has listened to on the show before.\n\nThe second track is Akan Ferguson, a remix of the CCL\'s \"Rain Again for Anna\" and the third track is Nadi Ferguson\'s Minx science ambient friends volume three. The mix of Rain Again and Fear is one of the most popular releases on the station. The DJ will also play some remixes of the releases from the artist\'s home frequency.',NULL,NULL),(69596,247,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/q5735r/November_25th_2023_Calling_All_Blues8wiou.mp3','2023-11-27 17:45:24',143961989,'2023-11-28 01:54:38','2023-11-27 19:05:50','The show is all about Mississippi blues and that he is going to play a lot of acoustic blues, acoustic folk blues, and real folk blues that were recorded in the 60s and 70s.\n\nThe second part of the program is called the \"Slop\" and it is a song by Jasper Love. He says he wants to loosen up a bit and tells his listeners that he used to do the \"slop\" for them. He tells them that as long as he was with them, he did \"the slop\" for \"you\" and then \"you did the slop for me\" . He then says that he\'s going to fill up the slop.',NULL,NULL),(69597,1437,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/27/Democracy Now - November 27, 2023 at 11:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-27 11:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-27 19:48:30','2023-11-27 19:07:25','',NULL,NULL),(69598,1438,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/27/Worst Responders - November 27, 2023 at 12:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-27 12:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-27 19:27:58','2023-11-27 19:07:26','',NULL,NULL),(69599,207,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/hxu49v/Music_w_db_Hawkes_Nov_29_2023_podcast64i4l.mp3','2023-11-27 19:48:05',285024129,'2023-11-27 21:45:53','2023-11-27 21:05:43','',NULL,NULL),(69600,80,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/27/CFRU Playlist - November 27, 2023 at 14:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-27 14:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-27 21:05:55','2023-11-27 21:05:55',NULL,NULL,NULL),(69601,64080,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/27/Slaughter Beach Who - November 27, 2023 at 13:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-27 13:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-27 21:29:43','2023-11-27 21:07:50','The show begins with Gwen introducing herself as the host of the CFRU-FM program, \"Slaughter Beach Who.\" Gwen introduces herself as a friend of hers who is also a fan of the band. Gwen explains that the band is made up of Jake Wald, lead singer, and Ian Farmer, drummer.\n\nThe band is on tour, and Gwen has the opportunity to go to one of their shows. Gwen describes the band as being \"indie rock,\" but she also describes their first two albums as \"Midwest emo\" and \"folk\" respectively. They also have an upcoming album, \"At the Moonbase,\" which Gwen describes as \"safe and also no fear.\"',NULL,NULL),(69610,81,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/27/The Sentinel’s Marvellous Kaleidoscope - November 27, 2023 at 15:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-27 15:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-27 23:49:05','2023-11-27 23:06:01','The narrator introduces himself as Nicholas Cooper, the guardian overseer of the music. He offers thanks to the First Nation, Inuit, and Métis peoples who live on Turtle Island. He also thanks the Black community for their contributions to the music, which are often dismissed and/or uncredited.\n\nThe first song of the day is by Bjork, who is known for her \"big time sensuality\" . The music opens with a set of tracks from the new album by the Los Angeles-based ambient composer Olive Arisoni, the Paulinski Micro-Band from Toronto, and the Bri-Web band from Guelph, Ontario. The narrator then reads about the new record by Bri-WEB, who returned to the stage after ten years away with his last album.',NULL,NULL),(69611,57654,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/27/Apollo Suns live on CFRU! - November 27, 2023 at 16:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-27 16:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-28 01:58:44','2023-11-27 23:07:36','The host and his friends are back on the CFRU 98.3 The Explorer with a new song: Vegas Phantom Power. The song is from the album Vegas Formula, and the host is glad it\'s out there. Also, one of the first songs on K-Tel, the third album from artist OX, is called Kung Fu.\n\nThe host is impressed with the ability of artists to change up their music genres so easily. Then, he\'s introduced to a band from Nova Scotia called Human Missile Crisis. They\'re a punk band with a punk vibe. Then he introduces Will Anderson, the lead singer of the band Weed. Weed is a Vancouver-based rock band. Weed has a rotating band of backing bands, which makes it sound like Weed has formed a band. ',NULL,NULL),(69612,82,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/27/Big Sis Radio - November 27, 2023 at 17:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-27 17:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-28 01:56:20','2023-11-28 01:05:56','In this special edition of Big Sis, Cece tells us about the new music being played on the show. First off, he tells us that this show is about supporting people who are experiencing poverty downtown.\n\nHe encourages listeners to push back against the injustices that exist around the world. He tells us the last tracks we listened to on Big Sis were Radio Collection by Ala-mode, Doubt by slowpulp, yearning by subsonic eye, palm owasa-nwok, and I-m-a-dog by faith healer. Next up, he gives us a track from Bri Webbs new album, Run With Me, which is about a period in his life when he was in turmoil and needed to find a way to get his music out there again. He says that the response to his new album was overwhelming. He thinks that Bris story reminds us all that we are all one human collective and that we all suffer from active hatred. This is the 58th show of Big sis.',NULL,NULL),(69613,83,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/27/to know the land - November 27, 2023 at 18:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-27 18:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-28 01:31:45','2023-11-28 01:06:02','Deer Day is here and Byron is the host of the show on 93.3 CFRU in Guelph. He\'s talking about the deer that are in the rut, the time when bucks are looking to mate. He explains that there are lots of deer tracks and signs all around the place. He says that people are out hunting and looking for these signs and tracks. He also says that the weather is cold, which is good because it means the deer are out in the cold.',NULL,NULL),(69614,157,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/wi6vmb/510-33-45-78-nov27-23.mp3','2023-11-28 01:38:15',287463030,'2023-11-28 04:15:33','2023-11-28 03:05:16','The show starts off with a discussion of King, who was a Canadian singer, songwriter, and musician who died in the United States in the early 1900s. He was followed by Deep Purple, King Crimson, King Cole, King Gannam, King and the Howler, and Bill King. King was a frequent guest on the Bill King Show, which was hosted by the late Bill King in Toronto in 1974. The first song on the King CD is \"Albatross\" by Fleetwood Mac. The second song is \"King and the Tubes with TV\" by King Crimson.\n\nThe third song is a song called \"Louis Rial\" by the King Crimson band. The fourth song is called \"Country and Western Hits\" by Jerry Lieber Mike. The fifth song is by Bob King and \"Gordie Howe Song\" which was written by Bob. The last song is an untitled song by King Cole. The song was recorded around the same time as the first two.',NULL,NULL),(69615,84,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/27/Blues Around the Block - November 27, 2023 at 20:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-27 20:00:00',86638720,'2023-11-28 03:51:09','2023-11-28 03:05:59','Mac Dee introduces himself as the host of the weekly blues show, \"Blues Around the Block.\" He welcomes listeners to the show and invites them to listen to the music.\n\nIn the first hour of the show, Mac Dee presents the music of Scott Ellison, Dawn Tyler Watson, Ben Racine, and Ditra Farr. The music of the Recording Alligator includes the Reverend Raven, the Chainsmoking Boys, Tony Joe White and the Charlie White. The song that Mac Dee and the others hear is \"It Takes A Lot to Laugh It Takes A Train to Cry.\" Mac Dee says that he doesn\'t play much of the music from the recording. He says that his favorite song is the one that the others heard.',NULL,NULL),(69616,84,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/27/Blues Around the Block - November 27, 2023 at 19:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-27 19:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-28 03:30:31','2023-11-28 03:06:00','This edition of the Blues Around the block is a continuation of the first edition, which was hosted by Mac Dee. This time around, Mac Dee is joined by his friend and fellow musician, the Hogtown All Stars. The show opens with John Primer\'s \"Hard Times\" and \"Tough Times,\" followed by \"Buddy Guy,\" \"Donald Ray Johnson,\" \"Last Call,\" and \"Down Child.\" Next, the show moves to Paul James\' \"Lost in Blues,\" \"Cut You Loose,\" and the \"Durham County Poets\'\" \"Hand Me Down Blues.\" The program ends with \"Something Ive Done,\" the last song ever recorded by Donald Ray Johnson.',NULL,NULL),(69617,85,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/27/Ripcord Radio - November 27, 2023 at 21:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-27 21:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-28 05:54:35','2023-11-28 05:05:52','The show opens with a shout-out to the listeners of 93.3 CFRU. It\'s a punk rock show with lots of music from the past and present. The first song we hear is from a band called We Believe, who have songs that are fast and dirty. The band\'s first album, Back from the Dead, was reissued in 2021. The band also has a demo from 1982 or 83, which they\'re currently offering as part of their complete discography collection at supremeecho.\n\nThen we hear some European music from Italy, Sweden, and England. We also hear some noisecore from the U.S. and Canada. The next song is from Young Mountain, who played their first Canadian show back in August at the New Friends Fest. Here\'s some more music from Europe. Next up is Superposition Principle, a project by Son of Denny from Poland. Then it\'s Old Pride from England. And finally, it\'ll be Age 16 from Baltimore.',NULL,NULL),(69618,86,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/27/The Deep House Project - November 27, 2023 at 22:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-27 22:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-28 05:34:19','2023-11-28 05:05:57','The Deep House Show opens with a recap of last week\'s show. The show starts off with a song called Feeling Sad by Nick Holder, which inspired the show to play an all-Canada mini-mix. The song features Diana Ross\'s voice from her hit \"Lover Man.\" The show then shifts to a song by Barbara Tucker, \"Beautiful People,\" which inspired them to play music inspired by other songs.\n\nThe next song is from Prophetic soul, \"Pyramid,\" which features a sample from \"The Temptations\" from their song \"Ant Too Proud To Beg.\" The next songs are from DJ Cozy, \"Pickup,\" and \"Jai Wolf,\" which reminds him of \"a few years back.\" The last track of the evening is from the Oles, \"Salvation,\" which will be their final track.',NULL,NULL),(69619,87,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/27/Back in the USSR - November 27, 2023 at 23:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-27 23:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-28 07:49:15','2023-11-28 07:06:21','',NULL,NULL),(69620,1447,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/28/Rainbow Country - November 28, 2023 at 00:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-28 00:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-28 07:30:47','2023-11-28 07:07:30','This week on the show, Conchita and her friends, Cora and Hard Cora, appear on the program to discuss their new book, \"Gay Talk,\" which is about their physical and emotional selves. The girls\' names are Barbie Q, and they are known as the \"B-Girls.\" The show is hosted by Mark Tara and produced by Conchita.',NULL,NULL),(69621,1447,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/28/Rainbow Country - November 28, 2023 at 01:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-28 01:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-28 09:27:41','2023-11-28 09:07:09','This is the first song on the Steve Grand tour, and it\'s called \"Rainbow Country.\" It\'s a tribute to all the music that he\'s loved throughout his life, whether it be classic disco, 80s house music, or even more recent independent artists like Grand himself. The song is called \"Everything I Own,\" \"Generations of Love,\" \"The Crying Game,\" \"Walking,\" \"Pink Champagne,\" and \"Don\'t Let The Light In,\" and it comes from Grand\'s latest album, \"Not The End of Me,\" which hit #2 on the Billboard Hot 100 chart and # 7 on the Independent',NULL,NULL),(69622,80,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/28/CFRU Playlist - November 28, 2023 at 06:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-28 06:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-28 13:05:53','2023-11-28 13:05:53',NULL,NULL,NULL),(69623,78,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/28/Morning Soul Shake-Up! - November 28, 2023 at 08:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-28 08:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-28 15:50:45','2023-11-28 15:06:10','This program is all about soul music. It\'s all about the community and how it\'s a great place to live. It starts off with a long description of the community, and then it moves on to a description of soul music and how you can sing along to it. It all ends with a shout-out to the people who are listening to the program.',NULL,NULL),(69624,110,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/28/Here Today - November 28, 2023 at 07:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-28 07:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-28 15:28:33','2023-11-28 15:06:33','On this edition of Know The Land, Byron tells listeners that deer day is here. He explains that the deer are in the rut and that there are lots of deer tracks and signs all around the place. He says that it\'s exciting for him to go out into the wild and track the deer because the population of wild animals has declined significantly. He\'s reading two books: Mammal Tracks, Sign, and Guide to North America Species and The Wildlife Series. He also reads a little bit from a book he\'s been reading.',NULL,NULL),(69625,2653,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/28/Solipsistic Retreat - November 28, 2023 at 10:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-28 10:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-28 17:44:17','2023-11-28 17:07:26','',NULL,NULL),(