st of a Spotify subscription. If you can\'t commit a month, there\'s a way to support the arts without committing a month.',NULL,NULL),(69667,110,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/30/Here Today - November 30, 2023 at 07:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-30 07:00:00',86638720,'2023-11-30 15:31:05','2023-11-30 15:06:34','Aaron Badgley welcomes listeners to his show on CFRU-FM 93.3 and says that he\'s going to play some new music for the hour.\n\nHe\'ll be talking about a local musician named Corey Weeds who is also a producer. He has an album out called Home Cooking, which has a title track called \"Home Cooking\" which is really eloquent. The other artists on the show are: Len Mazzoni, Jenna Nation, The Beatles, Bernard Frazier, Mimo, and Deborah Fajalkovo. Aaron says that the Christmas music he\'ll play this year is going to be pretty good. The first song is by Jenna, who\'s a singer/songwriter. The second is by Len, who is a jazz musician. The third is by the Beatles, who have a new song called \"Now.\n\n\" The fourth is by Bernard Frazier who has a new album coming out in February or March. The fifth is by Mimo who is from Windsor, Ontario. The last song is a new film music video called \"Farewell for Now,\" which is a really nice piece of music. And the final song is from Deborah, who has been working on producing new music all over the world.',NULL,NULL),(69668,173,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/iuic47/Club_Ned_Dec_3_2023_podcast8w10g.mp3','2023-11-30 16:29:11',284131786,'2023-11-30 18:08:37','2023-11-30 17:05:21','',NULL,NULL),(69669,111,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/30/Tales from the Bridge - November 30, 2023 at 09:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-30 09:00:00',86638720,'2023-11-30 17:51:16','2023-11-30 17:06:26','The Transgender Author and Musician Talk about the violin and writing. The author tells us that he picked up the violin as a way to confront his biggest fears and desires within music. He says that the violin is like a voice that finally reaches when it\'s time for him to be a trans man.\n\nWhen he\'s a trans woman , his voice drops to the level of a man\'s voice, but he can still play the violin because his voice finally reaches. He explains that he can sing through his voice because it finally reaches the point where he can be a man. The narrator says that writing allows him to take control of his narrative. It allows his characters to say things that he couldn\'t say otherwise.',NULL,NULL),(69670,112,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/30/FoodFarm Talk - November 30, 2023 at 10:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-30 10:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-30 17:32:35','2023-11-30 17:06:27','In this episode of Food Farm Talk, host Clinton Machuck speaks with Timothy Caulfield, a professor and a well-respected expert on a wide range of topics, from food to health to climate change. We learn that he is a professor in the law and public health departments at the University Alberta.\n\nHe is also an author, a public speaker, and an expert on Netflix. He discusses his passion for science and his involvement with the public sphere. He speaks of the lack of trust in the scientific community in general and in the food and health community in particular. He believes that this is a result of the widespread availability of new technology and new methods of production. He explains that the science is being produced in a time when people lack trust in its usefulness.',NULL,NULL),(69671,189,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/2s2zkf/VFTC_Nov29784d4.mp3','2023-11-30 18:30:42',282287040,'2023-11-30 20:12:36','2023-11-30 19:05:35','The guys are back from Aurelia and they\'re psyched to be back. They\'ve been waiting for a year and a half for them to come back. Kent and Larry have been back for about a year now, and Larry says it\'s been a year since they last saw each other.\n\nThe show they\'ve put on has a history and music theme. The first song is the \"Big Bang Theory\" theme song, and the second song is \"The Bare Naked Ladies