 Karim immediately wanted to know what was the origin of Chet\'s music, and Stewart explains that his father was a big fan. When he was looking for a new music, Stewart says, he decided to go into jazz. Stewart says Chet is a good guy, and that he\'s always been interested in music',NULL,NULL),(69676,205,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/d6i7ij/November_30th_2023_Music_at_High_Noon8lvu6.mp3','2023-11-30 21:39:24',228269056,'2023-12-01 01:06:49','2023-11-30 23:05:45','This week\'s program opens with a track from Outta Sight, a song from the recently released album Music That Kinda Losers, by Autogram. The music starts off with Born Rockers, then it moves on to Love Is for Fools, followed by Everclear, then Santa Monica, then Low of the Low, then Lonely One, then Elephant Stone, then Behind Those Eyes, then Fairy Boat Of the Mind, then Macco Road, then Adam And The Volumes, and finally Mother Tongues.',NULL,NULL),(69677,289,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/aa8pwd/The_Next_Stop_127agsh4.mp3','2023-11-30 22:49:46',271541035,'2023-12-01 00:47:27','2023-11-30 23:05:52','This is the 127th episode of the program. It is hosted by Sage Ranaldo and it airs on CIUT 99.5 FM. The program is free and can be listened to anywhere in the world. Some of the tracks are from the 1973 Western directed by Sam Peckinph and directed by Billy the Kid.\n\nThey have the most famous score from Bob Dylan, which is also one of the songs in the film. If you want to listen to the previous episodes, go to the next stop on the program and listen to them over at the nextstop.pod bean.com. After the opening song, the program will start with some energy. Then it will go into a kind of space music. After that, it will be back to the music. The show will start off with a song from Dylan. The first song is called \"Main Title Theme\" and it is from the film \"Garrett and Billy. The second song is \"City Lights\" from DJ Harrison. The third song is from Alani and Savath and the fourth song is in Tandem from 