fy evidence to support their false accusations. Dean Mitch explains that it is the police that are the problem, not the overall station in general, because it is an individual officer who is the problem.\n\nIt is up to a judge to find him innocent and he is not allowed in the public to do anything about the false accusers. The police are allowed to lie, which is unfair to the public, says Dean Mitch, because they can track him in society. He says he is sorry that he has been caught lying, but he is willing to say anything off the record if the police want him to.',NULL,NULL),(69681,116,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/11/30/T.K.O. - November 30, 2023 at 16:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-11-30 16:00:00',86507648,'2023-11-30 23:28:53','2023-11-30 23:06:53','',NULL,NULL),(69682,182,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/9inpda/NBR_Nov_2920239g1el.mp3','2023-11-30 23:58:36',161493158,'2023-12-01 02:07:48','2023-12-01 01:05:25','In this edition of the No Beat Radio Hour, host Minesh welcomes listeners to the show and thanks them for their financial support. He also encourages listeners to visit the station\'s official website to learn more about the station and to donate to help reach its goal of $100,000 in revenue.\n\nThe show opens with a track by One Drick\'s Point Never, followed by a track called \"Barely Lit Path\", the latest release from the artist Salimi Rose. The song is off of the artist\'s latest release, \"Again,\" and the show is playing first time at The Drake in Toronto on December 7th. The episode ends with the release of a new song by Joseph Shabelson, \"Welcome to Hell.\" The show also includes a release by Jamie Brunk titled \"Prayer for America,\" an album by Indian Jewelry, a release of health and wellness by \"Invasives,\" a brand new release by Joseph, Shabelson\'s \"Welcome,\" and a release from Ed Templeton titled \"Slimmy Rose.\n\n\" The shows that Minesh mentions include a We Are Time showcase at Baby G on December 1 and 2, a showcase by Elle on De