ct in a few weeks, but that they look forward to having him back on the show',NULL,NULL),(69752,108,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/12/03/Wind-Down - December 3, 2023 at 20:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-12-03 20:00:00',86638720,'2023-12-04 03:50:56','2023-12-04 03:06:32','The program begins with a description of the music featured on the show. The first song is from Flight Facilities featuring channel t Trey. The second is from Le Couleur featuring the song DIsre. The third is from Drama. The fourth is from Moon River featuring Gavin Gardner. The fifth is from Seishi She. The sixth is from New Chance and the seventh is from Lee Paradise.\n\nThe seventh is called Lilys Call. The eighth is from Little Dragon featuring all of the reach trims. The ninth is from Onion Kings of Otsego at University Brown in Asian American History. The song is titled No No Boy and it is from a record label called Smithsonian Folkways. The label is part of a research institute at the Smithsonian. It was founded in 1987. The label was established in 1987 by a family of Moses ash under the conditions that the institution continues Ashs policy of eating some notable artists.\n\nLeadbelly, Toronto Harlow Guthrie and now of course No Boy. Serra Willow tells us that he has two more songs to play for us. First, he\'ll play from Kat Clyde with her song Down Rounder I Feel It and the second will play from Feist with her album Multi-tudes with Hideout in the Open',NULL,NULL),(69753,150,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/12/03/Zombie Jamboree - December 3, 2023 at 19:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-12-03 19:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-04 03:33:42','2023-12-04 03:07:10','The first hour of the show starts off with a song by Beirut called \"So Many Plans\" . The second hour starts with \"Lemon Jelly\" and \"Negroid Tension\" and the third hour is \"Migraine\" with Kimi-Jabate on it.\n\nNext up is \"Bitter Sweet Morning\" , followed by \"Personality Surgery\" with Georg Turner . We\'ll hear from the UnDecidab