for the program is \"let them\" and this is what the song is about. The song is called \"Mana\" and the lyrics are from Mexico. The music is also very good.',NULL,NULL),(69800,91,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/12/05/Tuesday at 5 - December 5, 2023 at 17:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-12-05 17:00:00',86638720,'2023-12-06 01:46:46','2023-12-06 01:06:09','Dee Mac, the host of CFRU\'s live music program, introduces us to the show\'s guests. He tells us that if they make the program through December, they\'ll be okay.\n\nHe also tells us about the death of Pogues singer-songwriter, Shane McCowan. He\'s been ill for some time, but his hits include \"The Fairy Tale of NYC\" and \"A Rainy Night in London,\" which are both \"traditional stomping Irish music\" with the \"crashing chords\" of punk. The song is a classic. The band\'s greatest achievement was to bring together traditional Irish music with \"the crashing chords of north London punk\" . Like Brendan Behan, Dylan Thomas, and other Celtic musicians, Shane was an alcoholic who was also a great writer.\n\nBetween the years of 1984 and 1990, the band released a total of five albums with their hits, including \"A Fair of Brown eyes\" and the \"Aryday Night in Soho,\" which were both \"praised as classics.\" Christy McColl, the Pogue\'s lead singer and songwriter, worked with the band on the song \"Fairytale of New York,\" which made the song number two on the Billboard Hot 100 and became a Christmas tradition.',NULL,NULL),(69801,1455,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/12/05/Down the Rabbit Hole - December 5, 2023 at 18:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-12-05 18:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-06 01:28:38','2023-12-06 01:07:11','The narrator continues his story of the month. He begins with a song from the album of jazz drummer Charles Mingus, \"Minus Atum.\" The narrator says he\'s been trying to improve his technique of playing the drums. Next, the narrator listens to two songs from El Reyne\'s new album, \"I Killed Your Dog.\n\n