ator of the Dominican Republic, Fulgencio Batista.',NULL,NULL),(69807,96,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/12/05/Cyber Lich’s Gothic Castle - December 5, 2023 at 23:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-12-05 23:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-06 07:44:44','2023-12-06 07:06:31','Back at the Gothic Castle, we meet up with the band. They\'re talking about the various tracks they\'ve been playing recently. They all sound very similar, and the narrator tells us that they don\'t even like to joke about these kinds of things.\n\nHe explains that they\'re mostly interested in the mental side of things, but that sometimes they\'ll go into dungeons to crack people\'s brains. So yeah, torture is a big part of the show, but it\'s also important to note that this isn\'t just a music show. It\'s a horror show.',NULL,NULL),(69808,109,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/12/06/Radia - December 6, 2023 at 00:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-12-06 00:00:00',86638720,'2023-12-06 07:29:41','2023-12-06 07:06:45','We\'re back with another interview with Hadash\'s Aida Tumas Liman, a Member of the Knesset of Israel. She\'s a political activist and a member of the Communist Party of Israel, the only Jewish Arab political party in the country. She tells us that she\'s been a political party since she was 14 years old. She says that she joined Hadash when she was 21 years old and then she joined the Communist party when she turned 21.\n\nShe explains that her political party is called Hadash, which means \"coalition between the fanatics and supporters.\" It\'s basically a coalition of those who believe in the nine points that the communists agreed upon: peace, reaching for peace, stopping the Israeli occupation, trying to end the occupation, reaching a two state solution, women\'s equality, social rights, workers\' rights, and so on. The nine points are all agreed upon by the political parties in Israel. They\'re all agreed on by the anti-Netanyahu right-wing government, which is led by Netanyahu. The anti-war 