 She has a close relationship with a guy named Hye Sung who she meets in the movie. The music comes from two of David Letterman\'s favorite artists, Christopher Bear and his partner Daniel Rosson, who wrote the music for the film.\n\nWe\'re also going to hear some of the music from some of David\'s other favorite artists from his collection, like Shin Jung and Shin-Jung, who are also on the program. The first song is from Shin Jung, and it\'s called Mind That Wait. The second song is a song by Kim Mi, and the third song is by Jang Hyun. The fourth song is also from Shin-Jeung, and this is called Regret. The fifth track is from the music by Bobby Womack, and then the sixth track is by Nancy Sinatra, and that\'s it. The next song is another from the film, Past',NULL,NULL),(69984,280,'https://mcdn.podbean.com/mf/web/ghzm6t/Episode92_Venezuela99lib.mp3','2023-12-13 23:54:10',84597920,'2023-12-14 01:32:12','2023-12-14 01:05:42','On this episode of CIUT 852, Seth Martosh, the host of the Taylor Report and co-host of the radio show, introduces himself and introduces the show\'s guests. He and Troxel are on a trip to Venezuela and are going to visit a friend of theirs, Eliana Cueva, an artist from Venezuela.\n\nIn addition, they\'re also going to present a show called \"From Abroad\" at the university. The show is about exploring different cultures in the university and giving students a chance to talk about where they come from and what they want to do with their lives. Seth tells us that he\'s trying to raise money for the show, but he thinks they\'ll only be able to raise about ten percent of the way. If you go to the show on CIUT.fm, you can see the program\'s one and only guest, Seth, give an interview in Toronto.\n\nSo they\'ve got some extra incentive to reach the goal. They\'re going to head into their interview with Giovanna, a student from Venezuela who came to Canada when she was 16 years old. She\'s from the fourth largest city in the country. She loves the people there, the beaches, and the nature. She also loves the weather. She says she misses her family there, but she considers Canada her home now. Seth also tells us about his sister, who\'s back in Venezuela. They have a restaurant in the city.',NULL,NULL),(69985,13298,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/12/13/CFRU Selector - December 13, 2023 at 17:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-12-13 17:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-14 01:07:35','2023-12-14 01:07:35',NULL,NULL,NULL),(69986,106,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/12/13/Trail Mix - December 13, 2023 at 20:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-12-13 20:00:00',86638720,'2023-12-14 03:46:50','2023-12-14 03:06:18','',NULL,NULL),(69987,105,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/12/13/B Siide Radio - December 13, 2023 at 19:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-12-13 19:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-14 03:28:36','2023-12-14 03:06:19','The next day, the CFRU board of directors is meeting. This is an opportunity for students to run for board and help out with the station. Students who pay tuition are eligible to become members, but they must register at least thirty days before the meeting. If they haven\'t already done so, they can still vote. If that doesn\'t apply to you, please email the board chair at the station with the subject line \"Annual General Meeting\" . The meeting is on December 14th.',NULL,NULL),(69988,107,'https://archive.cfru.ca/archive/2023/12/13/Tone Zone - December 13, 2023 at 21:00 - CFRU 93.3.mp3','2023-12-13 21:00:00',86507648,'2023-12-14 05:06:08','2023-12-14 05:06:08',NULL,NULL,NULL);
